name: Steven
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this study! The purpose is to get your honest feedback on your experience at and relationship with Sheetz. 

We are looking to understand what purpose it serves in your life. We will also ask you to take us along on your shopping journey in the store.

There are no right or wrong answers – we’re just looking for your completely candid feedback! ALL feedback will be held private and will not be shared beyond the small group of people exploring this category.

Each of the circles on your home screen will explore a different topic.  For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. On a scheduled appointment for follow up, your moderator will ask you follow ups. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

name: Ambivalent 25-34
study_instructions:
LookLook® STUDY:   Fashion | Shopping | Life!

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this LookLook® study on how you shop for fashion today and the role it plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior.  We want to get into the details!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping?

 

Below are the instructions for the study.  Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses.  This is not a survey, it’s a conversation!  Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK:

Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s!  These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe.  It should take about half an hour.

 

GO-TO “LOOKS”

VISUAL:  POST THREE OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS.  We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality.  If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them?  (For ex., one person might have these four: “date night”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out-and-about.” But someone else might have: “client meeting”, “girls’ night”,  “Netflix and Chill”). This is all about your particular life style! Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light.  Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding!  But apparel is the focus of this exercise.

 

COMMENT:  IN EACH POST, tell me the following:  (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who is the designer of each piece and where did you buy? (iii) Where do you typically shop for this type of look? Why?

 

STUDY DAY!  

So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions!  Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment.  Look out for my follow-ups!

 

DISCOVERY AND INSPIRATION

VISUAL:  Post at least three screenshots of places you go online that INSPIRE the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, email from a brand, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.).  Where do you tend to discover new products/styles?  With each one, please complete the comment below:

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “This is ___________.  I go here (insert frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc).  I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”

 

WHY YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Find any image or picture (even an emoji) that represents the feeling that shopping (for apparel and accessories) brings alive in you.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “I chose this image because it represents my feeling of _______________ when I shop for clothes/accessories.” Why do you shop – is it always for replenishment of something you need – or do you shop for fun? At its best, what does a great shopping experience give you?  What really motivates you to make purchases? (ads, promotions, events, Instagram, etc)

 

WHERE YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Think about the top 3 places where you spend the majority of your apparel dollars.  Post a screenshot of each destination (please list at least 2!)

 

COMMENT (FOR EACH):  Please complete in your own words:  “I tend to buy a lot of my fashion here:  _______________________ because  __________________”.  What percentage of your apparel money goes to this place, and why?

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN THE DIGITAL WORLD!

VIDEO:  Next, you’re going shopping on your phone. Just go browsing for fun. You could look for a specific item or you could just go on a favorite site or to a favorite shopping app to look around and see what you like.

 

We want you to record your screen with audio while you do this (instructions below if you are not familiar with how to do this.)

 

Spend about 1-2 minutes browsing for the item. While you’re browsing, just say out loud what you are thinking.  Tell us where you start your search and voice out loud your comments as you browse. As you click through different options, tell me why you are making your choices of where to go and what to look at. After you record for a few minutes, upload your video to LookLook®. Note: you do not have to be a Ninja at this! Just look around and talk to me while you’re browsing on your phone. If you get frustrated for any reason, mention that!

 

How to screen record on an iPhone (please be sure to turn on audio!)

  1. Go to Settings > Control Center > Customize Controls, then tap next to Screen Recording.
  2. Swipe up from the bottom edge of any screen.
  3. Press the record button firmly until the screen recording box comes up (it takes 3 seconds), turn the microphone on, and then tap Start Recording.
  4. Upload your video to LookLook®

 

How to screen record on an Android phone

5.     Download and use the free app Mobizen

6.     Enable sound before recording

7.     Upload your video to LookLook®

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN-STORE)

VISUAL:  As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place.  Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. 

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words:  “Services that I enjoy at my favorite apparel/accessories stores include _______________________”.  These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to styling, events, exclusive product lines, delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a local sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.    

 

HOW IT ALL COMES TOGETHER

VISUAL:  Imagine for a moment that someone handed you the luxury of an entire afternoon to go clothing shopping – just for you.  How would you enjoy this gift of time? Would you curl up on the couch and go shopping online? Would you visit boutiques? A mall? Post a screenshot (or a few) of where you would go shopping.

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Where is this? What do enjoy most about this experience? Provide as much detail as possible!   

 

INTERMIX

 

WHO IS THE INTERMIX WOMAN?

VISUAL:  Please screenshot a picture that represents, in your mind, the woman who shops a lot of Intermix. (If you are not familiar at all with the brand, feel free to check out the website.) This can be anyone!  A celebrity, whatever pops into your head (don’t over think it!)

 

COMMENT:  Please complete: “I chose this image because_____________.” 

 

URGENCY

VISUAL:  Take a screenshot or picture of any type of retailer that you feel more excitement and urgency around shopping vs. Intermix.

 

COMMENT:  What did you choose, and why?  What do you think would give you more of a sense of excitement about getting to know the Intermix experience a bit better?  (Be completely honest!)

name: Thailand
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on enjoyable life experiences! We are excited to learn from you over the next few days as you reflect on what in-person experiences mean to you.  We’ve organized these into a handful of topics to be completed at your leisure over a period of three days, as you can consider them mindfully and can give us thoughtful responses. In this study, pictures, screenshots, and videos are very important for us to understand and visualize the experiences you’re sharing. Please be generous with these throughout – thank you! For timing, please finish answering all the questions by the end of the day on Sunday, October 3rd. On Monday, October 4th, a moderator will be asking you some follow-up questions and those should be answered by Tuesday, October 5th. We’ll be in touch with you throughout, via text/WhatsApp, and we’re happy to answer your questions along the way. Thank you!

study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study on how you make movie choices, and where the movies fit into your overall world of entertainment! 
 
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of where and how movies fit into your life. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Be sure to press SEND after entering your comments!
 
You will not receive notifications on your phone when your moderator starts sending you follow-ups, but you will see that a topic circle turns orange if they have engaged on that topic. You will see their comments marked with an orange symbol: "moderator comment". Your moderator will continue to ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
 
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty! Have fun!

study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Non Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! 

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before you move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!

 

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

 

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'

 

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! We want to see REAL LIFE - the good, the bad and the ugly. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Freshman
Participants
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY:  FOOD AT WORK

Instructions for Participants

 

Welcome to the LookLook® Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing. 

 

The purpose of this study is for us to show us how eating, drinking and other types of experiences affect how people feel at work. What makes you feel comfortable (or uncomfortable), more productive, more motivated, more creative…?  You can even think beyond food to other amenities like fitness centers, amazing décor, collaborative workspaces, etc.

 

We’re looking to find out what really matters to people – perhaps un-earthing some ideas that no one has thought of before!

 

Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions and accompany each with a picture that you either take – or save as a screen grab – and post. It’s all about the details, so NO ONE WORD COMMENTS please! 

 

Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to answer them.  Your moderator will respond with follow-up to many of your posts and answering those will likely take an additional half hour. 

 

Please note we want total candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will do with the study.  If you work in a public space such as a hospital, please avoid showing people in the photos that you take – just focus on the food and amenities! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and is being used for research purposes only. 

 

Finally, please label your answers with the letters and numbers as they are outlined in the instructions (#1a, #3b, etc)

 

THE QUESTIONS

 

1.      HOW YOU START YOUR DAY

a.      Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture:  is this at home, at work, during your commute?  How typical is this – or does it vary by day?

b.      Screenshot and post an emoji or other image that represents the vibe of where you work.  What three words describe how you feel at work on a typical day?

 

2.      Next, we want to see your food and drink options!  Do you have a café or cafeteria?  Is there a convenience store?  Please take a trip to the spots that are available to you for meals and take pictures to show what is offered.  If it is a café or cafeteria, please visit each station.  Don’t forget drinks and coffee/tea!  For each option please answer the following:

a.      How could the quality be improved?  (Freshness, taste, variety, etc?)

b.      Is it healthy enough for your tastes?  If not, how would you improve it?

c.       How convenient is it?  Could technology play a role in some way that would make its delivery more convenient?

d.      Are you able to personalize it to the extent that you wish? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative?

 

3.      Now, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work.  Where are there snacks available (ie vending, coffee shops, convenience stores, etc)?  Please take a picture of each option and answer:

a.      What is this?  How would you describe the quality?

b.      How convenient is it?

c.       How healthy is it?  Anything you would change on that front?

d.      Can you personalize it?

 

4.      This section is about where you eat AWAY from work.

a.      Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please take screenshots of the places near work where you go most often when not eating at the office, and answer the following:

                                                              i.      What is the name of this place?

                                                             ii.      What do you like about this place?

                                                           iii.      How often do you come here?

                                                           iv.      What adjectives describe the atmosphere of this place?  Do you wish there was something like this offered at your work?

 

5.      Finally, think about your comfort level at work.  What could be added to your work environment that would really lower your stress level and make it more fun, enjoyable and pleasant to be there? What would really blow your mind and surprise and delight you?   Grab a few screenshots of ideas that represent your ideas. With each one, tell me what it is and how you would like to see it brought to life.

  Please note:  If one of your posts does not show a checkmark, there is likely a follow-up to answer.  You will be compensated when you have answered all questions! Have fun, and thanks for participating!

name: Freshman
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™: Campus Life Food Study
Part I: Complete prior to Tuesday, April 10th Part II: Complete on Wednesday, April 11th Welcome to the LOOK-LOOK™ New York University Campus Life Food Study! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOK-LOOK™ screen. This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus. We don’t need you to write us a novel on every food choice. We just want you to simply take pictures of everything you choose to eat (and where you are eating it). These will be the basis of discussion for us to ask you about the surrounding experience of those food choices. Beyond the food itself, we also want to understand the importance of the overall environment (look, feel, seating, general vibe, etc.), the customer service, and anything else that’s important to you. We realize you are busy – and perhaps can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting you’re experiences. That’s ok – the beauty of Look-LookTM is that you can snap pictures (or video, if you are motivated), save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. DO THIS WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! HERE ARE THE TASKS: If possible, please do Part I before the study begins on February 8th, or at least before you move on to Part II. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or coffee time. PART I YOU
  1. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:
    1. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?
    2. What is important to you when it comes to food? Anything from “Chef-prepared” to local ingredients, to sustainable practices, etc.?
  2. Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like. How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots here but no stock photos please!
YOUR SCHOOL
3. What adjectives describe the unique culture of NYU?
FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL 4. Which dining facilities do you tend to use most often at school? What are the main points of contact you come into on a daily basis that offer you food or drink? (This can include on or off campus.) Please take pictures to show us each and every single one – down to the condiments for your tea or coffee. This is all about the details! 5. Upload a photo that represents how you feel about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen that photo and what does that photo represent? Are there any new facilities offering anything different or exciting? If so, please visit and photograph for us, with your opinions about it! 6. Are there any branded franchises on the campus today (i.e. Starbucks, etc.) – or if not, are there ones you’d be delighted to see? Take a picture or screenshot of any you’d like to see added to the mix. 7. What (if anything) do you miss from home – food-wise? Take a picture to represent it! Do you think there’s any way to replicate this on-campus in any way? PART II FOOD JOURNAL 8. We want to understand all points of availability of food that you experience during a typical day, and how campus dining fits in. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.
  1. What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue?
  2. What are you eating?
  3. Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now?
  4. What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts? What was great – or what could be better?
9. What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

name: Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! 

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before you move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: 3 Bilingual Non-Light Drinker
study_instructions:
We are very excited to have you participate in our research project! As was previously mentioned to you, prior to the online group discussion we would like to get to know you a little bit, and the way we would like to do this is by having you create some brief videos. 

A few things to keep in mind when recording your videos:
• Sometimes it helps to have a friend or family member hold the camera so you can focus on what you are talking about rather than worrying about holding the camera.
• Make sure you or whoever is filming holds the camera as still as possible (no shaking or jarring movements).
• Avoid any background noise or music - this often becomes much louder in the recording.
• Pause for two seconds at the beginning and end of your video to make sure your response isn't cut off at all.
• Before submitting your video(s), watch it to make sure everything looks/sounds okay:  
• Are you facing the right direction? It's easy to accidentally end up with sideways footage if you turn your smartphone while filming, and we want to avoid that happening!
• Is the lighting bright enough so we can see you and what you are recoding?
• Did you speak loud enough so we can clearly hear all that you are saying?

name: American Participants
study_instructions: Congratulations again on your selection to be part of The Global Luxury Collective! Thank you again for your effort to let us get to know you; we are so excited to start hearing your opinions on EVERYTHING. In this first month, we are looking to understand your top-of-mind thoughts on luxury and how the pandemic has affected your ideas about what looks and feels like luxury. As always, there are no right or wrong answers – every person is different! And very importantly - please share pictures and screenshots that truly bring alive your responses so that we can see the world through your eyes. This panel is all about capturing real life in shimmering detail. At the first of every month, there will be a new set of questions for you to answer, and you’ll always have about 4-5 days the following week to respond at your leisure. For this first set, please complete by Tuesday evening April 6th! Thanks - and have fun!

name: Sophomores
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Unassigned
study_instructions: Welcome to Part 2 of our discussion on CAD | CAM | CAE programs. Your input was so insightful and helpful the first time around that we now want to invite you into the creative process a bit. Based on your feedback, some new creative layouts have been developed and we would love to get your reactions to them. When you engage with the topics and questions, please reply with an honest, thorough, and thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. Your responses are anonymized and are STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. There are no “wrong” answers; we just want your honest opinions! Thanks!

name: Seoul
study_instructions: 세계 최초의 글로벌 럭셔리 연구에 참여하시게 된 것을 진심으로 환영합니다! 저희 LookLook®과 함께 여러분의 럭셔리에 대한 관심을 공유해주세요. 이미지 업로드 시 브랜드 명을 꼭 남겨주시기 바라며, 곧 더욱 재밌고 깊은 주제로 이야기를 나누어보아요!

name: Mexico
study_instructions: Felicidades, has sido elegido para un estudio divertido en el cual hablaremos de las experiencias agradables que has vivido. Estamos emocionados en aprender a lo largo de los siguientes días, durante los cuales tu meditarás lo que para ti es, el significado de experiencias en persona. Hemos estructurado un pequeño número de temas para que los completes en tu tiempo libre durante un período de tres días y considerarlos con detenimiento para darnos una opinión meditada. En este estudio las fotos, capturas de pantalla y videos son muy importantes para que comprendamos y visualicemos las experiencias que tu nos comuniques. Por favor se generoso de compartir estos materiales en todo momento. ¡Gracias! Para la cronograma, el viernes 1 de octubre serás invitado a responder algunas preguntas. Favor de contestar estas preguntas antes del domingo 3 de octubre. El lunes 4 de octubre un moderador te hará unas preguntas de seguimiento que deberán responderse antes del martes 5 de octubre. Estaremos en contacto contigo en todo momento a través de mensajes de texto / WhatsApp y estaremos encantados de contestar tus preguntas durante este proceso. ¡Gracias!

name: Poland
study_instructions: Gratulujemy bycia wybranym do tego ekscytującego badania na temat przyjemnych doświadczeń życiowych! Cieszymy się, że w ciągu najbliższych kilku dni, będziemy mogli się dowiedzieć wiecej o Tobie  podczas Twojej refleksji  nad tym, co oznaczają dla Ciebie te osobiste doświadczenia. Zorganizowaliśmy nasze pytania w kilka tematów/kategorii przewodnich, które będziesz mógł przeanalizować w wolnym czasie, w przeciągu trzech dni. Przemyśl je dokładnie i udziel nam szczegółowych odpowiedzi. W tym badaniu zdjęcia, zrzuty ekranu i filmiki są dla nas bardzo ważne - pomogą nam zrozumieć i zwizualizować doświadczenia, którymi się dzielisz. Prosimy hojnie się nimi podzielić! W odniesieniu do czasu wymaganego do ukończenia tego badania, zaprosimy Cię do odpowiadania na pytania w piątek, 1 października.  Proszę zakończyć odpowiadanie na te pytania do niedzieli 3 października.  W poniedziałek 4 października, moderator zada Ci kilka dodatkowych pytań, na które należy odpowiedzieć do wtorku 5 października.  Przez cały czas będziemy z Tobą w kontakcie za pośrednictwem wiadomości SMS/WhatsApp i z przyjemnością odpowiemy na Twoje pytania.  Dziękuję Ci!

name: Sophomores
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Gen Z Fashion
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on fashion and your lifestyle in the 21st century! Virtual fashion is a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Because it is such an experiential idea, we’ll be asking you to go online and on your phone as part of this study to try out some new technologies, which are in the early stages… so a lot of this will be about using your imagination and thinking conceptually. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. If screen recordings are new for you, let us know and we’ll send you demos. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by Friday August 6th. Starting on an assigned day around August 7-11, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: Non Freshman
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™: Campus Life Food Study
Part I: Complete prior to Tuesday, April 10th Part II: Complete on Wednesday, April 11th Welcome to the LOOK-LOOK™ New York University Campus Life Food Study! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOK-LOOK™ screen. This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus. We don’t need you to write us a novel on every food choice. We just want you to simply take pictures of everything you choose to eat (and where you are eating it). These will be the basis of discussion for us to ask you about the surrounding experience of those food choices. Beyond the food itself, we also want to understand the importance of the overall environment (look, feel, seating, general vibe, etc.), the customer service, and anything else that’s important to you. We realize you are busy – and perhaps can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting you’re experiences. That’s ok – the beauty of Look-LookTM is that you can snap pictures (or video, if you are motivated), save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. DO THIS WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! HERE ARE THE TASKS: If possible, please do Part I before the study begins on February 8th, or at least before you move on to Part II. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or coffee time. PART I YOU
  1. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:
    1. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?
    2. What is important to you when it comes to food? Anything from “Chef-prepared” to local ingredients, to sustainable practices, etc.?
  2. Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like. How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots here but no stock photos please!
YOUR SCHOOL
3. What adjectives describe the unique culture of NYU?
FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL 4. Which dining facilities do you tend to use most often at school? What are the main points of contact you come into on a daily basis that offer you food or drink? (This can include on or off campus.) Please take pictures to show us each and every single one – down to the condiments for your tea or coffee. This is all about the details! 5. Upload a photo that represents how you feel about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen that photo and what does that photo represent? Are there any new facilities offering anything different or exciting? If so, please visit and photograph for us, with your opinions about it! 6. Are there any branded franchises on the campus today (i.e. Starbucks, etc.) – or if not, are there ones you’d be delighted to see? Take a picture or screenshot of any you’d like to see added to the mix. 7. What (if anything) do you miss from home – food-wise? Take a picture to represent it! Do you think there’s any way to replicate this on-campus in any way? PART II FOOD JOURNAL 8. We want to understand all points of availability of food that you experience during a typical day, and how campus dining fits in. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.
  1. What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue?
  2. What are you eating?
  3. Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now?
  4. What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts? What was great – or what could be better?
9. What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

name: Other Offsite
Non-Lululemon Purchasers
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: Fitness Gear, Props and Accessories

Congratulations on being selected for this study on fitness gear, props and accessories! You’ve been selected for this elite panel because you are serious about your fitness, your wellness and specifically because you are into at least one of these three fitness activities:

(a)   Running

(b)   Training

(c)    Yoga/Barre/Pilates

 

While you may take part in a number of fitness activities, we specifically want to explore the gear and accessories you invest in for your primary fitness activities – the ones you take most seriously and do most often – as well as any other health and wellness focused activities.

   

Fitness accessories can be anything from what you carry to and from a work out, to what you use during, or after a workout! (i.e. socks, bags, mats, at-home equipment, rollers, massage balls, cold weather accessories – anything!)

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

OVERVIEW:

There are three parts to this study. 

(i)              First, we want to get to know you a bit. You can answer these questions as soon as you post your selfie.

(ii)            Next, we want you to keep a diary of how you use your gear/props/accessories for two separate workout occasions over the next four days, ideally one day over the weekend and one day over the week. (We want to see how your weekend fitness activity may be different from a weekday.)

(iii)           Finally, as a bit of a wrap-up on Tuesday June 11th we’ll be engaging in some back and forth discussion about how your fitness activity fits into your overall wellness strategy!

 

 

GETTING TO KNOW YOU: A DEEP DIVE ON BAGS AND SOCKS

 

1.     VISUAL: Think about an image that represents how you feel when you get the MOST out of your workout routine and post a screenshot that depicts that feeling. COMMENT: Tell me why you chose this and provide a few adjectives that describe the feeling.

 

2.     VIDEO – YOUR SOCK WARDROBE: Gather all of the socks that you wear most frequently both to work out and in day to day life. Choose only items you purchased for yourself (no gifts or generic items; we’re interested in brands here.) Group your socks into categories and lay them out. Then have a friend or family member film you while you show me the socks in each category and answer the following:

a.     Why did you group the socks into these categories? Which socks do you use for fitness and which are worn day to day, and which for both? What features make a sock good for one or the other, or both?

b.    What do you get out these socks? What benefits do each of the categories provide?

c.     What brands are your socks? What do you count on those brands for when it comes to socks?

name: Women
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™ Study: Migraine Solutions

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ Study on Migraine Solutions!

You've been selected for this particular study because you’ve suffered from migraines and are somewhat familiar with migraine related medications.

We are exploring how to simply describe a new prescription medicine for the treatment of migraine when you feel one coming on. Rest assured that when this new medicine comes out there will be complete information available on it. It is a tablet that dissolves under your tongue with no water needed. It has been tested on thousands of people, and we do know that it has very few, mild side effects. It will be covered by insurance, Medicare, and Medicaid. It is safe for people with high blood pressure. It starts working in 30 minutes and gives nearly full relief in two hours or less for pain and nausea. Right now, we are trying to come up with a “headline thought” – a simple summary to describe how it works. One that would pique your curiosity enough to want to learn more.

You can work through the study at your leisure, we estimate it may take between an hour to an hour and a half of your time – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along. A blue check mark in the thumbnail for each post indicates that the post has been resolved to the moderator’s satisfaction. If there is not a check mark on a post it means that the moderator may want to ask you further questions on your comment. Below are the tasks that we need you to complete. We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun! We look forward to your feedback.

 

THE TASKS

  1. FEELINGS ASSOCIATED WITH MIGRAINES
    1. Upload a photo (this can be a personal photo or a screen grab) that best represents how you feel when you experience a migraine. Please describe why you chose this photo in the comments.
  2. RESPONSE TO DESCRIPTIVE CONTENT
    1. Your moderator will push through some descriptive statements about how the new treatment works. In response to each statement please answer the following question: MY FIRST REACTION TO THIS STATEMENT IS_________. Please respond to all follow-up questions asked by your moderator on these posts.

Thank you for your participation!  You are complete when you have answered all of our follow-up questions.

name: Anna
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Athleisure Discovery

 

INTRODUCTION:

Congratulations on being selected for this study on athleisure’s role in your life and how you explore brands online!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolve” the post. Resolved posts will have a blue check mark on them. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-WORK VIDEO

Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignment during the weekend prior to the study.

 

Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out three (3) of your favorite athleisure and/or activewear items on your bed.

 

Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following: 

 

Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM.  If you want to submit three separate videos, that’s cool.  Or you would rather do the three pieces in one take, that is also fine – but please limit the length of the video to about 2 minutes total.

 

1.     What brand is this? Where did you buy it (if online, please specify)? When did you buy it? And why did you buy it?

2.     Roughly how much of your athleisure/activewear wardrobe is made up of this brand?

3.     What do you do while wearing this piece? (Exercise, lounge, etc). We are super interested in what items you choose for certain workout or non-workout activities!

4.     What product characteristics make this item good for doing that?  (Speak to fit, feel, function, style – whatever is important to you and for that activity!)

5.     Finally, how do you feel when wearing it?

 

DAY ONE:  A DAY IN YOUR LIFE!

 

1.     VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever it is that you see when you wake up!

COMMENT: What are we seeing here?  How are you feeling at this moment about the day ahead? 

 

2.     VISUAL: Take a picture or two of anything that is part of your morning ritual, from coffee to breakfast, to your commute, to meditation or exercise.

COMMENT: How do each of these elements make you feel?  What do you get out of it?

 

3.     VISUAL: Upload a few screenshots – or take pictures – of a few things that represent things that bring you JOY or INSPIRE YOU.

COMMENT:

·       What is this? Why are you passionate about this?

·       What is one goal you have that feels difficult to achieve but you REALLY WANT? What is standing in the way (if anything)?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of your work/studying or other primary activity during the day.

COMMENT:

·       How do you feel at various points of time during the primary part of your day?

·       What are the “pain points” (if any?)

·       What parts do you generally enjoy the most?

 

5.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of the most SOCIAL part of your day.

COMMENT: Who are you interacting with? How do you feel at these times?

 

6.     VISUAL: Think for a minute about the news and content/entertainment that draws you in (we’ll get to social media in a second.) Upload some screenshots that fill me in on the kind of content you enjoy.

COMMENT: What do you enjoy about these choices? What do you think they say about you?

 

7.     VISUAL: Now consider social media: Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn, Reddit, etc. Upload a screenshot or two that tells me which you engage with the most.

COMMENT:

·       For each, describe your way of participating. Do you observe more, or post more?

·       What do you enjoy about each social platform that you’re involved with? How important is it to you?

·       What brands or influencers do you follow on social media, and what do you get out of it?

·       What is your favorite brand to follow? Why? How has this impacted your perception of the brand? Your likelihood to purchase that brand?

 

8.     VISUAL: If you exercise at all regularly, please upload a picture of you doing what you do – i.e. workout, running, a fitness class, etc.

COMMENT:

·       Why do you exercise?

·       How important is exercising to you?

·       What is your favorite way to sweat? How frequently do you do this – and are there any other parts to your fitness repertoire?

·       How do you feel during exercising? Afterwards? Does this vary by activity?

 

9.     VISUAL:  We’re living in an age of technology obsession. Take a picture of any device or app that you are currently enjoying. 

COMMENT: What do you love about this? Do you ever use any tech as part of your fitness routine (apps, wearables, etc)? Why or why not?

 

10.  VISUAL: When evening rolls around, take a picture that tells me what you do for relaxation, or any other kind of evening activity or ritual.

COMMENT: What is it and what do you like about this?

 

11.  VISUAL: As you reflect on the day, what do you wish you could spend MORE time doing (if anything)? Upload a photo or screenshot to represent that.

COMMENT: Finally, if you had all the time in the world, what would you like to spend more time doing? Why?

 

PLEASE NOTE: Feel free to “ad lib” in this Day in the Life section and share additional photos, screenshots and comments about anything that tells me WHAT MAKES YOU YOU!  Food and drink choice posts are also super relevant and interesting here!

 

DAY TWO: LULULEMON & OTHER BRANDS – HOW DO YOU EXPLORE THEM?

 

12.  VISUAL:  Please take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? 

COMMENT:  FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how? 

 

13.  VISUAL: When you hear the lululemon name or see the logo, what comes immediately to mind? Upload a screenshot that represents this (it can be anything – be conceptual and creative!).

COMMENT: To what extend would you agree “lululemon is a brand for me” on a scale of 1-5 (with 5 being the strongest)? Why?

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™ Study: Butler University Dining Program

 

Part I:  Complete prior to Monday October 8th

Part II:  Complete on Tuesday October 9th

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ Butler University Campus Life Food Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus.

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them!  Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where and what you are eating!  With EACH of those posts, please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS!  You’re getting paid for your opinions as well as showing us what is available to you!

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook™ is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

 Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Monday, October 8th.

 Please complete Part II on Tuesday, October 9th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee.

 Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Tuesday, October 9th.

PART I

YOU

1.     FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a.     How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b.     What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience?  Health?  Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?

2.     Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots from your camera roll here but make sure to use real photos!

YOUR SCHOOL

3.     Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at Butler.  What adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body?  What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4.     Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus.  This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it.  How can it be improved?  We want details here, down to the condiments for your tea or coffee. 

5.     Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6.     Are you on a meal plan? Why or why not?  If you’re an upperclassman, what do you recall about your experience on the meal plan?

7.     How do you feel about the branded franchises that exist on the Butler campus today (ie coffee shops, fast food etc) – are there others you’d be delighted to see?  Take a picture of one of these if possible.

8.     What do you miss about the way you eat when you’re not at school?  Any aspects of living at home that you miss when it comes to food, drink, etc?

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

9.     Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit.  For each, please answer:  when do you tend to go here?  How often?  Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? 

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL

10.  We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that.  It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE. 

a.     What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends?

b.     What are you eating?

c.     Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now?

d.     What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts?  What was great – or what could be better?

11.  PIE IN THE SKY

a.     What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. 

Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

name: Main Campus
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: UK iPhone Older
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study! We are looking to understand your lifestyle, values, and attitudes towards technology.
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of your experience with technology.  
For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow up questions throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: Current Guests
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOKTM STUDY: Athleisure & Life INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-LookTM study on the role that athleisure plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you buy nice-quality athleisure but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and passions. If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-LookTM, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does it mean for you to live a balanced life, and how do you make quality choices in today’s busy world? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. DAY ONE: A Day in Your Life
Today, I want to understand what it’s like to be you. We’d like you to document your day with visuals and send us comments on what you are doing and how you’re feeling at key points of your day. Before we get started with that, let’s start with a few questions specific to athleisure – then we’ll get on with documenting your day! VISUAL: Take a picture of a few of your favorite and most often-worn pieces of athleisure, whether it’s a jacket, shorts, pants, tank, warm-up, etc.
COMMENT: FOR EACH, tell me the following: (i) What draws you to wearing this? (ii) Where and why did you buy it? VISUAL: Take a screenshot of the stores/sites where you buy most of your athleisure. COMMENT: FOR EACH, (i) What do you count on from this store/website? What kind of athleisure do you buy here and why?
 
Thank you! Now let’s get started with “A Day in My Life!” Below are a few prompts to get you started. VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever you see when you wake up in the morning. COMMENT: What’s going through my head right now is ____________________. VISUAL: Take a few shots of your morning ritual(s). From getting ready to morning coffee, what is the rhythm of your morning? Show me.
COMMENT: Here, I’m [doing]_____________________. Feeling _____________. As you progress through your day, we’re not just interested in what you’re doing but how you’re feeling – when are you feeling good... and when are you stressed... bored, etc. Activities to document can include: work, running around, shopping, errands, spiritual practices, fitness, sports, relaxing, ... really, anything that normally falls into place during a given weekday/evening. We really want to understand what your daily rhythm feels like. Important: please show us a picture of some things you enjoy doing on the weekends as well! By the way, we know you’re on your phone during the day and we want to understand that too! What do you spend time on your phone doing most often – group chats? Insta/FB/Snapchat/YouTube? Games? Shopping? Fantasy football? Please send me screenshots of your phone activity. REALLY IMPORTANT: With each post, tell me something in the spirit of “This is me, [doing] _________. I’m feeling ________ because ____________.” Looking for honesty here, real life, not perfection! I will respond with follow up questions in the evening, so look for the notifications that take you to my questions, either that night or first thing in the morning before we get started with Day 2. Any post with a blue dot signals there’s something from me to respond to. This will be different for everyone, but I’m expecting to see a minimum of 20 posts from you but we love photos and thoughtful comments so please be generous!
 
DAY TWO: Lululemon
So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups!
  1. VISUAL: Take a few pictures now (or screenshots) of several things that inspire you! Anything that gives you energy and inspiration to achieve your dreams, goals, desires, etc.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and it inspires me because _____________.
  2. VISUAL: Next, think about anything you've been contemplating doing in your life that you haven't yet done. Take a picture or grab a screenshot of something that represents that desire/goal and tell me what is holding you back from doing it. COMMENT: This is _______________ and it represents my desire to __________. What might be holding me back from doing this is ________________________.
  3. VISUAL: Next, what are a few of your personal passions? You may have touched on these yesterday, but really spell it out for me now. What do you love and get excited about? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.
  4. VISUAL: Show me several screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of athleisure you buy. Where do you discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below:
    COMMENT: This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.
  5. VISUAL: Take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? COMMENT: FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how?
  6. VISUAL: Screenshot something that represents the Lululemon brand. Could be a storefront or the logo. COMMENT: What are three juicy adjectives that come to mind when you see this brand or hear it mentioned? Why?
  1. VISUAL: Choose a screenshot that represents the personality of lululemon. COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? How is Lululemon distinct from other athleisure brands in its personality? For ex, if Nike, Lululemon, Under Armor, Reebok and any other athleisure brands in your consideration set were all at a party, how would they all interact? (What would they drive to the party, show up wearing, choose to drink, want to dance to, hang out with... what energy would they bring? etc). Please have fun with this question – no one-sentence answers! J
  2. VISUAL: Take a screenshot of something that represents the universal archetype that Lululemon fulfills, in your personal experience. Examples of this might be: a “Sage”, a “Hero”, a “Magician”, a “Rebel”, a “Creator” or an “Everyman” (For example, Amazon Prime might be considered a “hero” archetype because it reliably delivers things quickly to your doorstep.) COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? Finally, if Lululemon disappeared from the face of the earth tomorrow – what would the world be suddenly missing?
PERSONAL VIDEO
Your final task before completion will be to ask a friend or family member to record you talking about a specific subject that your moderator will choose, based on your two-day dialogue. It will probably be one of your areas of interest/passions. Stay tuned! This does not need to feel produced or rehearsed – we just want you to speak honestly from the heart, “off the cuff”, so to speak. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

We will go deeper into these subjects when we meet up next week! Thanks!

name: Alphas
study_instructions:
Welcome to the Luxury Jewelry and Watches Study!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

You have been chosen for this very selective study because you have great taste, and you buy luxury jewelry. This is not a focus group, although we do want your opinions. But we also want your input on how to revitalize a storied European luxury jewelry and watches brand. Therefore, we refer to this type of project as co-creation. We are looking for your ideas as well as your honest take on some jewelry designs. The voice of this brand should be developed to reach women like you.

We appreciate how busy you all are. In order for the study to be successful, the following questions must be completed and submitted on LOOKLOOK™ prior to the first scheduled day of your participation. Please do ‘Task 1: Selfie Time’ and answer all 4 questions and their subparts.

FIRST TASK: IT’S SELFIE TIME!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

Now, please upload photos of yourself wearing the pieces of jewelry you described to Susan when you spoke. For each of the pictures you have sent, please specify:

o   Was this a gift or did you buy it for yourself?  

o   Where was it purchased?

o   How did you discover this piece? What made you covet it?

THE QUESTIONS

On LOOKLOOK™, you will be prompted where to put these answers.

1.    SHOPPING FOR THE JEWELRY AND WATCH BRANDS YOU LOVE

 

a.    When you purchase jewelry, is it typically for a milestone, a seasonal  purchase, or an impulse buy?

b.   What are 1 or 2 of your favorite luxury jewelry/watch brands, and why?

c.    Do you browse for jewelry in stores or online?

o   If you browse in store, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite stores.

o   If you browse online, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite sites.

d.   When it’s time to purchase jewelry, do you do it in store or online? Or both?

e.    Is it different for watches?

 

2.    TELL ME ABOUT YOUR STYLE

 

a.    What 3  adjectives would you choose to describe your personal style (in general?)

b.   Please also upload 2 or 3 photos that demonstrate how you like to wear jewelry.

o   What rings do you wear?

o   What is your wrist look? Do you like to stack, mix designs, alloys, etc. or do you prefer to match?

o   What earring do you like to wear? Studs, cuffs, drop, etc.?

o   What necklaces do you like to wear? Do you like to layer them or wear one at a time?

o   Do you wear the same jewelry day and night or do you switch for evening?

c.    Do your jewelry pieces serve different needs (ie investment, statement, everyday)? How often do you  make fine jewelry purchases?

d.   List 1 or 2 of your favorite brands outside of jewelry (can be anything!)

 

3.YOUR MEDIA DIET

 

a.    Which of the following media do you use regularly (for anything – in general – not just shopping!)

o   Social media - If yes, what platforms?  

o   Websites - What sites?

o   Print magazines - Which ones? Subscribe or buy occasionally?  

o   Anything else? (Satellite Radio? Podcasts?)

o   TV Shows (Netflix? Cable?)

 

4.    WHAT YOU LOVE

a.    What are you most passionate about in life – other than your family? Take a  screenshot or picture that illustrates 1 or 2 of those interests.

b.   Where do you like to travel? 

c.    What happens to be on your wish list for your next jewelry purchase? Why do you love it? How did it get on your radar?

 

Thank you for completing the questions above! On your scheduled day of participation, your moderator will let you know what brand we are focusing on for the remainder of the study, and will start unveiling the pieces to you for your feedback! You get to take a break from sending us pictures.

At the time, please respond to your moderator’s queries on each specific piece. When you are done, your moderator will send through a bit of the background story on the brand we’re focusing on. Once you’ve read that, you are done with Day One!  

The focus of Day Two will be helping us come up with great creative ideas!
