study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on fashion and your lifestyle in the 21st century! Virtual fashion is a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of this concept these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by end of day. Saturday August 21st. Starting on an assigned day around August 23-26, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: Non-Frappe Drinkers
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study! We are excited to learn from you throughout the next couple of weeks. There are two phases to this study. In the first part, I want to learn about your tastes and preferences in general. We will be asking some open-ended questions about certain topics, as well as asking you to upload some pictures and videos. Later on, in Phase Two, we’ll invite you to a new study. Before that one starts, you will receive a new product to unbox and taste, giving us your honest feedback on the experience along the way! Each topic on your LookLook home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! Have fun!

name: Freshman
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Aspirants
study_instructions: Congrats on being contacted for this fun study on plant-based food options! No matter where you are on your journey with plant-based eating, we want to understand your perspective. There are no right or wrong answers. We’re simply interested in your honest opinions on the products and choices we’ll be discussing. You have a week to complete the study at your own pace. The one important thing to note is that we need you to complete a food diary for two subsequent days, as part of the study, recording what you eat, where, why, etc. It’s important that eat and make choices as you normally do during those days. We want real life!  And, it’s <u>totally fine</u> if you eat meat during these two days if that is what you would normally do. We’re interested in the dynamics around these daily choices! Topics One, Two and Three cover your lifestyle and attitude towards plant-based foods. Topics Four & Five consist of a food diary – we just really want to see what you eat during the course of a normal day! Topic Six – you take us on a little shopping trip to buy some plant-based frozen food! Topic Seven – we’ll focus on a specific brand of plant-based food and wrap up the discussion. We will be asking for lots of screenshots and one piece of video at the end where you talk to the camera briefly in your own words. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by July 30. Beginning the week of August 2nd, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: Brazil
study_instructions: Parabéns por ter sido selecionado para este estudo divertido que falará sobre as experiências agradáveis da vida! Estamos super empolgados para aprender com você nos próximos dias, conforme você for compartilhando o que as experiências pessoais significam para você.  Nós organizamos essa experiência em um punhado de tópicos a serem concluídos em seu momento lazer ao longo de um período de três dias, assim você pode refletir com atenção e nos dar respostas bem pensadas. Neste estudo, imagens, capturas de tela e vídeos são muito importantes para entendermos e visualizarmos as experiências que você está compartilhando. Por favor, seja generoso com tudo isso - obrigado! Seguem algumas informações sobre a duração e tempo das questões. Pediremos que você comece a responder às perguntas na sexta-feira, 1º de outubro. Por favor, termine de responder a essas perguntas até domingo, 3 de outubro. Na segunda-feira, 4 de outubro, o(a) moderador(a) fará algumas perguntas de acompanhamento e elas devem ser respondidas até terça-feira, 5 de outubro. Estaremos em contato com você durante todo o processo, via SMS / WhatsApp, e responderemos quaisquer perguntas que tenham ao longo do caminho. Obrigado!

name: Potential Guests
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOKTM STUDY: Athleisure & Life INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-LookTM study on the role that athleisure plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you buy nice-quality athleisure but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and passions. If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-LookTM, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does it mean for you to live a balanced life, and how do you make quality choices in today’s busy world? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. DAY ONE: A Day in Your Life
Today, I want to understand what it’s like to be you. We’d like you to document your day with visuals and send us comments on what you are doing and how you’re feeling at key points of your day. Before we get started with that, let’s start with a few questions specific to athleisure – then we’ll get on with documenting your day! VISUAL: Take a picture of a few of your favorite and most often-worn pieces of athleisure, whether it’s a jacket, shorts, pants, tank, warm-up, etc.
COMMENT: FOR EACH, tell me the following: (i) What draws you to wearing this? (ii) Where and why did you buy it? VISUAL: Take a screenshot of the stores/sites where you buy most of your athleisure. COMMENT: FOR EACH, (i) What do you count on from this store/website? What kind of athleisure do you buy here and why?
 
Thank you! Now let’s get started with “A Day in My Life!” Below are a few prompts to get you started. VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever you see when you wake up in the morning. COMMENT: What’s going through my head right now is ____________________. VISUAL: Take a few shots of your morning ritual(s). From getting ready to morning coffee, what is the rhythm of your morning? Show me.
COMMENT: Here, I’m [doing]_____________________. Feeling _____________. As you progress through your day, we’re not just interested in what you’re doing but how you’re feeling – when are you feeling good... and when are you stressed... bored, etc. Activities to document can include: work, running around, shopping, errands, spiritual practices, fitness, sports, relaxing, ... really, anything that normally falls into place during a given weekday/evening. We really want to understand what your daily rhythm feels like. Important: please show us a picture of some things you enjoy doing on the weekends as well! By the way, we know you’re on your phone during the day and we want to understand that too! What do you spend time on your phone doing most often – group chats? Insta/FB/Snapchat/YouTube? Games? Shopping? Fantasy football? Please send me screenshots of your phone activity. REALLY IMPORTANT: With each post, tell me something in the spirit of “This is me, [doing] _________. I’m feeling ________ because ____________.” Looking for honesty here, real life, not perfection! I will respond with follow up questions in the evening, so look for the notifications that take you to my questions, either that night or first thing in the morning before we get started with Day 2. Any post with a blue dot signals there’s something from me to respond to. This will be different for everyone, but I’m expecting to see a minimum of 20 posts from you but we love photos and thoughtful comments so please be generous!
 
DAY TWO: Lululemon
So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups!
  1. VISUAL: Take a few pictures now (or screenshots) of several things that inspire you! Anything that gives you energy and inspiration to achieve your dreams, goals, desires, etc.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and it inspires me because _____________.
  2. VISUAL: Next, think about anything you've been contemplating doing in your life that you haven't yet done. Take a picture or grab a screenshot of something that represents that desire/goal and tell me what is holding you back from doing it. COMMENT: This is _______________ and it represents my desire to __________. What might be holding me back from doing this is ________________________.
  3. VISUAL: Next, what are a few of your personal passions? You may have touched on these yesterday, but really spell it out for me now. What do you love and get excited about? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.
  4. VISUAL: Show me several screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of athleisure you buy. Where do you discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below:
    COMMENT: This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.
  5. VISUAL: Take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? COMMENT: FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how?
  6. VISUAL: Screenshot something that represents the Lululemon brand. Could be a storefront or the logo. COMMENT: What are three juicy adjectives that come to mind when you see this brand or hear it mentioned? Why?
  1. VISUAL: Choose a screenshot that represents the personality of lululemon. COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? How is Lululemon distinct from other athleisure brands in its personality? For ex, if Nike, Lululemon, Under Armor, Reebok and any other athleisure brands in your consideration set were all at a party, how would they all interact? (What would they drive to the party, show up wearing, choose to drink, want to dance to, hang out with... what energy would they bring? etc). Please have fun with this question – no one-sentence answers! J
  2. VISUAL: Take a screenshot of something that represents what keeps you from shopping the brand more often. COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? What would the brand need to do for you to become more enthused about buying it more frequently?
PERSONAL VIDEO
Your final task before completion will be to ask a friend or family member to record you talking about a specific subject that your moderator will choose, based on your two-day dialogue. It will probably be one of your areas of interest/passions. Stay tuned! This does not need to feel produced or rehearsed – we just want you to speak honestly from the heart, “off the cuff”, so to speak. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® Study: Campus Life and Food!

Part I: Complete by Tuesday 3 pm, January 22nd

Part II: Complete on Wednesday, January 23rd

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK® Campus Life and Food Study! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm

your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment

and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK® screen.

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus – showing us the options you have

available to you and the choices you make!

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and

answer them! Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see

where you are on campus (or off!) and what you are eating! With EACH of those posts,

please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS! You’re getting paid for your thoughtful opinions! J

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your

experiences. That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera

roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE

CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Tuesday, January 22nd.

Please complete Part II on Wednesday, January 23rd. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING,

at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee. We want to see what you eat and drink ALL DAY

LONG, and we want to see the facilities that are available to you.

Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday, January 23rd.

PART I

YOU

1. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the

relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b. What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience? Health? Quality of the

food? Ability to personalize it?

2. Describe (through a few pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like. Please

comment on the following: How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs.

hanging out with friends?

YOUR SCHOOL

3. Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at your school. What three

adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture at your school? What adjectives would

you use to describe the student body? What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4. Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus. This can include

anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe

what you are sharing and what you get out of it. How can it be improved? We want details here,

down to the condiments you prefer for your tea or coffee.

5. Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience

at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6. Take pictures of any branded franchises that exist on your campus today (i.e., coffee shops, fast

food etc) and tell me if you ever frequent them, and why or why not. Are there others you’d be

delighted to see? If so, upload screenshots of them and tell me what you would like about

adding them!

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

7. Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you

most often visit. For each, please answer: when do you tend to go here? How often? Why do

you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often

would you say you go off campus to eat or drink?

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL

We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your

campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go

about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture

of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the

context. Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

8. What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or

with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).

9. What are you eating?

10. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?

11. What details are important – how is the QUALITY? HEALTHINESS? CONVENIENCE FACTOR?

PERSONALIZATION FACTOR? What was great – or what could be better?

PIE IN THE SKY

12. What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when

it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks,

restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these

ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would

improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on

your wish list?

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the

food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally

expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only.

Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and

your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up

questions. Thanks so much for participating!

LOOKLOOK® STUDY: FOOD AT WORK
Instructions for Participants
Welcome to the LookLook® Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing.
The purpose of this study is for us to show us how eating, drinking and other types of experiences affect how people feel at work. What makes you feel comfortable (or uncomfortable), more productive, more motivated, more creative…? You can even think beyond food to other amenities like fitness centers, amazing décor, collaborative workspaces, etc.
We’re looking to find out what really matters to people – perhaps un-earthing some ideas that no one has thought of before!
Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions and accompany each with a picture that you either take – or save as a screen grab – and post. It’s all about the details, so NO ONE WORD COMMENTS please!
Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to answer them. Your moderator will respond with follow-up to many of your posts and answering those will likely take an additional half hour.
Please note we want total candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will do with the study. If you work in a public space such as a hospital, please avoid showing people in the photos that you take – just focus on the food and amenities! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and is being used for research purposes only.
Finally, please label your answers with the letters and numbers as they are outlined in the instructions (#1a, #3b, etc)
THE QUESTIONS
1. HOW YOU START YOUR DAY
a. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
b. Screenshot and post an emoji or other image that represents the vibe of where you work. What three words describe how you feel at work on a typical day?
2. Next, we want to see your food and drink options! Do you have a café or cafeteria? Is there a convenience store? Please take a trip to the spots that are available to you for meals and take pictures to show what is offered. If it is a café or cafeteria, please visit each station. Don’t forget drinks and coffee/tea! For each option please answer the following:
a. How could the quality be improved? (Freshness, taste, variety, etc?)
b. Is it healthy enough for your tastes? If not, how would you improve it?
c. How convenient is it? Could technology play a role in some way that would make its delivery more convenient?
d. Are you able to personalize it to the extent that you wish? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative?
3. Now, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work.
Where are there snacks available (ie vending, coffee shops, convenience stores, etc)?
Please take a picture of each option and answer:
a. What is this? How would you describe the quality?
b. How convenient is it?
c. How healthy is it? Anything you would change on that front?
d. Can you personalize it?
4. This section is about where you eat AWAY from work.
a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please take screenshots of the places near work where you go most often when not eating at the office, and answer the following:
i. What is the name of this place?
ii. What do you like about this place?
iii. How often do you come here?
iv. What adjectives describe the atmosphere of this place? Do you wish there was something like this offered at your work?
5. Finally, think about your comfort level at work. What could be added to your work environment that would really lower your stress level and make it more fun, enjoyable and pleasant to be there? What would really blow your mind and surprise and delight you? Grab a few screenshots of ideas that represent your ideas. With each one, tell me what it is and how you would like to see it brought to life.
Please note: If one of your posts does not show a checkmark, there is likely a follow-up to answer. You will be compensated when you have answered all questions! Have fun, and thanks for participating!

study_instructions:
Welcome to the LOOK-LOOK™ Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOK-LOOK™ screen. The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how people feel at work. In other words, we want to find out what types of physical things can boost your motivation, inspire your creativity, and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable. Food, coffee, dry cleaning, a place to collect packages, etc. We’re looking to find out what really matters to people, and perhaps some ideas that haven’t been done before! Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below – and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me. Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them. I’ll be responding to most of your comments, and answering these follow-up questions should about an additional hour (probably less) and you can complete them in the evening when you are home from work if that is easier. PLEASE NOTE: We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – ie for 1s, 1b, etc. Generally speaking, the more pictures the better!
In this study, it’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE
QUESTIONS BELOW, PLEASEJ
THE QUESTIONS:
  1. 1)  DAY IN THE LIFE
    1. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute...? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
    2. Next, show me a picture that describes your workspace. In the comment space, tell me three adjectives that describe the rhythm of a typical workday.
    3. If you think about your current workplace, what are some of your favorite amenities – or things that are offered to employees there?
    4. Is there anything special about your workplace compared to other workplaces in your city? Give us as much detail as possible!
    5. What three words would you use to describe the unique culture at your company?
  2. 2)  Next, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work. How many places to eat exist? (ie full-sized cafeterias, snacks and vending, cafes, convenience stores? Please take a picture of any place food or drinks are offered. For each one, what do you like about it, and tell me what – if anything – you would change about it!
  3. 3)  Next, we want to see your cafe/cafeteria(s)! Take a trip down there and capture pictures of what is offered – especially the parts that are your favorite and your least favorite. For each of the questions below, take a picture that brings to life the question you are answering:
    1. What could be improved? What do you wish was offered that currently is not available?
    2. How could they improve the atmosphere of the cafe/cafeteria?
    3. Does your workplace offer healthy options? If so, what do they look like? Could they be improved in any way?
    4. Is the food service making use of technology to keep things customized and efficient? What else could they do to improve on that front (for example, a mobile app for pre-ordering that earns you loyalty points)?
    5. How innovative is the food and drink offering – overall? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative? We want to hear your suggestions!
  4. 4)  This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work.
a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please visit the place near work where you go most often when not eating at work, and take a picture to accompany your answer to each of the following:
  1. What is the name of this place?
  2. What do you like about this place? What do they offer that you enjoy?
  3. How often do you visit? Do you come alone or with colleagues?
  4. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details.
b. Now, think about where you live – please take some screen grabs of places you like to go out to eat near your home. With the picture for each one, please answer the following questions:
  1. What do you like about this place?
  2. How often do you visit?
  3. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details.
5) The final part is about some pie-in-the-sky dreaming. What could your work offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, snacks, restaurants, bars, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could an employer possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS I’ll ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of my follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating! Have fun!

La sophistication de vos réponses ainsi que votre attention du détail continuent de nous impressionner, et un grand merci à celles qui ont pu réaliser les enregistrements ! name: King of Prussia (Control)
Under 35
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun lifestyle study! We are looking to understand women’s interests and how you indulge your areas and spend time with them!
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different topic.
For each question, please upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. Please respond to the questions in Topics 1 through 6 by the end of the day on Sunday, October 18th.
On Monday, October 19th, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest, and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: 5 Spanish Non-Light Drinker
study_instructions:
¡Nos da mucho gusto que esté participando en nuestro proyecto de investigación! Tal como se lo habíamos comentado, antes de su discusión de grupo en línea queremos conocerlo un poco, y la forma cómo nos gustaría  hacer esto es por medio de unos videos que usted grabará.  

A continuación, se encuentran algunas cosas para tener en mente al grabar sus videos:
• A veces ayuda que un amigo o familiar sostenga la cámara para que pueda concentrarse en lo que está hablando en lugar de preocuparse por sostener la cámara.
• Asegúrese de que usted o quien sea que esté filmando mantenga la cámara lo más quieta posible (sin movimientos temblorosos o agitados).
• Evite cualquier ruido de fondo o música - esto a menudo se escucha mucho más alto en la grabación.
• Haga una pausa durante dos segundos al principio y al final del vídeo para asegurarnos de que la respuesta no esté cortada.
• Antes de enviar su(s) video(s), reprodúzcalo para asegurarse de que todo se ve/suena bien: 
• ¿Está usted mirando en la dirección correcta? Es fácil accidentalmente terminar con imágenes laterales si gira su smartphone mientras filma, ¡y queremos evitar que eso suceda!
• ¿La iluminación es lo suficientemente brillante para que podamos verlo
• ¿Habló lo suficientemente alto para que podamos escuchar claramente todo lo que está diciendo

name: Juniors
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: U.S. Participants
study_instructions: It’s August, time to relax, reflect and relish the moment. This month we’re going to talk about BEAUTY, what it means, how it inspires you, what, when, where and how you feel beautiful. Please complete by Sunday, August 8th! Follow-ups will be posted the following week. Thank you!

study_instructions: 지난 달의 럭셔리 의류 수선과 관리에 관련해 주신 흥미로운 답변에 대해 다시 한번 감사의 인사를 드립니다. 이번 달에는 저번 달에 이어 럭셔리에 있어 가장 중요한 컨셉인 ‘서비스’에 대해 더 얘기해보고자 합니다. 이번 달에 다루는 ‘서비스’는 고객이 럭셔리 물품을 구매하는데에 있어 받을 수 있는 모든 것들에 대한 서비스 입니다. A/S 서비스 부터 개인화된 웰커밍 서비스, 럭셔리 하우스의 VIP 고객으로서 받는 리터치 서비스까지 경험할 수 있는 모든 서비스에 대해 알아보고자 합니다! 10/8 까지 완료해 주시면 감사하겠습니다.

name: Memorial Hermann
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: FOOD AT WORK
Instructions for Participants
Welcome to the LookLook® Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing.
The purpose of this study is for us to show us how eating, drinking and other types of experiences affect how people feel at work. What makes you feel comfortable (or uncomfortable), more productive, more motivated, more creative…? You can even think beyond food to other amenities like fitness centers, amazing décor, collaborative workspaces, etc.
We’re looking to find out what really matters to people – perhaps un-earthing some ideas that no one has thought of before!
Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions and accompany each with a picture that you either take – or save as a screen grab – and post. It’s all about the details, so NO ONE WORD COMMENTS please!
Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to answer them. Your moderator will respond with follow-up to many of your posts and answering those will likely take an additional half hour.
Please note we want total candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will do with the study. If you work in a public space such as a hospital, please avoid showing people in the photos that you take – just focus on the food and amenities! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and is being used for research purposes only.
Finally, please label your answers with the letters and numbers as they are outlined in the instructions (#1a, #3b, etc)
THE QUESTIONS
1. HOW YOU START YOUR DAY
a. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
b. Screenshot and post an emoji or other image that represents the vibe of where you work. What three words describe how you feel at work on a typical day?
2. Next, we want to see your food and drink options! Do you have a café or cafeteria? Is there a convenience store? Please take a trip to the spots that are available to you for meals and take pictures to show what is offered. If it is a café or cafeteria, please visit each station. Don’t forget drinks and coffee/tea! For each option please answer the following:
a. How could the quality be improved? (Freshness, taste, variety, etc?)
b. Is it healthy enough for your tastes? If not, how would you improve it?
c. How convenient is it? Could technology play a role in some way that would make its delivery more convenient?
d. Are you able to personalize it to the extent that you wish? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative?
3. Now, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work.
Where are there snacks available (ie vending, coffee shops, convenience stores, etc)?
Please take a picture of each option and answer:
a. What is this? How would you describe the quality?
b. How convenient is it?
c. How healthy is it? Anything you would change on that front?
d. Can you personalize it?
4. This section is about where you eat AWAY from work.
a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please take screenshots of the places near work where you go most often when not eating at the office, and answer the following:
i. What is the name of this place?
ii. What do you like about this place?
iii. How often do you come here?
iv. What adjectives describe the atmosphere of this place? Do you wish there was something like this offered at your work?
5. Finally, think about your comfort level at work. What could be added to your work environment that would really lower your stress level and make it more fun, enjoyable and pleasant to be there? What would really blow your mind and surprise and delight you? Grab a few screenshots of ideas that represent your ideas. With each one, tell me what it is and how you would like to see it brought to life.
Please note: If one of your posts does not show a checkmark, there is likely a follow-up to answer. You will be compensated when you have answered all questions! Have fun, and thanks for participating!

study_instructions: 지난 달의 재미있는 주제였던 핸드백에 관련한 정성 어린 피드백을 주신 것에 대해 다시 한번 더 감사드립니다. 여러분의 자세하고 정교한 설명이 굉장히 인상 깊었습니다. 그리고 스크린 레코딩을 해주신 분들께도 다시 한번 감사의 인사 드립니다. 인터넷 쇼핑을 하실 때 여러분이 어떤 생각을 하는지에 대해 훌륭하게 보여주셨습니다.이번 달에는 매우 다른 주제에 대해 여러분의 전문 지식이 필요합니다. 오늘날 명품 브랜드를 유지하는 데는 제품의 무결성부터 매우 중요한 창의성까지 책임져야하는 많은 측면이 있으며, 이번 주제와 질문에서는 명품 하우스가 빠르게 변화하는 세상에서 세계적인 세력으로서 사회적 책임을 가장 잘 전달할 수 있는 방법에 대해 얘기해보려고 합니다.이곳은 정치적인 의견을 보여주는 장소가 아닙니다. 저희는 “여러분께 중요한 것”에 대한 솔직한 의견을 듣고 싶습니다.이번 달은 여러분의 사려 깊은 생각과 구두 답변이 사진과 동영상보다 더 중요합니다.7월 7일 까지 완료해주시면 감사하겠습니다! 추후 질문은7월 8일 부터 게시될 예정입니다.

name: Unassigned
study_instructions: None

name: Occasionals
study_instructions:
Welcome back!!  We're excited to share some new ideas about Nabisco and what the brand stands for. Nabisco has some major product evolutions in the works and brand activations that I think you will enjoy hearing about in this final phase of the study.
We'll be sharing two distinct new ideas with you for your honest feedback. It's REALLY IMPORTANT that you understand this is NOT ADVERTISING. 
What you'll see are two sets of ideas (each has two parts) that describe a NEW DIRECTION for the brand. We want to know which direction you find most intriguing, bold and compelling. Which one really nails it for you and may even get you a little excited about what Nabisco is becoming?
Thanks in advance for your thoughtful attention to this MOST important part of the project!

name: Temple
study_instructions: Congratulations on being selected for this important study on Food and the Modern Workplace! The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other aspects of your work environment can boost your motivation and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable. Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different part of your work experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! If you work in a public space such as a hospital, please avoid showing people in the photos that you take – just focus on the food and amenities! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and is being used for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Kids at Home
study_instructions: This chat is about how you manage one part of your busy life which is keeping stocked on personal care products. As a woman who buys luxury brands for herself, how do you mix high low in this category? And how do you manage stocking up your own products as well as those for others in your household?

name: Men
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™ Study: Migraine Solutions

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ Study on Migraine Solutions!

You've been selected for this particular study because you’ve suffered from migraines and are somewhat familiar with migraine related medications.

We are exploring how to simply describe a new prescription medicine for the treatment of migraine when you feel one coming on. Rest assured that when this new medicine comes out there will be complete information available on it. It is a tablet that dissolves under your tongue with no water needed. It has been tested on thousands of people, and we do know that it has very few, mild side effects. It will be covered by insurance, Medicare, and Medicaid. It is safe for people with high blood pressure. It starts working in 30 minutes and gives nearly full relief in two hours or less for pain and nausea. Right now, we are trying to come up with a “headline thought” – a simple summary to describe how it works. One that would pique your curiosity enough to want to learn more.

You can work through the study at your leisure, we estimate it may take between an hour to an hour and a half of your time – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along. A blue check mark in the thumbnail for each post indicates that the post has been resolved to the moderator’s satisfaction. If there is not a check mark on a post it means that the moderator may want to ask you further questions on your comment. Below are the tasks that we need you to complete. We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun! We look forward to your feedback.

 

THE TASKS

  1. FEELINGS ASSOCIATED WITH MIGRAINES
    1. Upload a photo (this can be a personal photo or a screen grab) that best represents how you feel when you experience a migraine. Please describe why you chose this photo in the comments.
  2. RESPONSE TO DESCRIPTIVE CONTENT
    1. Your moderator will push through some descriptive statements about how the new treatment works. In response to each statement please answer the following question: MY FIRST REACTION TO THIS STATEMENT IS_________. Please respond to all follow-up questions asked by your moderator on these posts.

Thank you for your participation!  You are complete when you have answered all of our follow-up questions.

study_instructions: Herzlichen Glückwunsch zur Teilnahme an dieser unterhaltsamen Studie zu schönen Erlebnissen im Leben. Wir freuen uns darauf, in den nächsten Tagen von Dir lernen zu dürfen, was persönliche Erlebnisse für Dich bedeuten. Wir haben die Studie in verschiedene Themen unterteilt. Diese kannst Du in aller Ruhe innerhalb von drei Tagen bearbeiten, um sorgfältig über jede Frage nachzudenken und gut überlegte Antworten zu geben. In dieser Studie spielen Bilder, Bildschirmfotos und Videos für uns eine wichtige Rolle, da sie es uns ermöglichen, Deine Erlebnisse besser zu verstehen. Bitte versuche daher, die Antworten mit viel visuellem Material zu begleiten. Die Zeitfenster sehen wie folgt aus: Du wirst am Freitag, den 1. Oktober, eine Einladung zur Beantwortung der Fragen erhalten. Diese Fragen sollten bis Sonntag, den 3. Oktober, beantwortet sein. Am Montag, den 4. Oktober, wird ein Moderator einige Follow Up Fragen bezüglich deiner Antworten stellen, die du dann bis Dienstag, den 5. Oktober beantworten solltest.  Wir werden mit dir per WhatsApp oder SMS in Kontakt treten und beantworten gerne Deine Fragen während der Studie.

name: Ambivalent 45-54
study_instructions:
LookLook® STUDY:   Fashion | Shopping | Life!

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this LookLook® study on how you shop for fashion today and the role it plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior.  We want to get into the details!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping?

 

Below are the instructions for the study.  Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses.  This is not a survey, it’s a conversation!  Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK:

Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s!  These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe.  It should take about half an hour.

 

GO-TO “LOOKS”

VISUAL:  POST THREE OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS.  We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality.  If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them?  (For ex., one person might have these four: “date night”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out-and-about.” But someone else might have: “client meeting”, “girls’ night”,  “Netflix and Chill”). This is all about your particular life style! Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light.  Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding!  But apparel is the focus of this exercise.

 

COMMENT:  IN EACH POST, tell me the following:  (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who is the designer of each piece and where did you buy? (iii) Where do you typically shop for this type of look? Why?

 

STUDY DAY!  

So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions!  Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment.  Look out for my follow-ups!

 

DISCOVERY AND INSPIRATION

VISUAL:  Post at least three screenshots of places you go online that INSPIRE the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, email from a brand, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.).  Where do you tend to discover new products/styles?  With each one, please complete the comment below:

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “This is ___________.  I go here (insert frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc).  I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”

 

WHY YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Find any image or picture (even an emoji) that represents the feeling that shopping (for apparel and accessories) brings alive in you.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “I chose this image because it represents my feeling of _______________ when I shop for clothes/accessories.” Why do you shop – is it always for replenishment of something you need – or do you shop for fun? At its best, what does a great shopping experience give you?  What really motivates you to make purchases? (ads, promotions, events, Instagram, etc)

 

WHERE YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Think about the top 3 places where you spend the majority of your apparel dollars.  Post a screenshot of each destination (please list at least 2!)

 

COMMENT (FOR EACH):  Please complete in your own words:  “I tend to buy a lot of my fashion here:  _______________________ because  __________________”.  What percentage of your apparel money goes to this place, and why?

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN THE DIGITAL WORLD!

VIDEO:  Next, you’re going shopping on your phone. Just go browsing for fun. You could look for a specific item or you could just go on a favorite site or to a favorite shopping app to look around and see what you like.

 

We want you to record your screen with audio while you do this (instructions below if you are not familiar with how to do this.)

 

Spend about 1-2 minutes browsing for the item. While you’re browsing, just say out loud what you are thinking.  Tell us where you start your search and voice out loud your comments as you browse. As you click through different options, tell me why you are making your choices of where to go and what to look at. After you record for a few minutes, upload your video to LookLook®. Note: you do not have to be a Ninja at this! Just look around and talk to me while you’re browsing on your phone. If you get frustrated for any reason, mention that!

 

How to screen record on an iPhone (please be sure to turn on audio!)

  1. Go to Settings > Control Center > Customize Controls, then tap next to Screen Recording.
  2. Swipe up from the bottom edge of any screen.
  3. Press the record button firmly until the screen recording box comes up (it takes 3 seconds), turn the microphone on, and then tap Start Recording.
  4. Upload your video to LookLook®

 

How to screen record on an Android phone

5.     Download and use the free app Mobizen

6.     Enable sound before recording

7.     Upload your video to LookLook®

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN-STORE)

VISUAL:  As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place.  Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. 

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words:  “Services that I enjoy at my favorite apparel/accessories stores include _______________________”.  These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to styling, events, exclusive product lines, delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a local sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.    

 

HOW IT ALL COMES TOGETHER

VISUAL:  Imagine for a moment that someone handed you the luxury of an entire afternoon to go clothing shopping – just for you.  How would you enjoy this gift of time? Would you curl up on the couch and go shopping online? Would you visit boutiques? A mall? Post a screenshot (or a few) of where you would go shopping.

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Where is this? What do enjoy most about this experience? Provide as much detail as possible!   

 

INTERMIX

 

WHO IS THE INTERMIX WOMAN?

VISUAL:  Please screenshot a picture that represents, in your mind, the woman who shops a lot of Intermix. (If you are not familiar at all with the brand, feel free to check out the website.) This can be anyone!  A celebrity, whatever pops into your head (don’t over think it!)

 

COMMENT:  Please complete: “I chose this image because_____________.” 

 

URGENCY

VISUAL:  Take a screenshot or picture of any type of retailer that you feel more excitement and urgency around shopping vs. Intermix.

 

COMMENT:  What did you choose, and why?  What do you think would give you more of a sense of excitement about getting to know the Intermix experience a bit better?  (Be completely honest!)

name: Non Freshman
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™: Campus Life Food Study
 
Part I: Complete on Tuesday, October 2nd 
Part II: Complete on Wednesday, October 3rd
Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ University of Nevada, Reno University Campus Life Food Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.
This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus.
DAY ONE – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where and what you are eating and drinking! With EACH of those posts, please answer questions 1a-d in full.
DAY TWO – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them!  Please reference the question number (3a, 3b, 4, etc.) in your responses.
PLEASE NO ONE WORD ANSWERS.
We realize you are busy – and perhaps can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook™ is that you can snap pictures (or video, if you are motivated), save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  DO THIS WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!
HERE ARE THE TASKS:
Please complete Part I on Tuesday, October 2nd. PART I SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or coffee time.
Please complete Part II on Wednesday, October 3rd. 
Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday, October 3rd.
 
PART I – DAY ONE
FOOD JOURNAL
1. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.  PLEASE START THIS WHEN YOU WAKE UP IN THE MORNING!
a. What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue?
b. What are you eating?
c. Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now?
d. What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts?  What was great – or what could be better?
 
PART II – DAY TWO
YOU
2. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:
a. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?
b. What is important to you when it comes to food? Is it taste?  Convenience?  Healthiness?  The ability to personalize your food?
3. Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots here but no stock photos please!  
 
YOUR SCHOOL
4. Upload a photo that represents the student body. What adjectives would you use to describe the student body at U of NE, Reno? Why?
5. Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at the university. What adjectives would you use to describe the unique culture at U of NE, Reno? Why?
 
FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL
6. Please take pictures of the dining facilities use most often (on or off campus).  This can include anything from a café to a vending machine to a convenience store! With each, please describe what we are seeing, and tell us what you get out of it.  Are there any ways it could be improved?
7.    Upload a photo that represents how you feel about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen that photo and what does that photo represent? 
8. Are there any branded franchises on the campus today (ie Starbucks, etc) – or if not, are there ones you’d be delighted to see? Take a picture or screenshot of any you’d like to see added to the mix.
9. What (if anything) do you miss from home – food-wise?  Take a picture to represent it!  Do you think there’s any way to replicate this on-campus in any way?
 
10. DREAMING     
What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Also think beyond food and drink. What else could your college possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?
PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this! 
Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

name: U.S. HVG - Female
New York Participants
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY:  Smartphones in Your Daily LIfe

Study Instructions

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study!  Together we’ll be discussing how smartphones help us in daily life, and where perhaps they could do a better job of it, as machine learning can potentially improve your experience.

  

DAY ONE:  “How You, Your Smartphone and Your Apps Get Stuff Done” will take about an hour and a half over the course of the day for you to give us a show and tell of your daily rhythm.  Your moderator will ask you some follow up questions throughout the day.

 

DAY TWO:  “Machine Learning & Your Smartphone” will take about an hour.  We will have more of an active dialogue, getting your top of mind thoughts about what artificial intelligence even means, and brainstorming a little on how your smartphone could become more intuitive to your needs to be more useful.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you to complete. For each question, please upload a relevant photo along with your response. We're just looking for your honest opinions so just give us the straight talk – it’s not a survey, it’s a conversation!  When your moderator has responded to a conversation thread, you’ll see a blue dot on the thumbnail of that post so you’ll know which ones to respond to!

 

THE TASKS

 

PREAMBLE: (To be completed prior to the study):

 

  1. Please upload a quick selfie so we can put a face to the name!

  2. Upload a screenshot of your current smartphone, and tell me what make and model it is.  In the comment section, tell me why you’re in the market for a new phone!  Is it just the lust for a particular new gadget or is something wrong with your current phone,  etc.?

  3. Take a screenshot of your homescreen, and tell us what apps are some of your most frequently used and why!

 

DAY ONE:  “How You, Your Smartphone and Your Apps Get Stuff Done”

 

Welcome to Day One! Today, we want to see how you use your smartphone to be productive, helping you throughout the day.  There are so many tools out there these days (digital and analog) and everyone has their own things they rely on to try to stay organized, informed and connected…   we want to see what this looks like for you.  

 

Today, you will be journaling all the ways you work with data in your daily life that helps everything run smoothly (or, at least, run…)

 

Send us pictures and screen grabs of everything you’re doing today, whether it’s managing a to-do list, texting or connecting with friends with friends, checking your FitBit, Skyping, setting up a calendar invite, searching on Google or on a social media platform, ordering an Uber, getting directions, shopping on Alexa or Google Home... we want to see it all!

 

With every screenshot you post, please tell us:

 

  1. What you’re doing

  2. What app you’re using (individually, or any pairs of apps you’re using together)

  3. Any frustrations with the task at hand (or anything that’s working unexpectedly well!)

 

If you use any resources other than your smartphone to help you get information or get things done today, we want to hear about that too.  Maybe you use an app like Slack or Trello on your laptop to coordinate projects?  Or Dropbox to organize your files?  Maybe you carry an analog organizer?  These are the kinds of things we’re interested in.

 

DAY TWO:  “A.I., Machine Learning & Your Smartphone”

 

So today we’re going to delve into the hot topic of machine learning and artificial intelligence.  

 

VISUAL ONE:

Please find a screenshot of an image or picture that represents whatever comes to mind when you think of the concept of artificial intelligence and machine learning.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

  • What visual did you select?  Why did you choose this to represent artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • What three adjectives pop into your head when you hear the terms artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • What parts of your life are you aware of that have been made better or worse by artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • Is there a difference between artificial intelligence and machine learning in your mind? If so, how would you explain the difference?

  • Are there any smartphone manufacturers talking about artificial intelligence or machine learning? If so, who are they and what have you heard? 

  • If your smartphone could get to know your needs and help you do things in the most useful and intuitive way, what would you hope it could do?

  • When it comes to your phone understanding you better and adapting to your specific needs, what excites you? What would you expect it could help with? ...and what potentially scares you (if anything)?

 

VISUAL TWO:

THE ALL-IMPORTANT BATTERY:  

Please select a screengrab of something that represents how you feel when you know your battery is starting to run low, and might not stay powered for the entire time you need it.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

  • What visual did you select?  Why did you choose this?

  • What terms do you use to describe your phone’s battery?  

  • How do you think about your battery life and your battery usage?

  • What sort of expectations do you have for how long your battery lasts?

  • Have you ever used something like a battery pack, a replaceable battery, or carried your charger with you because you knew you wouldn’t get through the day? If so, how often did you do this? What made you think you wouldn’t make it through the day?

  • What sort of things come to mind when you think about battery usage?  For example, individual app usage, screen brightness, etc?  What do you feel drains your battery, and why?

  • Do you make any trade-offs or sacrifices in how you use your phone in order to save battery?

  • Is battery performance a consideration when it comes to shopping for your new smartphone?  Why or why not?  

 

VISUAL THREE:

Upload an image that represents how you might research the battery performance of a future potential smartphone.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

name: Gamers
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on gaming and the virtualization of fashion in the 21st century! It's a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of this concept these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. There is frequent mention of luxury in this study. You don't need to be interested in luxury fashion to answer the questions. As a gamer, we are interested in your perspective on this concept and what is appealing or not appealing about it. As always, looking for your honest thoughts! Wherever you see the mention of "luxury", just think about your favorite apparel brands, no matter what they are. Please complete your responses by end of day Saturday August 21st. Starting on an assigned day around August 23-26, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. Please be open, honest, and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: 1 Bilingual Non-Light Drinker
study_instructions:
We are very excited to have you participate in our research project! As was previously mentioned to you, prior to the online group discussion we would like to get to know you a little bit, and the way we would like to do this is by having you create some brief videos. 

A few things to keep in mind when recording your videos:
• Sometimes it helps to have a friend or family member hold the camera so you can focus on what you are talking about rather than worrying about holding the camera.
• Make sure you or whoever is filming holds the camera as still as possible (no shaking or jarring movements).
• Avoid any background noise or music - this often becomes much louder in the recording.
• Pause for two seconds at the beginning and end of your video to make sure your response isn't cut off at all.
• Before submitting your video(s), watch it to make sure everything looks/sounds okay:  
• Are you facing the right direction? It's easy to accidentally end up with sideways footage if you turn your smartphone while filming, and we want to avoid that happening!
• Is the lighting bright enough so we can see you and what you are recoding?
• Did you speak loud enough so we can clearly hear all that you are saying?

study_instructions: Welcome to the first-ever global luxury panel! You have been selected to apply for this opportunity via personal reference. Here on LookLook® please share some of your favorite luxury brand purchases. With each image upload, please identify the brand. Thank you - and we look forward to chatting soon about luxury!

name: Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study!

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! 

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! 

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.' 

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. 

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink. 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! We want to see REAL LIFE - the good, the bad and the ugly. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® Study: Campus Life and Food! Part I: Complete by Wednesday 9 pm, February 13th Part II: Complete on Thursday, February 14th Welcome to the LOOKLOOK® Campus Life and Food Study! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK® screen.
In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus – showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them! Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses. PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where you are on campus (or off!) and what you are eating! With EACH of those posts, please answer related questions in full. PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS! You’re getting paid for your thoughtful opinions!J
We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! HERE ARE THE TASKS: Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday February 14th.
Please complete Part I by 9:00 pm on Wednesday February 13th! Please complete Part II on Wednesday February 14th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee. We want to see what you eat and drink ALL DAY LONG, and we want to see the facilities that are available to you.
PART I YOU
  1. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:
    1. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?
    2. What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience? Health? Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?
  2. Describe (through a few pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like. Please comment on the following: How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends?
YOUR SCHOOL 3. Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at your school. What three adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture at your school? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body? What makes this place unique? FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL
  1. Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus. This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it. How can it be improved? We want details here, down to the condiments you prefer for your tea or coffee.
  2. Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?
  3. Take pictures of any branded franchises that exist on your campus today (i.e., coffee shops, fast food etc) and tell me if you ever frequent them, and why or why not. Are there others you’d be delighted to see? If so, upload screenshots of them and tell me what you would like about adding them!
FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL 7. Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit. For each, please answer: when do you tend to go here? How often? Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? FOOD JOURNAL (A) (DINNER, LATE NIGHT SNACKS) In an effort to make tomorrow’s food journal a little easier to navigate we ask that you make your dinner post tonight. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Tonight, when you eat dinner, please snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context. Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.
  1. What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).
  2. What are you eating?
  3. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?
  4. What details are important – how is the QUALITY? HEALTHINESS? CONVENIENCE FACTOR?
PERSONALIZATION FACTOR? What was great – or what could be better? PART II FOOD JOURNAL (B) (BREAKFAST, LUNCH, SNACKS – THROUGH LATE AFTERNOON) Today’s food journal will follow the same format as food journal (A) and should include your first meal or beverage of the day, coffee (if you drink it), any snacks or refreshments you have throughout the morning, your lunch, and any afternoon snacks. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context. Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.
  1. What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).
  2. What are you eating?
  3. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?
  4. What details are important – how is the QUALITY? HEALTHINESS? CONVENIENCE FACTOR? PERSONALIZATION FACTOR? What was great – or what could be better?
Once you’ve made your last afternoon snacks post you can continue on to PIE IN THE SKY. PIE IN THE SKY 16. What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only.  Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!
