study_instructions: Nous avons une fois encore beaucoup apprécié vos feedbacks sur le sujet passionnant des sacs à main ! La sophistication de vos réponses ainsi que votre attention du détail continuent de nous impressionner, et un grand merci à celles qui ont pu réaliser les enregistrements ! Ils nous ont permis de bien cerner votre vision et ressenti lors de votre navigation au travers des pages internet.Ce mois-ci, nous avons besoin de votre expertise sur un sujet très différent. Bien des aspects sont importants aujourd’hui pour le maintien d’une marque de luxe, allant de la créativité à l’intégrité des produits ; et dans ce jeu de questions nous souhaiterions recueillir votre opinion sincère sur la meilleure manière, pour une marque de luxe, de communiquer sur sa responsabilité sociale et son impact au sein d’un monde en transition. Pas besoin de recourir au « politiquement correct » dans cette étude, nous souhaitons (comme toujours) votre véritable opinion sur ce qui VOUS IMPORTE le plus. L’étude sera un peu différente.Ce mois-ci, les photos et vidéos sont moins importantes que votre réflexion approfondie et vos réponses verbales.Merci de compléter le questionnaire pour le mercredi 7 Juillet ! Les questions follow-ups de suivi commenceront à partir du Jeudi 8 Juillet.

name: Readers
study_instructions:
You have been selected for this project because we know you through a past luxury or fashion study or because you have been referred by a past participant. You have style, you are literate in luxury, well-versed in fashion and beauty, and you know your way around both online and boutique/department store shopping. Because you are successful, yet young and on your way up, some marketers would call you a HENRY – a “High Earner Not Rich Yet”. The objective of this study is to understand a little more about the lives of individual HENRY women across the country. We are curious to know how you like to live, how you curate your purchases, how you prioritize your spending, and how you weave in luxury brands with less expensive purchases. Please note that you don’t have to make everything look camera-ready in this study. We do want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. So don’t worry about everything needing to look perfect! One of the topics we will want to explore with you is how you feel about spending money and saving money. We will not be talking with you about your salary. But we will talk about where you prioritize your spending, and the challenges of living the life you want and fulfilling your dreams given the challenges of modern life. Some of the women in the study are married, some are divorced, some have little kids, some have no children, others have grown children. Everyone is busy with many interests. We want to hear about how you strive for balance and make room for the things you are passionate about. And of course – we want to go shopping with you. Shopping is a big part of this study, and we’re going to be super curious about your preferences and your choices. There are no right or wrong answers! We just want your candid honesty. Below are the three days’ assignments. We recommend planning to complete one on each of the three days of the study – but if you want to get it all done on the weekend, feel free! DAY ONE: SHOW US AROUND!
Let’s start with you telling us a little about where you live. Take some pictures of your home or apartment and tell us both what you love about it and what you envision changing about it, if anything. Next we want you to show us some possessions you have acquired that really spark joy in your life – across a few categories. Specifically, we’d like to see a few items in each of the areas below. With each picture, tell me where you bought it, the name of the brand and what you love about it. 1. FASHION 2. BEAUTY
3. JEWELRY (Can include watches)
4. HOME GOODS (ie furniture, art, kitchen appliance) Next, choose an image to accompany your answer to each of the following questions (it’s fine to just Google search an image on your phone):
  1. (Post an image that represents your answer in some way): “My personal definition of luxury is _______________________________”. Note: There is no right or wrong way to answer this – for some people it may about the history of a brand or item, or craftsmanship, its rarity or just the way it makes you feel.
  2. (Post an image that represents your answer in some way): “My personal definition of success is_______________________________”
  3. (Post an image that represents your answer in some way): “I will really feel like I’ve made it when __________________________.”
  4. Next, put together a go-to outfit for work that makes you feel authentic and powerful. We would love to see you model this outfit but you could also hang it on hangers or lay it out on your bed. Please include jewelry, shoes and handbag. (Can you tell, details matter in this study?) Take a picture and answer these questions:
    1. I feel great in this for work because ________________________.
    2. The reason this type of outfit is a good fit for my work environment is ___________________________________.
    3. The most important piece in this whole ensemble is ____________ because it makes me feel __________________________.
    4. If I don’t feel confident in the outfit I’m wearing at work I _________________.
  5. Now, compose an outfit to show us or you can share a picture of you where you are wearing something you love going out in – ie with your friends, on a date, etc. Again, include detail – jewelry, shoes, whatever completes the look. Take a picture and answer these questions: a. I describe this style as ______________________________________.
    b. The most important piece in this ensemble is _______________________     because it makes me feel ____________________________________.
  6. Take a picture of your jewelry collection – ie where you keep your earrings, rings, necklaces. Answer these questions with that picture:
    1. Give me some words to describe your jewelry style. What are some of your favorite brands of jewelry?
    2. What role does costume jewelry play vs. fine jewelry? When do you wear either / both?
c. When purchasing fine jewelry, is it something you buy personally or more likely to be gifted? d. Do you own a fine watch? (If so, show us!) Do you wear a watch every day? If so, is it more for style or function (in the day of iPhones, maybe it’s just a style statement?). What’s your dream watch?
  1. Next, gather your three favorite skin care products. Why are these your favorites, and where did you buy them?
  2. Finally, gather your three favorite makeup products. What does each of these do for you? Where did you buy them?
  3. Final question of the day – what are some other “things” in your life that represent YOUR personal definition of luxury? (ie could be a car, a piece of jewelry passed down from your mother, an eye cream, your passport or a picture of a vacation, your closet or even your home - anything!) Show us one or two and tell us why.
DAY TWO: Shopping! Pre-Shopping Questions
We’re going to shopping with you, but a few important questions first!
  1. If you had a whole afternoon to spend shopping for fashion – just for you – where would you choose to go? Think about this, and show us a few screen grabs/images that bring this to life. Would it be a department store? A neighborhood of boutiques? A shopping mall? Maybe you’d rather curl up on your sofa and shop online? If so, take screen grabs on your phone of the websites or apps you love to experience. As you share your online shopping habits, please answer these questions:
    1. What percent of your fashion shopping is done online vs. in store? Why? Does it vary by price tag/type of item?
    2. Do you tend to get more excited about finding an “It” item that is super popular, or finding things that no one else has? How do your choices reflect your individual style?
  2. Now show me some screen grabs of where you most enjoy shopping for beauty products – ie makeup and skin care, and answer these questions: a. What do you most enjoy about shopping for makeup and skin care and why? b. How do you discover new products and trends? If you read magazines or blogs or vlogs specific to beauty, please show us these with screen grabs. c. What percentage of your beauty purchases take place online?
  3. What about jewelry – where do you go for that? (Show a screen grab) Does it differ for fine jewelry vs. costume jewelry?
  4. Handbags?
  1. Technology?
  2. Home goods?
  3. We’re all a work in progress. What do you feel you still need to learn about shopping and about how to build the wardrobe – and the lifestyle - to which you ultimately aspire? Capture a screen grab that brings this to life somehow. Then answer these questions:
    1. Do you consider yourself a savvy shopper? If so, how exactly are you savvy? What are some of the tricks and tips you’ve learned?
    2. If you were to cultivate even better shopping skills than you already have, what would that look like? Would it involve a personal shopper? Relationships with great sales associates? If the world of shopping were at your command, what would it provide you with?
  4. Everyone talks about the “experience” being so important in retail these days. Take a picture of a brand that is doing a great job at this, in your opinion (could be fashion, beauty, auto, wellness, travel, etc – anything you feel strongly about! Bricks and mortar, please – not online.) Answer these questions: a. How have they created a great experience? What does this even mean to you? b. Take a screen grab of a brand that you used to love but has fallen off your radar. What did they stop doing – why did they lose relevance for you? What could they do (from an experiential perspective) to make you love them again?
  5. What brands are in your future that aren’t there now? Are there any you aspire to – or feel out of reach – that you’d like to get to know better? Send me screen grabs of the logos and please speak to that.
Time to Go Shopping! Take us to your favorite neighborhood of boutiques, a department store or other type of shopping mecca. We want to you choose a place where you can show us clothing, jewelry, shoes, and beauty.
  1. Take a picture of the outside of a favorite store. With the picture, describe how often you visit here, and what usually motivates you to come? How are you feeling outside of the store?
  2. Next, go inside and visit just enjoy browsing. We want to experience this through you. Take a picture of anything that catches your eye, and describe your thought process. What is your mind telling you about potential purchases? What is your internal conversation? At each destination while you shop, what are you feeling and what could make the experience better? (NOTE: please visit enough shops to show us clothing, jewelry, shoes, and beauty.)
3. When you get home, put up your feet and do a little online shopping and take some screen grabs of places you shop or browse online. Attached to these images, please answer these questions: a. What do you get out of shopping online vs. in-store?
b. Do you ever buy fashion or beauty on Amazon? Why or why not?
c. What are your favorite places to shop online?
d. Where do you end up making final purchases – online or in-store? Do you use one way of shopping more for browsing and one for transacting? Why? And does that vary with what you’re buying? DAY THREE:
The last day is about some self-reflection and also about learning where you go for inspiration and discovery. You’ll also record a video.
  1. Show me a little of your social media. Send me screen grabs of your very favorite influences on Instagram, Facebook and Pinterest. (These can be fashion bloggers, brands, celebs, or entertainment/humor sites). With each, describe it a bit and tell me why you love it.
  2. What role does word of mouth with your friends and co-workers play when it come to discovering new looks, new products, new apps, etc? If you text with your friends about purchases or anything fashion related, take a screen shot of your groups texts and share that.
  3. Do you read magazines? Either print or online? If so, take pictures and show me your favorite parts of those publications. Why do you like them? (NOTE: BAZAAR readers, we want to know what it is you love about the magazine, how it is distinct from other magazines, is it shoppable, what you feel you can count on it for, etc. NON-BAZAAR readers, what do you think of when you see Harper’s BAZAAR magazine? Have either heard of or visited ShopBAZAAR.com? or made a purchase?
  4. Next were going to talk a little bit about money. Find an image or picture that represents how you feel about your financial situation and answer the following questions: a. What are your personal financial goals?
    b. At what level of wealth will you feel that you are where you want to be?
    c. What does it mean to you to be financially responsible?
    d. Do you use any sort of investment tools (like Mint) or a personal investment     advisor?
 
  1. Next let’s talk about your wish list. Show me what you would do with a windfall of $500? $1,000? $10,000? $100,000? How would you spend each of these amounts? Show me a picture that represents each.
  2. Your future – find an image that represents where you see yourself in 5 years, and then in 10 years. Where do you envision yourself at these points in your future?
FINAL TASK: VIDEO COMMENTARY When you get to this point, your moderator is going to ask you to speak on a particular subject that you have touched on in the study – this is going to be personalized to each respondent. Your video response should be about a minute in length. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!
Please remember to answer all the moderator follow-up questions.

study_instructions: The Global Luxury Collective 에 참여하시게 되신 것을 다시 한번 더 축하 드립니다! 여러분들에 대해 알아갈 수 있는 기회에 시간과 노력을 들여주신 것에 다시 한번 더 감사드립니다. 저희는 플랫폼에서 다루게 될 모든 것들에 대한 여러분의 의견을 정말 기대하고 있습니다! 이번 첫번째 달에는, 여러분이 “럭셔리” 라는 단어를 떠올렸을 때, 가장 먼저 드는 생각과 코로나 이후 “럭셔리란 어떤 것인가?” 대한 생각에 변화가 있으셨다면, 어떤 변화가 있었는지에 대해 알아보고자 합니다. 항상 그랬듯이, 틀린 답은 없습니다- 개개인은 다 다르니까요! 그리고 가장 중요한 점은, 저희는 여러분의 눈을 통해 세상을 보는 것을 중요시 하기 때문에 미디어 업로드를 하실 때 여러분들의 답변을 가장 잘 살릴 수 있는 사진이나 스크린 샷을 업로드 해주시면 감사하겠습니다. 이 스터디는 현실 세계의 디테일을 세부적으로 포착하고자 하는 것을 목표로 합니다. 매달 초에 여러분이 답변 하실 새로운 질문들이 공유될 것이고, 그 주4일 ~ 5일 정도의 기간 이내에 여러분들께서 편하실 때에 답변 해주시면 됩니다.  첫번째로 나가는 이번 질문 세트는 5월4일까지 완료해주시길 바랍니다! 감사합니다.

name: Balance Seekers
study_instructions: Congrats on being contacted for this fun study on plant-based food options! No matter where you are on your journey with plant-based eating, we want to understand your perspective. There are no right or wrong answers. We’re simply interested in your honest opinions on the products and choices we’ll be discussing. You have a week to complete the study at your own pace. The one important thing to note is that we need you to complete a food diary for two subsequent days, as part of the study, recording what you eat, where, why, etc. It’s important that eat and make choices as you normally do during those days. We want real life!  And, it’s <u>totally fine</u> if you eat meat during these two days if that is what you would normally do. We’re interested in the dynamics around these daily choices! Topics One, Two and Three cover your lifestyle and attitude towards plant-based foods. Topics Four & Five consist of a food diary – we just really want to see what you eat during the course of a normal day! Topic Six – you take us on a little shopping trip to buy some plant-based frozen food! Topic Seven – we’ll focus on a specific brand of plant-based food and wrap up the discussion. We will be asking for lots of screenshots and one piece of video at the end where you talk to the camera briefly in your own words. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by July 30. Beginning the week of August 2nd, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: Students 11-14
Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! 

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before you move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

Non Freshman
study_instructions: LOOKLOOK™: Campus Life Food Study Part I: Complete prior to Tuesday September 25th Part II: Complete on Wednesday, September 26th   Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ University of Virginia University Campus Life Food Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen. This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus. We don’t need you to write us a novel on every food choice. We just want you to simply take pictures of everything you choose to eat (and where you are eating it). These will be the basis of discussion for us to ask you about the surrounding experience of those food choices. Beyond the food itself, we also want to understand the importance of the overall environment (look, feel, seating, general vibe, etc.), the customer service, and anything else that’s important to you. We realize you are busy – and perhaps can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting you’re experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook™ is that you can snap pictures (or video, if you are motivated), save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  DO THIS WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! HERE ARE THE TASKS: Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Tuesday, September 25th. Please complete Part II on Wednesday, September 26th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or coffee time. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday, September 26th. PART I – DAY ONE YOU 1.   FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following: a.   How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis? b.   What is important to you when it comes to food? Anything from “Chef-prepared” to local ingredients, to sustainable practices, etc.? 2.   Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots here but no stock photos please!   YOUR SCHOOL 3.   What adjectives would you use to describe the student body at U of VA? Why? Upload a photo that represents the student body.   FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL 4.   Which dining facilities do you tend to use most often at school? What are the main points of contact you come into on a daily basis that offer you food or drink?  (This can include on or off campus.)  Please take pictures to show us each and every single one – down to the condiments for your tea or coffee.  This is all about the details! 5. Upload a photo that represents how you feel about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen that photo and what does that photo represent? Are there any new facilities offering anything different or exciting?  If so, please visit and photograph for us, with your opinions about it!  6.    Are there any branded franchises on the campus today (ie Starbucks, etc) – or if not, are there ones you’d be delighted to see? Take a picture or screenshot of any you’d like to see added to the mix. 7.    What (if anything) do you miss from home – food-wise?  Take a picture to represent it!  Do you think there’s any way to replicate this on-campus in any way? PART II – DAY TWO FOOD JOURNAL 8. We want to understand all points of availability of food that you experience during a typical day, and how campus dining fits in. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.  PLEASE START THIS WHEN YOU WAKE UP IN THE MORNING! a.   What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? b.   What are you eating? c.   Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now? d.   What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts?  What was great – or what could be better? 9.  DREAMING      What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Also think beyond food and drink. What else could your college possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?   PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this!   Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

name: Participants
23-39 Women
study_instructions:
PARTICIPANT INSTRUCTIONS

 

Welcome to the Luxury Skin Care Product Study.

 

You've been selected for this particular study because you are well-versed in luxury and you are passionate about luxury skin care products.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you complete.  We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun and we can't wait to see what you show us!

 

We estimate that answering the questions, taking the pictures and recording the video will take a total of two and a half hours to complete (we’ve put time estimates in for each section but don’t feel limited by these!) Two hours for the tasks, and an additional half and hour to respond to follow-up questions throughout.

 

You can work through the study at your leisure – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along.

 

If you can finish by Wednesday November 9th it would be fantastic, but it you need a little more time, just let us know.

 

THE TASKS

 

FIRST, show me the luxury skin care products you are most loyal to, and tell me why. You may have two, you may have ten – everyone prioritizes differently.  We do not need to see your makeup choices – just skin care. Photograph each item that is currently part of your routine and tell us what motivated you to try it.  Is it a favorite or something new that you're trying?  What role does brand and product loyalty play when it comes to your skin care routine?  Do friends, word of mouth, or recommendations from aestheticians or dermatologists play a role at all in what you use?

(time estimate: 10 minutes)

 

SECOND, let’s discuss what influences your choices. Please answer these seven questions:

  1. How do you find out about the latest products, trends and innovations?  Show me through pictures and be as specific as possible.  If it’s blogs or vlogs, take screen shots.  If it’s through magazines (online or print), show me that.  Perhaps it’s through websites or by shopping in stores?  Do you typically have to sample a product before trying it?  Whatever counts for you, show me visually and explain in your comments WHY those things have the most influence for you.
  2. How often (if at all) do you visit a dermatologist or an aesthetician?  What services are you regularly receiving?  How do these influence your choices of product (if at all)?
  3. Where do you prefer to shop for luxury skin care - department stores, online, Sephora, boutiques?  Take screen grab of the type of environment that is most compelling for you.  Do you prefer an open environment/self-service model like Sephora or having interaction with sales associates/experts in a department store?  Why? Can the sales associate’s opinions and knowledge get you to try new things or convert from other brands?  Tell me about it.
  4. Do points or loyalty programs play a role in where you shop and if so, what do you desire in return?  How important are promotions or gift with purchase?  Product samples?  When you really think about it, what really drives your loyalty to a shopping environment, and to specific luxury skin care products?
  5. When you shop for luxury skincare, do you typically narrow down a brand's offering by shopping for a specific type of product (i.e. cream, serum, eye cream) or is it more by benefit – ie anti-aging, brightening, hydration, etc.)?
  6. When it comes to price, is there a threshold on what you will spend for a product to which you are loyal?  Is there a certain category that you are willing to invest more in than others?
  7. How important is product exclusivity – ie items that are exclusively available at one retailer?  Does that add to a sense of discovery or loyalty to that store?  How important is a sense of discovery when it comes to luxury skin care products?

(time estimate: 20 minutes)

 

THIRD, you're going shopping.  Choose an actual store where you really love to browse for luxury skin care products.  We realize that you may shop online for some products but we'd like to start in an actual store.

 

Please wander as you normally would and stop wherever you are interested.  Take pictures of whatever catches your eye, and describe why it got your attention. We are really curious about what draws you in – ie the display, the brand name, beautiful packaging, a friendly salesperson (if there is one), etc.  If you find a product that you're seriously coveting, please photograph and then define – why do you desire it?

(time estimate:  1 hour)

 

FOURTH, we’re going to talk about shopping online. Please take screen grabs of where you shop for luxury skin care products online, if you do.  Please send screen shots of all online stores that are in your repertoire, and describe what you typically buy there and why – even if it’s only occasional.

(time estimate:  15 minutes)

 

FINALLY, please have someone record you speaking to us on the following subject.  The video should be about a minute in length.  Think about it first, then use the video to tell us:  if you had your own luxury skin care store or luxury skin care website, what would be your best in class practices?  Describe what the experience would be like for the customer If you are in a store, what services are you receiving?  If you are online, how are you delivering a sense of luxury?  What is most important in this luxury skin care shopping experience?

(time estimate: 15 minutes)

name: Commuters
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study!  The most important thing to know about this study is that we want you to focus on life BEYOND COVID . In other words, we're looking to create a revamped dining experience for NEXT YEAR. That's why we're going to ask you about your memories of what was available last year so we can build from that . This assumes that while some safety protocols will still be necessary, a much more varied and complete dining experience will again be available!

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 3 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Parents
Men
study_instructions:
PARTICIPANT INSTRUCTIONS

 

Welcome to the Luxury Skin Care Product Study.

 

You've been selected for this particular study because you are well-versed in luxury and you are passionate about luxury skin care products.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you complete.  We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun and we can't wait to see what you show us!

 

We estimate that answering the questions, taking the pictures and recording the video will take a total of two and a half hours to complete (we’ve put time estimates in for each section but don’t feel limited by these!) Two hours for the tasks, and an additional half and hour to respond to follow-up questions throughout.

 

You can work through the study at your leisure – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along.

 

If you can finish by Wednesday November 9th it would be fantastic, but it you need a little more time, just let us know.

 

THE TASKS

 

FIRST, show me the luxury skin care products you are most loyal to, and tell me why. You may have two, you may have ten – everyone prioritizes differently.  We do not need to see your makeup choices – just skin care. Photograph each item that is currently part of your routine and tell us what motivated you to try it.  Is it a favorite or something new that you're trying?  What role does brand and product loyalty play when it comes to your skin care routine?  Do friends, word of mouth, or recommendations from aestheticians or dermatologists play a role at all in what you use?

(time estimate: 10 minutes)

 

SECOND, let’s discuss what influences your choices. Please answer these seven questions:

  1. How do you find out about the latest products, trends and innovations?  Show me through pictures and be as specific as possible.  If it’s blogs or vlogs, take screen shots.  If it’s through magazines (online or print), show me that.  Perhaps it’s through websites or by shopping in stores?  Do you typically have to sample a product before trying it?  Whatever counts for you, show me visually and explain in your comments WHY those things have the most influence for you.
  2. How often (if at all) do you visit a dermatologist or an aesthetician?  What services are you regularly receiving?  How do these influence your choices of product (if at all)?
  3. Where do you prefer to shop for luxury skin care - department stores, online, Sephora, boutiques?  Take screen grab of the type of environment that is most compelling for you.  Do you prefer an open environment/self-service model like Sephora or having interaction with sales associates/experts in a department store?  Why? Can the sales associate’s opinions and knowledge get you to try new things or convert from other brands?  Tell me about it.
  4. Do points or loyalty programs play a role in where you shop and if so, what do you desire in return?  How important are promotions or gift with purchase?  Product samples?  When you really think about it, what really drives your loyalty to a shopping environment, and to specific luxury skin care products?
  5. When you shop for luxury skincare, do you typically narrow down a brand's offering by shopping for a specific type of product (i.e. cream, serum, eye cream) or is it more by benefit – ie anti-aging, brightening, hydration, etc.)?
  6. When it comes to price, is there a threshold on what you will spend for a product to which you are loyal?  Is there a certain category that you are willing to invest more in than others?
  7. How important is product exclusivity – ie items that are exclusively available at one retailer?  Does that add to a sense of discovery or loyalty to that store?  How important is a sense of discovery when it comes to luxury skin care products?

(time estimate: 20 minutes)

 

THIRD, you're going shopping.  Choose an actual store where you really love to browse for luxury skin care products.  We realize that you may shop online for some products but we'd like to start in an actual store.

 

Please wander as you normally would and stop wherever you are interested.  Take pictures of whatever catches your eye, and describe why it got your attention. We are really curious about what draws you in – ie the display, the brand name, beautiful packaging, a friendly salesperson (if there is one), etc.  If you find a product that you're seriously coveting, please photograph and then define – why do you desire it?

(time estimate:  1 hour)

 

FOURTH, we’re going to talk about shopping online. Please take screen grabs of where you shop for luxury skin care products online, if you do.  Please send screen shots of all online stores that are in your repertoire, and describe what you typically buy there and why – even if it’s only occasional.

(time estimate:  15 minutes)

 

FINALLY, please have someone record you speaking to us on the following subject.  The video should be about a minute in length.  Think about it first, then use the video to tell us:  if you had your own luxury skin care store or luxury skin care website, what would be your best in class practices?  Describe what the experience would be like for the customer If you are in a store, what services are you receiving?  If you are online, how are you delivering a sense of luxury?  What is most important in this luxury skin care shopping experience?

(time estimate: 15 minutes)

study_instructions: Congrats on being contacted for this fun study on plant-based food options! No matter where you are on your journey with plant-based eating, we want to understand your perspective. There are no right or wrong answers. We’re simply interested in your honest opinions on the products and choices we’ll be discussing. You have a week to complete the study at your own pace. The one important thing to note is that we need you to complete a food diary for two subsequent days, as part of the study, recording what you eat, where, why, etc. It’s important that eat and make choices as you normally do during those days. We want real life!  And, it’s <u>totally fine</u> if you eat meat during these two days if that is what you would normally do. We’re interested in the dynamics around these daily choices! Topics One, Two and Three cover your lifestyle and attitude towards plant-based foods. Topics Four & Five consist of a food diary – we just really want to see what you eat during the course of a normal day! Topic Six – you take us on a little shopping trip to buy some plant-based frozen food! Topic Seven – we’ll focus on a specific brand of plant-based food and wrap up the discussion. We will be asking for lots of screenshots and one piece of video at the end where you talk to the camera briefly in your own words. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by July 30. Beginning the week of August 2nd, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

Freshman
study_instructions: LOOKLOOK™: Campus Life Food Study Part I: Complete prior to Tuesday September 25th Part II: Complete on Wednesday, September 26th   Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ University of Virginia University Campus Life Food Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen. This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus. We don’t need you to write us a novel on every food choice. We just want you to simply take pictures of everything you choose to eat (and where you are eating it). These will be the basis of discussion for us to ask you about the surrounding experience of those food choices. Beyond the food itself, we also want to understand the importance of the overall environment (look, feel, seating, general vibe, etc.), the customer service, and anything else that’s important to you. We realize you are busy – and perhaps can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting you’re experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook™ is that you can snap pictures (or video, if you are motivated), save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  DO THIS WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! HERE ARE THE TASKS: Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Tuesday, September 25th. Please complete Part II on Wednesday, September 26th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or coffee time. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday, September 26th. PART I – DAY ONE YOU 1.   FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following: a.   How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis? b.   What is important to you when it comes to food? Anything from “Chef-prepared” to local ingredients, to sustainable practices, etc.? 2.   Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots here but no stock photos please!   YOUR SCHOOL 3.   What adjectives would you use to describe the student body at U of VA? Why? Upload a photo that represents the student body.   FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL 4.   Which dining facilities do you tend to use most often at school? What are the main points of contact you come into on a daily basis that offer you food or drink?  (This can include on or off campus.)  Please take pictures to show us each and every single one – down to the condiments for your tea or coffee.  This is all about the details! 5. Upload a photo that represents how you feel about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen that photo and what does that photo represent? Are there any new facilities offering anything different or exciting?  If so, please visit and photograph for us, with your opinions about it!  6.    Are there any branded franchises on the campus today (ie Starbucks, etc) – or if not, are there ones you’d be delighted to see? Take a picture or screenshot of any you’d like to see added to the mix. 7.    What (if anything) do you miss from home – food-wise?  Take a picture to represent it!  Do you think there’s any way to replicate this on-campus in any way? PART II – DAY TWO FOOD JOURNAL 8. We want to understand all points of availability of food that you experience during a typical day, and how campus dining fits in. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.  PLEASE START THIS WHEN YOU WAKE UP IN THE MORNING! a.   What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? b.   What are you eating? c.   Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now? d.   What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts?  What was great – or what could be better? 9.  DREAMING      What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Also think beyond food and drink. What else could your college possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?   PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this!   Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study on how you make movie choices, and where the movies fit into your overall world of entertainment! 
 
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of where and how movies fit into your life. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Be sure to press SEND after entering your comments!
 
You will not receive notifications on your phone when your moderator starts sending you follow-ups, but you will see that a topic circle turns orange if they have engaged on that topic. You will see their comments marked with an orange symbol: "moderator comment". Your moderator will continue to ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
 
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty! Have fun!

name: Sophomore
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

study_instructions: Welcome to this creative ideation session where you will be weighing in on the most appealing way to bring a new brand character to life! We’re talking to people of all ages and walks of life who include grain or protein bars as part of a balanced lifestyle. It doesn’t matter whether you currently eat them, but for this LookLook session we are focusing on the Belvita brand! Please be expressive with the questions that ask for written responses! Welcome to this study! You are part of a select group of women from all ages across the country. This study has been designed by SPARK, not any specific brand or company. Each Topic is meant to explore how your immediate world might have shifted as a result of the Covid-19 phenomenon that is unfolding into our lives day by day. No right or wrong answers - we're looking for very authentic, honest opinions. And, no judgment. Some people really are finding there to be nightmarish aspects of this, while there are also some enjoyable silver linings! We want to hear it all. Thanks for making your voice heard!

name: GUESTS
study_instructions: 欢迎您参与此次调研！我们希望通过此次对话，详细地了解中国男性消费者购买高级运动服/休闲服的整个体验过程。您的想法和见解将会帮到lululemonx线上和线下实体店的店内体验设计，并为lululemon男士的品牌/营销策略提供更多的灵感，谢谢！

name: Unnaculturated
study_instructions:
¡Bienvenidos a este estudio! Usted ha sido seleccionado para formar parte de un grupo especial de personas a lo largo y ancho del país para explorar y entender mejor cómo su mundo inmediato puede haber cambiado como resultado del fenómeno Covid-19. Aunque vamos a explorar un amplio rango de temas, es importante que sepa que no hay una respuesta correcta o incorrecta a cualquier pregunta, ¡sus verdaderos sentimientos y respuestas sinceras son de gran valor para nosotros!
Hay algunas preguntas donde le pedimos que nos conteste con un video, y verá que solo la opción de video estará activa. Para las demás preguntas, podrá contestar con texto o video según lo prefiera y agregar imágenes y emojis para ilustrar su respuesta.
¡Muchas gracias!

name: Participants
study_instructions: In this study, we want to understand your sensitive skin issues and how you approach caring for it. Tata Harper is excited to hear your feedback on Superkind, their line for sensitive skin. Remember, the brand will be selecting some participants' video footage for their marketing, which comes with extra compensation! So be sure to use your tripod and ensure you're well-lit and in a quiet place. Thanks!

name: Luxury Car Buyers
study_instructions:
欢迎您来到这个有关豪华轿车的品牌调研！在这个调研中，我们希望您能和我们分享您个人对于奢华轿车的看法以及一款即将在中国上市的新概念豪华轿车的感想。
在您的主页上，每一个圆圈都代表一个不同的话题。您需要点击每一个圆圈进入回答，对于其中的每一个问题，您都可以进行相应的回答/上传图片和截屏。
当主持人对您的回答进行确认并完成追问后，话题圆圈将会变成“蓝色”。当最后您看到所有的话题圆圈变成蓝色后，即代表您完成了此次调研。
希望您能尽情并如实地表达您的观点，这样我们的调研会更有意义。您写下的所有信息都将“严格保密”，并仅作为调研使用。
最后，感谢您的参与，让我们听到您的声音！

name: China HC - Male
study_instructions:
恭喜您被甄选为本次有关运动服饰尺码合身问题调研的参与者！
本次调研中，我们将会邀请您和我们分享您过往购买运动服饰品牌的经历以及在实体店和线上购物中关于尺码和试穿等问题的反馈。
当您进入调研的页面中，您的主页上会出现不同的圆圈，每个圈都会代表一个大的话题，每个话题下会分别有一些小问题需要您的回答，根据题目提示，会需要您发表您的观点，上传相关图片，截屏，或者录制并上传相关短片视频。
在您回答之后，主持人会进行随机的追问，您可以进入到相关问题下再次回答。在追问环节结束后，您的话题圆圈会从之前的“橙色”变成“蓝色”这表示该话题下的问题已全部完成，直到所有的话题圆圈均变成蓝色，此次调研才算全部结束。
我们希望您能真诚如实地回答我们的问题，这将对我们的调研起到非常至关重要的作用。我们希望通过这次机会和您进行一次隔空“对话”而不是书面调查！请您放心，调研中您给予的所有回答，资料和信息，我们都将严格保密。我们非常尊重您的隐私并希望您也能对本次调研中所看到的信息进行保密。
最后，衷心感谢您和我们分享您的看法并献出您宝贵的时间参与此次调研！
在调研中我们会经常提到运动服饰以及非运动服饰，为了让您有更清楚的认识，我们对于这两个概念的解释分别是：
运动服饰：您锻炼时所穿的服装，比如：打底紧身裤，慢跑运动裤，短裤，运动上衣，运动胸衣等
非运动服饰：日常休闲服饰，比如牛仔裤，长裤，T恤，长袖上衣，连帽衫，线衫等

name: Sam
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Athleisure Discovery

 

INTRODUCTION:

Congratulations on being selected for this study on athleisure’s role in your life and how you explore brands online!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolve” the post. Resolved posts will have a blue check mark on them. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-WORK VIDEO

Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignment during the weekend prior to the study.

 

Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out three (3) of your favorite athleisure and/or activewear items on your bed.

 

Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following: 

 

Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM.  If you want to submit three separate videos, that’s cool.  Or you would rather do the three pieces in one take, that is also fine – but please limit the length of the video to about 2 minutes total.

 

1.     What brand is this? Where did you buy it (if online, please specify)? When did you buy it? And why did you buy it?

2.     Roughly how much of your athleisure/activewear wardrobe is made up of this brand?

3.     What do you do while wearing this piece? (Exercise, lounge, etc). We are super interested in what items you choose for certain workout or non-workout activities!

4.     What product characteristics make this item good for doing that?  (Speak to fit, feel, function, style – whatever is important to you and for that activity!)

5.     Finally, how do you feel when wearing it?

 

DAY ONE:  A DAY IN YOUR LIFE!

 

1.     VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever it is that you see when you wake up!

COMMENT: What are we seeing here?  How are you feeling at this moment about the day ahead? 

 

2.     VISUAL: Take a picture or two of anything that is part of your morning ritual, from coffee to breakfast, to your commute, to meditation or exercise.

COMMENT: How do each of these elements make you feel?  What do you get out of it?

 

3.     VISUAL: Upload a few screenshots – or take pictures – of a few things that represent things that bring you JOY or INSPIRE YOU.

COMMENT:

·       What is this? Why are you passionate about this?

·       What is one goal you have that feels difficult to achieve but you REALLY WANT? What is standing in the way (if anything)?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of your work/studying or other primary activity during the day.

COMMENT:

·       How do you feel at various points of time during the primary part of your day?

·       What are the “pain points” (if any?)

·       What parts do you generally enjoy the most?

 

5.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of the most SOCIAL part of your day.

COMMENT: Who are you interacting with? How do you feel at these times?

 

6.     VISUAL: Think for a minute about the news and content/entertainment that draws you in (we’ll get to social media in a second.) Upload some screenshots that fill me in on the kind of content you enjoy.

COMMENT: What do you enjoy about these choices? What do you think they say about you?

 

7.     VISUAL: Now consider social media: Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn, Reddit, etc. Upload a screenshot or two that tells me which you engage with the most.

COMMENT:

·       For each, describe your way of participating. Do you observe more, or post more?

·       What do you enjoy about each social platform that you’re involved with? How important is it to you?

·       What brands or influencers do you follow on social media, and what do you get out of it?

·       What is your favorite brand to follow? Why? How has this impacted your perception of the brand? Your likelihood to purchase that brand?

 

8.     VISUAL: If you exercise at all regularly, please upload a picture of you doing what you do – i.e. workout, running, a fitness class, etc.

COMMENT:

·       Why do you exercise?

·       How important is exercising to you?

·       What is your favorite way to sweat? How frequently do you do this – and are there any other parts to your fitness repertoire?

·       How do you feel during exercising? Afterwards? Does this vary by activity?

 

9.     VISUAL:  We’re living in an age of technology obsession. Take a picture of any device or app that you are currently enjoying. 

COMMENT: What do you love about this? Do you ever use any tech as part of your fitness routine (apps, wearables, etc)? Why or why not?

 

10.  VISUAL: When evening rolls around, take a picture that tells me what you do for relaxation, or any other kind of evening activity or ritual.

COMMENT: What is it and what do you like about this?

 

11.  VISUAL: As you reflect on the day, what do you wish you could spend MORE time doing (if anything)? Upload a photo or screenshot to represent that.

COMMENT: Finally, if you had all the time in the world, what would you like to spend more time doing? Why?

 

PLEASE NOTE: Feel free to “ad lib” in this Day in the Life section and share additional photos, screenshots and comments about anything that tells me WHAT MAKES YOU YOU!  Food and drink choice posts are also super relevant and interesting here!

 

DAY TWO: LULULEMON & OTHER BRANDS – HOW DO YOU EXPLORE THEM?

 

12.  VISUAL:  Please take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? 

COMMENT:  FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how? 

 

13.  VISUAL: When you hear the lululemon name or see the logo, what comes immediately to mind? Upload a screenshot that represents this (it can be anything – be conceptual and creative!).

COMMENT: To what extend would you agree “lululemon is a brand for me” on a scale of 1-5 (with 5 being the strongest)? Why?

name: Future Guests - France
Potential Guest - In Store (Shopping for Female)
Educators
Non-Readers
study_instructions:
You have been selected for this project because we know you through a past luxury or fashion study or because you have been referred by a past participant. You have style, you are literate in luxury, well-versed in fashion and beauty, and you know your way around both online and boutique/department store shopping. Because you are successful, yet young and on your way up, some marketers would call you a HENRY – a “High Earner Not Rich Yet”. The objective of this study is to understand a little more about the lives of individual HENRY women across the country. We are curious to know how you like to live, how you curate your purchases, how you prioritize your spending, and how you weave in luxury brands with less expensive purchases. Please note that you don’t have to make everything look camera-ready in this study. We do want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. So don’t worry about everything needing to look perfect! One of the topics we will want to explore with you is how you feel about spending money and saving money. We will not be talking with you about your salary. But we will talk about where you prioritize your spending, and the challenges of living the life you want and fulfilling your dreams given the challenges of modern life. Some of the women in the study are married, some are divorced, some have little kids, some have no children, others have grown children. Everyone is busy with many interests. We want to hear about how you strive for balance and make room for the things you are passionate about. And of course – we want to go shopping with you. Shopping is a big part of this study, and we’re going to be super curious about your preferences and your choices. There are no right or wrong answers! We just want your candid honesty.  Below are the three days’ assignments. We recommend planning to complete one on each of the three days of the study – but if you want to get it all done on the weekend, feel free! DAY ONE: SHOW US AROUND!
Let’s start with you telling us a little about where you live. Take some pictures of your home or apartment and tell us both what you love about it and what you envision changing about it, if anything. Next we want you to show us some possessions you have acquired that really spark joy in your life – across a few categories. Specifically, we’d like to see a few items in each of the areas below. With each picture, tell me where you bought it, the name of the brand and what you love about it. 1. FASHION 2. BEAUTY
3. JEWELRY (Can include watches)
4. HOME GOODS (ie furniture, art, kitchen appliance) Next, choose an image to accompany your answer to each of the following questions (it’s fine to just Google search an image on your phone):
  1. (Post an image that represents your answer in some way): “My personal definition of luxury is _______________________________”. Note: There is no right or wrong way to answer this – for some people it may about the history of a brand or item, or craftsmanship, its rarity or just the way it makes you feel.
  2. (Post an image that represents your answer in some way): “My personal definition of success is_______________________________”
  3. (Post an image that represents your answer in some way): “I will really feel like I’ve made it when __________________________.”
  4. Next, put together a go-to outfit for work that makes you feel authentic and powerful. We would love to see you model this outfit but you could also hang it on hangers or lay it out on your bed. Please include jewelry, shoes and handbag. (Can you tell, details matter in this study?) Take a picture and answer these questions:
    1. I feel great in this for work because ________________________.
    2. The reason this type of outfit is a good fit for my work environment is ___________________________________.
    3. The most important piece in this whole ensemble is ____________ because it makes me feel __________________________.
    4. If I don’t feel confident in the outfit I’m wearing at work I _________________.
  5. Now, compose an outfit to show us or you can share a picture of you where you are wearing something you love going out in – ie with your friends, on a date, etc. Again, include detail – jewelry, shoes, whatever completes the look. Take a picture and answer these questions: a. I describe this style as ______________________________________.
    b. The most important piece in this ensemble is _______________________     because it makes me feel ____________________________________.
  6. Take a picture of your jewelry collection – ie where you keep your earrings, rings, necklaces. Answer these questions with that picture:
    1. Give me some words to describe your jewelry style. What are some of your favorite brands of jewelry?
    2. What role does costume jewelry play vs. fine jewelry? When do you wear either / both?
c. When purchasing fine jewelry, is it something you buy personally or more likely to be gifted? d. Do you own a fine watch? (If so, show us!) Do you wear a watch every day? If so, is it more for style or function (in the day of iPhones, maybe it’s just a style statement?). What’s your dream watch?
  1. Next, gather your three favorite skin care products. Why are these your favorites, and where did you buy them?
  2. Finally, gather your three favorite makeup products. What does each of these do for you? Where did you buy them?
  3. Final question of the day – what are some other “things” in your life that represent YOUR personal definition of luxury? (ie could be a car, a piece of jewelry passed down from your mother, an eye cream, your passport or a picture of a vacation, your closet or even your home - anything!) Show us one or two and tell us why.
DAY TWO: Shopping! Pre-Shopping Questions
We’re going to shopping with you, but a few important questions first!
  1. If you had a whole afternoon to spend shopping for fashion – just for you – where would you choose to go? Think about this, and show us a few screen grabs/images that bring this to life. Would it be a department store? A neighborhood of boutiques? A shopping mall? Maybe you’d rather curl up on your sofa and shop online? If so, take screen grabs on your phone of the websites or apps you love to experience. As you share your online shopping habits, please answer these questions:
    1. What percent of your fashion shopping is done online vs. in store? Why? Does it vary by price tag/type of item?
    2. Do you tend to get more excited about finding an “It” item that is super popular, or finding things that no one else has? How do your choices reflect your individual style?
  2. Now show me some screen grabs of where you most enjoy shopping for beauty products – ie makeup and skin care, and answer these questions: a. What do you most enjoy about shopping for makeup and skin care and why? b. How do you discover new products and trends? If you read magazines or blogs or vlogs specific to beauty, please show us these with screen grabs. c. What percentage of your beauty purchases take place online?
  3. What about jewelry – where do you go for that? (Show a screen grab) Does it differ for fine jewelry vs. costume jewelry?
  4. Handbags?
  1. Technology?
  2. Home goods?
  3. We’re all a work in progress. What do you feel you still need to learn about shopping and about how to build the wardrobe – and the lifestyle - to which you ultimately aspire? Capture a screen grab that brings this to life somehow. Then answer these questions:
    1. Do you consider yourself a savvy shopper? If so, how exactly are you savvy? What are some of the tricks and tips you’ve learned?
    2. If you were to cultivate even better shopping skills than you already have, what would that look like? Would it involve a personal shopper? Relationships with great sales associates? If the world of shopping were at your command, what would it provide you with?
  4. Everyone talks about the “experience” being so important in retail these days. Take a picture of a brand that is doing a great job at this, in your opinion (could be fashion, beauty, auto, wellness, travel, etc – anything you feel strongly about! Bricks and mortar, please – not online.) Answer these questions: a. How have they created a great experience? What does this even mean to you? b. Take a screen grab of a brand that you used to love but has fallen off your radar. What did they stop doing – why did they lose relevance for you? What could they do (from an experiential perspective) to make you love them again?
  5. What brands are in your future that aren’t there now? Are there any you aspire to – or feel out of reach – that you’d like to get to know better? Send me screen grabs of the logos and please speak to that.
Time to Go Shopping! Take us to your favorite neighborhood of boutiques, a department store or other type of shopping mecca. We want to you choose a place where you can show us clothing, jewelry, shoes, and beauty.
  1. Take a picture of the outside of a favorite store. With the picture, describe how often you visit here, and what usually motivates you to come? How are you feeling outside of the store?
  2. Next, go inside and visit just enjoy browsing. We want to experience this through you. Take a picture of anything that catches your eye, and describe your thought process. What is your mind telling you about potential purchases? What is your internal conversation? At each destination while you shop, what are you feeling and what could make the experience better? (NOTE: please visit enough shops to show us clothing, jewelry, shoes, and beauty.)
3. When you get home, put up your feet and do a little online shopping and take some screen grabs of places you shop or browse online. Attached to these images, please answer these questions: a. What do you get out of shopping online vs. in-store?
b. Do you ever buy fashion or beauty on Amazon? Why or why not?
c. What are your favorite places to shop online?
d. Where do you end up making final purchases – online or in-store? Do you use one way of shopping more for browsing and one for transacting? Why? And does that vary with what you’re buying? DAY THREE:
The last day is about some self-reflection and also about learning where you go for inspiration and discovery. You’ll also record a video.
  1. Show me a little of your social media. Send me screen grabs of your very favorite influences on Instagram, Facebook and Pinterest. (These can be fashion bloggers, brands, celebs, or entertainment/humor sites). With each, describe it a bit and tell me why you love it.
  2. What role does word of mouth with your friends and co-workers play when it come to discovering new looks, new products, new apps, etc? If you text with your friends about purchases or anything fashion related, take a screen shot of your groups texts and share that.
  3. Do you read magazines? Either print or online? If so, take pictures and show me your favorite parts of those publications. Why do you like them? (NOTE: BAZAAR readers, we want to know what it is you love about the magazine, how it is distinct from other magazines, is it shoppable, what you feel you can count on it for, etc. NON-BAZAAR readers, what do you think of when you see Harper’s BAZAAR magazine? Have either heard of or visited ShopBAZAAR.com? or made a purchase?
  4. Next were going to talk a little bit about money. Find an image or picture that represents how you feel about your financial situation and answer the following questions: a. What are your personal financial goals?
    b. At what level of wealth will you feel that you are where you want to be?
    c. What does it mean to you to be financially responsible?
    d. Do you use any sort of investment tools (like Mint) or a personal investment     advisor?
 
  1. Next let’s talk about your wish list. Show me what you would do with a windfall of $500? $1,000? $10,000? $100,000? How would you spend each of these amounts? Show me a picture that represents each.
  2. Your future – find an image that represents where you see yourself in 5 years, and then in 10 years. Where do you envision yourself at these points in your future?
FINAL TASK: VIDEO COMMENTARY When you get to this point, your moderator is going to ask you to speak on a particular subject that you have touched on in the study – this is going to be personalized to each respondent. Your video response should be about a minute in length. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!
Please remember to answer all the moderator follow-up questions.

study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this important study on gluten-free pizza!Against the Grain is growing fast as a brand and we want to collect your feedback to understand how we can make it even better.In this study we want to understand the role that gluten-free foods play in your life, how you shop for them, how you discovered Against the Grain, and what we can do to make it even better!As someone who buys gluten-free, we also want to talk about what is important to communicate on gluten-free products and how new products get on your radar!Each of the topics in this study contains a set of questions which you can answer at your leisure as long as you’ve completed them by end of day Sunday June 6th! Definitely take a read through in advance.Next week, we’ll let you know when to expect follow-up questions! In the meantime, please be generous with pictures, screenshots and commentary! It’s all about the details in this kind of research! Thanks!

study_instructions:
恭喜您被甄选为本次有关运动服饰尺码合身问题调研的参与者！
本次调研中，我们将会邀请您和我们分享您过往购买运动服饰品牌的经历以及在实体店和线上购物中关于尺码和试穿等问题的反馈。
当您进入调研的页面中，您的主页上会出现不同的圆圈，每个圈都会代表一个大的话题，每个话题下会分别有一些小问题需要您的回答，根据题目提示，会需要您发表您的观点，上传相关图片，截屏，或者录制并上传相关短片视频。
在您回答之后，主持人会进行随机的追问，您可以进入到相关问题下再次回答。在追问环节结束后，您的话题圆圈会从之前的“橙色”变成“蓝色”这表示该话题下的问题已全部完成，直到所有的话题圆圈均变成蓝色，此次调研才算全部结束。
我们希望您能真诚如实地回答我们的问题，这将对我们的调研起到非常至关重要的作用。我们希望通过这次机会和您进行一次隔空“对话”而不是书面调查！请您放心，调研中您给予的所有回答，资料和信息，我们都将严格保密。我们非常尊重您的隐私并希望您也能对本次调研中所看到的信息进行保密。
最后，衷心感谢您和我们分享您的看法并献出您宝贵的时间参与此次调研！
在调研中我们会经常提到运动服饰以及非运动服饰，为了让您有更清楚的认识，我们对于这两个概念的解释分别是：
运动服饰：您锻炼时所穿的服装，比如：打底紧身裤，慢跑运动裤，短裤，运动上衣，运动胸衣等
非运动服饰：日常休闲服饰，比如牛仔裤，长裤，T恤，长袖上衣，连帽衫，线衫等

name: Participants
study_instructions:
STUDY INSTRUCTIONS

 

Welcome to the Smartphone Study!

 

You've been selected for this particular study because you own a particular type of Android device with 1 GB of RAM or less.  We’ll be chatting with you about how you use your phone, specifically which apps you are using and any frustrations you encounter with your phone – ie slowness, freezing, etc.

 

Below are the tasks we need you to complete over the next two days. For each question, please upload a relevant photo with your response. We're just looking for your honest opinions so just give us the straight talk – there are no right or wrong answers!

 

You can work through the study at your leisure – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along!

 

 

THE TASKS

 

DAY 1

TELL US ABOUT YOUR PHONE!

 

• PHOTO:  Take a screen grab you find on the Internet of your current phone that shows the make and model.  COMMENT:  Tell me about your phone.  How long have you had it?

 

• PHOTO:  Take a screen grab from the Internet that shows me the place where you purchased or received your phone. COMMENT:  How much did you pay for it? 

 

• PHOTO:  Next, go into SETTINGS and take a screen grab of the ABOUT PHONE screen to show me some of the technical aspects of your phone. COMMENT:  What operating system does it run? Are you familiar with what storage capacity it has? Amount of RAM? Please upload a screen grab with this information on your phone screen along with your response.  If it’s too hard to figure out, just tell me that.

 

• PHOTO:  Take a screen grab of your cell phone carrier. COMMENT: Who provides your service, and how much data do you have to use, per month? Do you watch your data usage closely?  Why or why not?  Do you have pre-paid service or do you have a contract?

 

• PHOTO:  Take a screen grab off the internet of your previous phone make and model. COMMENT:  What did you use before you got your current phone?  Where had you obtained that phone, and what carrier provided your service?  How does your newer phone compare to that one?  Why did you switch to the new phone?

 

• Do you have more than one phone? If not, skip to the next question.  If you do have a secondary phone, PHOTO please take a picture of it.  COMMENT:  what do you use each of your phones for?  Why? Is there one phone you are more proud to use in front of other people for any reason? 

 

• PHOTO:  Next, please find an image on the internet that represents how you feel about your data and the limits on your data.  Be creative and expressive – this should be some sort of feeling or emotion!  Screen grab and upload it.  COMMENT:  How do you manage your data plan? Do you ever have to make choices about what you do on your phone according to how much data it might require?

 

HOW YOU USE YOUR PHONE

 

• PHOTO:  Find an image on the internet and take a screen grab of it that represents the role that your smartphone plays in your life.  COMMENT:  Describe how you use your phone during a typical day. How early in the morning do you check your phone? What do you use your phone for?  Work?  Entertainment? Other stuff?

 

• PHOTO:  Take screen grabs of the apps you use the most.  This can be anything, from YouTube, to Google Mail, to Google Maps, to Candy Crush.  COMMENTS:  For each one, please answer these questions:

o What do you use this one for?

o How often do you use it?  How many minutes per day would you estimate you spend using this app?

o If you could think of any way you would like to improve the performance of this app, what would it be?

 

• PHOTO:  Next, please take screen grabs of any websites you browse using your phone.  COMMENT:  How is the experience, generally speaking, of Internet browsing on your phone? Do you ever run into any problems?  I’d love to hear about this, in detail!

 

• PHOTO:  Find an image on the Internet and take a screen grab that shows me how attached you are to your phone.  COMMENT:  When you think about how important phones are to people these days, where do you fall on that spectrum… in other words, is your phone one of your most important possessions, or is it just a phone? 

 

 

A NEW SMARTPHONE

 

1. Now we’re going to share some benefits of a new kind of smartphone with an optimized operating system for phones that run on 1 GB of RAM or less. 

 

2. The features they are thinking of including are the following – we are curious as to which appeal to you and why.  With each one, tell me what is interesting about it, AND how appealing it is to you on a scale of 1-10, with TEN being MOST APPEALING. 

 

a. When I’m about to look at a video on YouTube, I can first take a look at how much data will be uses (against my limit) so I can make an easy choice between  higher or lower streaming quality.  (The lower streaming quality will take up less data.)

b. I can check how much data various apps use (on average) and easily turn them on and off to conserve data

c. I can download YouTube videos while connected to WiFi and then save them to view offline later so I won’t use data for watching them

d. I would have a special tool to show me how much data I have left, with an option to top up from my carrier if and when I want to

e. I can preview videos on YouTube before getting caught in an expensive, heavy data download

f. I can share content like photos, videos, etc with a friend or family member in close physical proximity without having to use data or WiFi 

g. It would have longer battery life than my current phone

h. It would have more storage than my current phone.

i. I can easily switch my keyboard between two different languages 

 

3. PHOTO:  Find an image on the internet that represents your level of excitement around this new phone and share it with me.  COMMENT:  Why does this image represent your feelings about the new phone?  If a new phone came out priced less than $100 with these features would it be something you might be interested in if you could trade for it?  Why? Why or why not?

 

DAY TWO

 

Welcome to Day Two! Today, we want to see a day in the life of your smartphone! 

 

You will be journaling everything you do on your smartphone today via LookLook. 

 

Send us screen grabs of everything you’re doing on your phone, whether it’s playing a game, making a call, browsing the internet, texting, scrolling through social media, or getting GPS directions, we want to see it all! With every photo you post, please tell us what you’re doing on your phone and how well your phone is performing the various tasks. If you have any moments of frustration or gratitude towards your smartphone, we want to hear about them!

 

FINALLY, please have someone record you while you create a video for us. The video should be roughly a minute in length. Think about your answers to the questions first, then answer the following questions:

 

● What role does your smartphone play in your life?

● If you could talk to your smartphone and ask it to do a better job, how would you ask it to step up its performance?

 

THANK YOU!  You will be finished with this study when you answer all of the moderator’s follow-up questions.

Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study. It’s designed for people like you that live and breathe the creative content industry. What we want to understand from this is what the ideal workplace can look like coming out of Covid (whenever that will be). We’ll discuss what kind of environment would get you excited to accept an offer somewhere, and more importantly, would get you excited to go in and be in that place and do great work!
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of your experience of workplaces you have known in the past, your current workplace, and the type of office environment that you would consider a game-changer in the future.  
For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!
