name: NYC
study_instructions: Congratulations on being selected for this important study on what the American Workplace looks like as the country deals with the challenges of reopening post-Covid.The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other aspects of your work environment can boost your motivation and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable as you return to the office post-Covid.Each topic on your LookLook home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)!All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study! We are looking to understand your lifestyle, values, and attitudes towards technology.
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of your experience with technology.  
For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow up questions throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: Millennials no Kids
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study! We are excited to learn from you over the next few days as you reflect on how you shop for things that are necessary (or just fun). In particular, we’re looking to understand how Covid has shifted some of your preferences and behavior, and what you think you might want from shopping experiences in the future! We’ve organized these into a few modules to be completed over a week. Each “day” is a different topic that explores various aspects of shopping. For each question throughout the study, please upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Visual details are super important in this one)!Please complete all questions by the end of Sunday night and look for follow ups on Monday and Tuesday. Have fun!

Je ehrlicher und ausdrucksfähiger Du bist, desto besser wirst Du diese Studie bearbeiten können. Alle Informationen werden ausschließlich zu Forschungszwecken und STRENG VERTRAULICH behandelt. Vielen Dank, dass Du Deine Stimme gibst!

name: Participants
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™ Study: Creating the Ideal Work Environment Location: Seattle Metro
Instructions for Participants Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ Study on Dining, Amenities, and Creating the Ideal Work Environment! If you have not yet sent a selfie to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen. The purpose of this study is to collect a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how you feel during your workday. What sort of new culinary experiences would you want to see added? What other amenities would be valuable? What does the modern workplace demand today not only to meet your needs, but to get you excited and make you feel proud and excited to work where you do? Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below – and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me. There are no right or wrong answers in this study – we’re just looking for your opinions! Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them. I’ll be responding to most of your comments and answering these follow-up questions should about an additional hour. Some are dependent on being at work, but the majority can be answered anywhere, as the requested visuals are screenshots you can capture right on your smartphone. PLEASE NOTE: We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – ie for 1a, 1b, etc. Generally speaking, the more pictures the better!
In this study, it’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE
QUESTIONS BELOW, PLEASEJ
THE QUESTIONS
  1. 1)  KICKING OFF THE DAY
    1. SHOW ME WHAT YOU EAT FOR BREAKFAST! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute...? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
    2. NEXT, SHOW ME A PICTURE OF SOMETHING THAT REPRESENTS YOUR COMMUTE. Whether it is 5 minutes or 50 minutes, give me a glimpse of the experience, and describe it in a few sentences, including what you may enjoy or hate about it.
  2. 2)  DAY IN THE LIFE
    1. TAKE A PICTURE OF YOUR DESK AREA. How long have you worked at your current company? Give me three descriptive adjectives that describe the energy at your company, and then three words that come to mind that describe the feeling and rhythm of any given workday.
    2. Now, think back for a second – was there anything about the physical office space at your firm that you were excited about when you first joined...? TAKE A PICTURE OF ANYTHING YOU WOULD MISS IF YOU LEFT!
    3. Next, TAKE A PICTURE OF ANYTHING YOU LOVE ABOUT YOUR CURRENT WORK ENVIRONMENT. This could be an amenity you value... as small a detail as filtered water or free coffee, or a beautiful atrium or collaborative workspace – anything goes. What do you like most about the physical set up of your current office/campus?
    4. Think for a minute about what you feel needs to be overhauled in the current setup – architecture, design, conference rooms, break rooms, collaborative workspaces, availability of any cafes in the building or in-house dining options (or lack thereof)? NOW TAKE A QUICK WALK AROUND AND SNAP SOME PICTURES OF THOSE ASPECTS THAT NEED ADDRESSING. With each, please describe how you would change it!
    5. TAKE A PICTURE OF AN AREA AT YOUR WORK WHERE MEETINGS TAKE PLACE. Do you ever attend meetings that are catered? What comments can you share on the quality of the food and beverages offered? What would you love to see instead?
  3. 3)  CREATING THE FUTURE!
    1. Now forget about your current place of work. We want to shift gears and get your ideas on what the ideal workplace of the future would look like! FIND A SCREENSHOT OF THE TYPE OF AMBIENCE YOU WOULD WANT TO SEE CREATED at this ideal work environment. What kind of vibe appeals to you? This can be anywhere in or outside your office even in a public space.
    2. Thinking about in-house dining options, SNAP A FEW SCREENSHOTS OF THE TYPES OF FOOD YOU WOULD LIKE TO HAVE OFFERED. What are your favorite types of food to eat during a workday? Would you want breakfast offered? What would that look like? What would delight you for lunch options? What are the executional details that would be critical? (ie open all afternoon, open into the evening, dinner options packed to-go for you, diverse ethnic menu items, gluten-free, dairy-free, vegan/vegetarian options, healthy foods, etc)
    3. Thinking about the liquid fuel that keeps you going, what would you want in terms of beverage experiences? POST SOME SCREENSHOTS OF THE BEVERAGES YOU WOULD LIKE TO SEE OFFERED. Think outside the box! If coffee or tea is important, tell me about the details you would want available. And if there are other types of beverages that would improve your quality of work life, we want to hear about those too!
    4. Beyond food, what other amenities would you love in this ideal work environment? POST A FEW SCREENSHOTS OF ANY AMENITIES YOU WOULD WANT TO SEE. Can be anything from an in-house fitness center to nap pods to a Zen garden. Think big! Nothing is impossible in this exercise.
    5. CAPTURE A SCREENSHOT OF AN IMAGE THAT REPRESENTS YOUR ATTITUDE ABOUT SUSTAINABILITY and how you would want your workplace to ideally show its commitment to a greener planet. How might this translate to any dining or refreshment services? What would you like to see?
    6. Consider any company events you’ve attended, whether in small groups or larger-scale. Could be charitable/community events, or holiday fetes. Now consider how the workplace of the future could be configured to celebrate togetherness at a corporate level. What comes to mind? POST A SCREENSHOT OF WHAT A GREAT COMPANY EVENT EXPERIENCE WOULD FEEL LIKE. What would it look and feel like? Are community events important to you as part of a workplace environment? Are you involved in anything like this now? Why or why not?

4) This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work, in the Seattle metro area.

a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please visit the place near work where you go most often when not eating at work, and take a picture to accompany your answer to each of the following:

i. What is the name of this place?

ii. What do you like about this place? What do they offer that you enjoy?

iii. How often do you visit? Do you come alone or with colleagues?

iv. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details. 5) One last chance for some pie-in-the-sky dreaming. What could your work offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? What else, in addition to what you have shared already, could an employer possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS I’ll ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of my follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating! Have fun!

study_instructions: Nous sommes en août, le moment idéal pour se relaxer, réfléchir et profiter de l’instant présent. Ce mois-ci, nous allons parler de BEAUTÉ, ce que cela signifie, comment cela vous inspire, ce qui vous fait vous sentir belle, mais aussi quand, où et comment précisément vous éprouvez ce sentiment.

study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: US iPhone Older
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study! We are looking to understand your lifestyle, values, and attitudes towards technology.
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of your experience with technology.  
For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow up questions throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: High Value 25-34
study_instructions:
LookLook® STUDY:   Fashion | Shopping | Life!

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this LookLook® study on how you shop for fashion today and the role it plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior.  We want to get into the details!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping?

 

Below are the instructions for the study.  Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses.  This is not a survey, it’s a conversation!  Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK:

Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s!  These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe.  It should take about half an hour.

 

GO-TO “LOOKS”

VISUAL:  POST THREE OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS.  We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality.  If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them?  (For ex., one person might have these four: “date night”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out-and-about.” But someone else might have: “client meeting”, “girls’ night”,  “Netflix and Chill”). This is all about your particular life style! Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light.  Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding!  But apparel is the focus of this exercise.

 

COMMENT:  IN EACH POST, tell me the following:  (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who is the designer of each piece and where did you buy? (iii) Where do you typically shop for this type of look? Why?

 

STUDY DAY!  

So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions!  Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment.  Look out for my follow-ups!

 

DISCOVERY AND INSPIRATION

VISUAL:  Post at least three screenshots of places you go online that INSPIRE the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, email from a brand, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.).  Where do you tend to discover new products/styles?  With each one, please complete the comment below:

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “This is ___________.  I go here (insert frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc).  I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”

 

WHY YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Find any image or picture (even an emoji) that represents the feeling that shopping (for apparel and accessories) brings alive in you.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “I chose this image because it represents my feeling of _______________ when I shop for clothes/accessories.” Why do you shop – is it always for replenishment of something you need – or do you shop for fun? At its best, what does a great shopping experience give you?  What really motivates you to make purchases? (ads, promotions, events, Instagram, etc)

 

WHERE YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Think about the top 3 places where you spend the majority of your apparel dollars.  Post a screenshot of each destination (please list at least 2!)

 

COMMENT (FOR EACH):  Please complete in your own words:  “I tend to buy a lot of my fashion here:  _______________________ because  __________________”.  What percentage of your apparel money goes to this place, and why?

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN THE DIGITAL WORLD!

VIDEO:  Next, you’re going shopping on your phone. Just go browsing for fun. You could look for a specific item or you could just go on a favorite site or to a favorite shopping app to look around and see what you like.

 

We want you to record your screen with audio while you do this (instructions below if you are not familiar with how to do this.)

 

Spend about 1-2 minutes browsing for the item. While you’re browsing, just say out loud what you are thinking.  Tell us where you start your search and voice out loud your comments as you browse. As you click through different options, tell me why you are making your choices of where to go and what to look at. After you record for a few minutes, upload your video to LookLook®. Note: you do not have to be a Ninja at this! Just look around and talk to me while you’re browsing on your phone. If you get frustrated for any reason, mention that!

 

How to screen record on an iPhone (please be sure to turn on audio!)

  1. Go to Settings > Control Center > Customize Controls, then tap next to Screen Recording.
  2. Swipe up from the bottom edge of any screen.
  3. Press the record button firmly until the screen recording box comes up (it takes 3 seconds), turn the microphone on, and then tap Start Recording.
  4. Upload your video to LookLook®

 

How to screen record on an Android phone

5.     Download and use the free app Mobizen

6.     Enable sound before recording

7.     Upload your video to LookLook®

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN-STORE)

VISUAL:  As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place.  Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. 

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words:  “Services that I enjoy at my favorite apparel/accessories stores include _______________________”.  These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to styling, events, exclusive product lines, delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a local sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.    

 

HOW IT ALL COMES TOGETHER

VISUAL:  Imagine for a moment that someone handed you the luxury of an entire afternoon to go clothing shopping – just for you.  How would you enjoy this gift of time? Would you curl up on the couch and go shopping online? Would you visit boutiques? A mall? Post a screenshot (or a few) of where you would go shopping.

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Where is this? What do enjoy most about this experience? Provide as much detail as possible!   

 

INTERMIX

 

FAVORITE ITEM:

VISUAL:  Please screenshot an item you have purchased from Intermix in the past two years.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “This is _______________________ and I bought it ________________ (store/website)”.  In addition, share these details:  What took you to Intermix on that particular occasion? How did you discover the piece?  What role does Intermix play in keeping your clothing repertoire up to date and exciting?

 

WHO IS THE INTERMIX WOMAN?

VISUAL:  Please screenshot a picture that represents, in your mind, the Intermix brand come to life as a woman.  This can be anyone!  Yourself, a celebrity, whatever pops into your head.  Don’t over-think this.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete: “I chose this image because_____________.”  Now imagine a cocktail party where a handful of your favorite apparel retail brands are brought to life as people (you can include retail websites!)  What would each be drinking?  What are they all wearing? Who would be talking to whom?  What are the energies like of these “people”?  Have fun with this and be creative please!

 

 

 

 

INTERMIX – NEXT GENERATION!

VISUAL:  Take a screenshot or picture of any type of experience or benefit that you would like to see Intermix create.

 

COMMENT:  What did you choose, and why? 

 

THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: U.S. Participants
study_instructions: Thank you for your exciting answers on luxury clothing and care last month! We're going to continue the conversation this month by discussing a concept that’s fundamental to luxury: service. By "service" we mean everything you may experience when making a luxury purchase and beyond: from the after-sales service we talked about last month to the personalized welcome during a visit to a boutique and the little touches you may receive as a valued customer of a luxury House, etc. Please respond to this set of questions by Friday, October 8th.

name: Clients
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this very fun study on shopping for luxury brands! We are excited to learn from you over the next few days as you reflect on how shopping for luxury has changed for you since the pandemic started, and how you envision shopping in the future. We’ve organized these into a few topics to be completed at your leisure over a period of three days, as you can consider them mindfully and can give us thoughtful responses. In this study, pictures, screenshots, and videos are very important for us to understand and visualize the experiences you’re sharing. Please be generous with these throughout – thank you!

name: Prime Prospects
study_instructions: This study is designed to better understand the opportunities and challenges involved in a woman's life who is responsible for making a home "sing". We'll be curious about your tastes and preferences, and how you make choices about where to shop to stock up on necessities not just for you but others in the home!

name: Meghan
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Athleisure Discovery

 

INTRODUCTION:

Congratulations on being selected for this study on athleisure’s role in your life and how you explore brands online!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolve” the post. Resolved posts will have a blue check mark on them. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-WORK VIDEO

Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignment during the weekend prior to the study.

 

Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out three (3) of your favorite athleisure and/or activewear items on your bed.

 

Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following: 

 

Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM.  If you want to submit three separate videos, that’s cool.  Or you would rather do the three pieces in one take, that is also fine – but please limit the length of the video to about 2 minutes total.

 

1.     What brand is this? Where did you buy it (if online, please specify)? When did you buy it? And why did you buy it?

2.     Roughly how much of your athleisure/activewear wardrobe is made up of this brand?

3.     What do you do while wearing this piece? (Exercise, lounge, etc). We are super interested in what items you choose for certain workout or non-workout activities!

4.     What product characteristics make this item good for doing that?  (Speak to fit, feel, function, style – whatever is important to you and for that activity!)

5.     Finally, how do you feel when wearing it?

 

DAY ONE:  A DAY IN YOUR LIFE!

 

1.     VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever it is that you see when you wake up!

COMMENT: What are we seeing here?  How are you feeling at this moment about the day ahead? 

 

2.     VISUAL: Take a picture or two of anything that is part of your morning ritual, from coffee to breakfast, to your commute, to meditation or exercise.

COMMENT: How do each of these elements make you feel?  What do you get out of it?

 

3.     VISUAL: Upload a few screenshots – or take pictures – of a few things that represent things that bring you JOY or INSPIRE YOU.

COMMENT:

·       What is this? Why are you passionate about this?

·       What is one goal you have that feels difficult to achieve but you REALLY WANT? What is standing in the way (if anything)?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of your work/studying or other primary activity during the day.

COMMENT:

·       How do you feel at various points of time during the primary part of your day?

·       What are the “pain points” (if any?)

·       What parts do you generally enjoy the most?

 

5.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of the most SOCIAL part of your day.

COMMENT: Who are you interacting with? How do you feel at these times?

 

6.     VISUAL: Think for a minute about the news and content/entertainment that draws you in (we’ll get to social media in a second.) Upload some screenshots that fill me in on the kind of content you enjoy.

COMMENT: What do you enjoy about these choices? What do you think they say about you?

 

7.     VISUAL: Now consider social media: Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn, Reddit, etc. Upload a screenshot or two that tells me which you engage with the most.

COMMENT:

·       For each, describe your way of participating. Do you observe more, or post more?

·       What do you enjoy about each social platform that you’re involved with? How important is it to you?

·       What brands or influencers do you follow on social media, and what do you get out of it?

·       What is your favorite brand to follow? Why? How has this impacted your perception of the brand? Your likelihood to purchase that brand?

 

8.     VISUAL: If you exercise at all regularly, please upload a picture of you doing what you do – i.e. workout, running, a fitness class, etc.

COMMENT:

·       Why do you exercise?

·       How important is exercising to you?

·       What is your favorite way to sweat? How frequently do you do this – and are there any other parts to your fitness repertoire?

·       How do you feel during exercising? Afterwards? Does this vary by activity?

 

9.     VISUAL:  We’re living in an age of technology obsession. Take a picture of any device or app that you are currently enjoying. 

COMMENT: What do you love about this? Do you ever use any tech as part of your fitness routine (apps, wearables, etc)? Why or why not?

 

10.  VISUAL: When evening rolls around, take a picture that tells me what you do for relaxation, or any other kind of evening activity or ritual.

COMMENT: What is it and what do you like about this?

 

11.  VISUAL: As you reflect on the day, what do you wish you could spend MORE time doing (if anything)? Upload a photo or screenshot to represent that.

COMMENT: Finally, if you had all the time in the world, what would you like to spend more time doing? Why?

 

PLEASE NOTE: Feel free to “ad lib” in this Day in the Life section and share additional photos, screenshots and comments about anything that tells me WHAT MAKES YOU YOU!  Food and drink choice posts are also super relevant and interesting here!

 

DAY TWO: LULULEMON & OTHER BRANDS – HOW DO YOU EXPLORE THEM?

 

12.  VISUAL:  Please take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? 

COMMENT:  FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how? 

 

13.  VISUAL: When you hear the lululemon name or see the logo, what comes immediately to mind? Upload a screenshot that represents this (it can be anything – be conceptual and creative!).

COMMENT: To what extend would you agree “lululemon is a brand for me” on a scale of 1-5 (with 5 being the strongest)? Why?

name: Female Season Ticket Holders/Group Ticket Buyers
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study on The Fever!
In this study, you’ll be telling us about your connection to The Fever and how you engage with your love of sports, particularly basketball!
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study.  
For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Minneapolis
study_instructions: Congratulations on being selected for this important study on what the American Workplace looks like as the country deals with the challenges of reopening post-Covid.The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other aspects of your work environment can boost your motivation and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable as you return to the office post-Covid.Each topic on your LookLook home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)!All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

Unassigned

name: U.K.
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on enjoyable life experiences! We are excited to learn from you over the next few days as you reflect on what in-person experiences mean to you.  We’ve organised these into a handful of topics to be completed at your leisure over a period of three days, as you can consider them mindfully and can give us thoughtful responses. In this study, pictures, screenshots, and videos are very important for us to understand and visualize the experiences you’re sharing. Please be generous with these throughout – thank you. For timing, you’ll be invited to begin answering questions on Friday, October 1st. Please finish answering those questions by Sunday, October 3rd. On Monday, October 4th, a moderator will be asking you some follow-up questions and those should be answered by Tuesday, October 5th. We’ll be in touch with you throughout, via text/WhatsApp, and we’re happy to answer your questions along the way. Thank you!

name: Seniors
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Previous Regular
study_instructions: Welcome to our discussion on packaged snacks and their role in everyday life! Your input was so insightful and helpful the first time around that we now want to invite you into the creative process a bit. Based on your feedback, some new creative layouts have been developed and we would love to get your reactions to them. When you engage with the topics and questions, please post the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: Light Users NO Kids
study_instructions: Welcome to this creative ideation session where you will be weighing in on the most appealing way to bring a new brand character to life! We’re talking to people of all ages and walks of life who include grain or protein bars as part of a balanced lifestyle. It doesn’t matter whether you currently eat them, but for this LookLook session we are focusing on the Belvita brand! Please be expressive with the questions that ask for written responses! And finally, there are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty – have fun! One last note, a reminder from the LookLook® terms of service that this project is confidential, please don’t post about it on social media:No material from the Website or the Mobile App may be copied, reproduced, displayed, republished, reverse engineered, downloaded, posted, digitized, translated, modified, transmitted, distributed or commercially exploited in any way without SPARK’s express consent.

name: China HVG - Male
study_instructions:
恭喜您被甄选为本次有关运动服饰尺码合身问题调研的参与者！
本次调研中，我们将会邀请您和我们分享您过往购买运动服饰品牌的经历以及在实体店和线上购物中关于尺码和试穿等问题的反馈。
当您进入调研的页面中，您的主页上会出现不同的圆圈，每个圈都会代表一个大的话题，每个话题下会分别有一些小问题需要您的回答，根据题目提示，会需要您发表您的观点，上传相关图片，截屏，或者录制并上传相关短片视频。
在您回答之后，主持人会进行随机的追问，您可以进入到相关问题下再次回答。在追问环节结束后，您的话题圆圈会从之前的“橙色”变成“蓝色”这表示该话题下的问题已全部完成，直到所有的话题圆圈均变成蓝色，此次调研才算全部结束。
我们希望您能真诚如实地回答我们的问题，这将对我们的调研起到非常至关重要的作用。我们希望通过这次机会和您进行一次隔空“对话”而不是书面调查！请您放心，调研中您给予的所有回答，资料和信息，我们都将严格保密。我们非常尊重您的隐私并希望您也能对本次调研中所看到的信息进行保密。
最后，衷心感谢您和我们分享您的看法并献出您宝贵的时间参与此次调研！
在调研中我们会经常提到运动服饰以及非运动服饰，为了让您有更清楚的认识，我们对于这两个概念的解释分别是：
运动服饰：您锻炼时所穿的服装，比如：打底紧身裤，慢跑运动裤，短裤，运动上衣，运动胸衣等
非运动服饰：日常休闲服饰，比如牛仔裤，长裤，T恤，长袖上衣，连帽衫，线衫等

name: Non Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study!

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! 

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! 

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.' 

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. 

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink. 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! We want to see REAL LIFE - the good, the bad and the ugly. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Potential Guests
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOKTM STUDY: Athleisure & Life INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-LookTM study on the role that athleisure plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you buy nice-quality athleisure but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and passions. If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-LookTM, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does it mean for you to live a balanced life, and how do you make quality choices in today’s busy world? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. DAY ONE: A Day in Your Life
Today, I want to understand what it’s like to be you. We’d like you to document your day with visuals and send us comments on what you are doing and how you’re feeling at key points of your day. Before we get started with that, let’s start with a few questions specific to athleisure – then we’ll get on with documenting your day! VISUAL: Take a picture of a few of your favorite and most often-worn pieces of athleisure, whether it’s a jacket, shorts, pants, tank, warm-up, etc.
COMMENT: FOR EACH, tell me the following: (i) What draws you to wearing this? (ii) Where and why did you buy it? VISUAL: Take a screenshot of the stores/sites where you buy most of your athleisure. COMMENT: FOR EACH, (i) What do you count on from this store/website? What kind of athleisure do you buy here and why?
 
Thank you! Now let’s get started with “A Day in My Life!” Below are a few prompts to get you started. VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever you see when you wake up in the morning. COMMENT: What’s going through my head right now is ____________________. VISUAL: Take a few shots of your morning ritual(s). From getting ready to morning coffee, what is the rhythm of your morning? Show me.
COMMENT: Here, I’m [doing]_____________________. Feeling _____________. As you progress through your day, we’re not just interested in what you’re doing but how you’re feeling – when are you feeling good... and when are you stressed... bored, etc. Activities to document can include: work, running around, shopping, errands, spiritual practices, exercise, sports, relaxing, watching TV, listening to music, having fun with friends or family, going out, entertainment, reading/other media, taking care of a pet or loved one... really, anything that normally falls into place during a given weekday/evening. By the way, we know you’re on your phone during the day and we want to understand that too! What do you spend time on your phone doing most often – group chats? Insta/FB/Snapchat/YouTube? Games? Shopping? Fantasy football? Please send me screenshots of your phone activity. REALLY IMPORTANT: With each post, tell me something in the spirit of “This is me, [doing] _________. I’m feeling ________ because ____________.” I will respond with follow up questions in the evening, so look for the notifications that take you to my questions, either that night or first thing in the morning before we get started with Day 2. Any post with a blue dot signals there’s something from me to respond to. This will be different for everyone, but I’m expecting to see a minimum of 20 posts throughout your day and evening - but we love photos, so the more the merrier!
 
DAY TWO: Lululemon
So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups!
  1. VISUAL: Take a few pictures now (or screenshots) of several things that inspire you! Anything that gives you energy and inspiration to achieve your dreams, goals, desires, etc.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and it inspires me because _____________.
  2. VISUAL: Next, think about anything you've been contemplating doing in your life that you haven't yet done. Take a picture or grab a screenshot of something that represents that desire/goal and tell me what is holding you back from doing it. COMMENT: This is _______________ and it represents my desire to __________. What might be holding me back from doing this is ________________________.
  3. VISUAL: Next, what are a few of your personal passions? You may have touched on these yesterday, but really spell it out for me now. What do you love and get excited about? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.
  4. VISUAL: Show me several screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of athleisure you buy. Where do you discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below:
    COMMENT: This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.
  5. VISUAL: Take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? COMMENT: FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how?
  6. VISUAL: Screenshot something that represents the Lululemon brand. Could be a storefront or the logo. COMMENT: What are three juicy adjectives that come to mind when you see this brand or hear it mentioned? Why?
  1. VISUAL: Choose a screenshot that stands for what the Lululemon brand represents to you. COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? How does Lululemon live alongside other athleisure brands in your heart and mind? For ex, if Nike, Lululemon, Under Armor, Reebok and any other athleisure brands in your consideration set were all at a party, how would they all interact? (What would they drive to the party, show up wearing, choose to drink, want to dance to, hang out with... what energy would they bring? etc). Please have fun with this question. J
  2. VISUAL: Take a screenshot of something that represents what keeps you from feeling more loyal towards Lululemon and shopping the brand more often. COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? What would the brand need to do for you to become more enthused about buying it more frequently?
PERSONAL VIDEO
Your final task before completion will be to ask a friend or family member to record you talking about a specific subject that your moderator will choose, based on your two-day dialogue. It will probably be one of your areas of interest/passions. Stay tuned! This does not need to feel produced or rehearsed – we just want you to speak honestly from the heart, “off the cuff”, so to speak. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: Participants
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LOOKLOOK Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK screen. The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how people feel at work. In other words, we want to find out what types of physical things can boost your motivation, inspire your creativity, and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable. Food, coffee, dry cleaning, a place to collect packages, etc. We’re looking to find out what really matters to people, and perhaps some ideas that haven’t been done before! Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below – and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me. Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them. I’ll be responding to most of your comments, and answering these follow-up questions should about an additional hour (probably less) and you can complete them in the evening when you are home from work if that is easier. PLEASE NOTE: We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – ie for 1s, 1b, etc. Generally speaking, the more pictures the better!
In this study, it’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE
QUESTIONS BELOW, PLEASEJ
THE QUESTIONS:
  1. 1)  DAY IN THE LIFE
    1. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute...? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
    2. Next, show me a picture that describes your workspace. In the comment space, tell me three adjectives that describe the rhythm of a typical workday.
    3. If you think about your current workplace, what are some of your favorite amenities – or things that are offered to employees there?
    4. Is there anything special about your workplace compared to other workplaces in your city? Give us as much detail as possible!
    5. What three words would you use to describe the unique culture at your company?
  2. 2)  Next, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work. How many places to eat exist? (ie full-sized cafeterias, snacks and vending, cafes, convenience stores? Please take a picture of any place food or drinks are offered. For each one, what do you like about it, and tell me what – if anything – you would change about it!
  3. 3)  Next, we want to see your cafe/cafeteria(s)! Take a trip down there and capture pictures of what is offered – especially the parts that are your favorite and your least favorite. For each of the questions below, take a picture that brings to life the question you are answering:
    1. What could be improved? What do you wish was offered that currently is not available?
    2. How could they improve the atmosphere of the cafe/cafeteria?
    3. Does your workplace offer healthy options? If so, what do they look like? Could they be improved in any way?
    4. Is the food service making use of technology to keep things customized and efficient? What else could they do to improve on that front (for example, a mobile app for pre-ordering that earns you loyalty points)?
    5. How innovative is the food and drink offering – overall? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative? We want to hear your suggestions!
  4. 4)  This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work.
a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please visit the place near work where you go most often when not eating at work, and take a picture to accompany your answer to each of the following:
  1. What is the name of this place?
  2. What do you like about this place? What do they offer that you enjoy?
  3. How often do you visit? Do you come alone or with colleagues?
  4. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details.
 
b. Now, think about where you live – please take some screen grabs of places you like to go out to eat near your home. With the picture for each one, please answer the following questions:
  1. What do you like about this place?
  2. How often do you visit?
  3. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details.
5) The final part is about some pie-in-the-sky dreaming. What could your work offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, snacks, restaurants, bars, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could an employer possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS I’ll ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of my follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating! Have fun!

study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY:  Smartphones in Your Daily LIfe

Study Instructions

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study!  Together we’ll be discussing how smartphones help us in daily life, and where perhaps they could do a better job of it, as machine learning can potentially improve your experience.

  

DAY ONE:  “How You, Your Smartphone and Your Apps Get Stuff Done” will take about an hour and a half over the course of the day for you to give us a show and tell of your daily rhythm.  Your moderator will ask you some follow up questions throughout the day.

 

DAY TWO:  “Machine Learning & Your Smartphone” will take about an hour.  We will have more of an active dialogue, getting your top of mind thoughts about what artificial intelligence even means, and brainstorming a little on how your smartphone could become more intuitive to your needs to be more useful.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you to complete. For each question, please upload a relevant photo along with your response. We're just looking for your honest opinions so just give us the straight talk – it’s not a survey, it’s a conversation!  When your moderator has responded to a conversation thread, you’ll see a blue dot on the thumbnail of that post so you’ll know which ones to respond to!

 

THE TASKS

 

PREAMBLE: (To be completed prior to the study):

 

  1. Please upload a quick selfie so we can put a face to the name!

  2. Upload a screenshot of your current smartphone, and tell me what make and model it is.  In the comment section, tell me why you’re in the market for a new phone!  Is it just the lust for a particular new gadget or is something wrong with your current phone,  etc.?

  3. Take a screenshot of your homescreen, and tell us what apps are some of your most frequently used and why!

 

DAY ONE:  “How You, Your Smartphone and Your Apps Get Stuff Done”

 

Welcome to Day One! Today, we want to see how you use your smartphone to be productive, helping you throughout the day.  There are so many tools out there these days (digital and analog) and everyone has their own things they rely on to try to stay organized, informed and connected…   we want to see what this looks like for you.  

 

Today, you will be journaling all the ways you work with data in your daily life that helps everything run smoothly (or, at least, run…)

 

Send us pictures and screen grabs of everything you’re doing today, whether it’s managing a to-do list, texting or connecting with friends with friends, checking your FitBit, Skyping, setting up a calendar invite, searching on Google or on a social media platform, ordering an Uber, getting directions, shopping on Alexa or Google Home... we want to see it all!

 

With every screenshot you post, please tell us:

 

  1. What you’re doing

  2. What app you’re using (individually, or any pairs of apps you’re using together)

  3. Any frustrations with the task at hand (or anything that’s working unexpectedly well!)

 

If you use any resources other than your smartphone to help you get information or get things done today, we want to hear about that too.  Maybe you use an app like Slack or Trello on your laptop to coordinate projects?  Or Dropbox to organize your files?  Maybe you carry an analog organizer?  These are the kinds of things we’re interested in.

 

DAY TWO:  “A.I., Machine Learning & Your Smartphone”

 

So today we’re going to delve into the hot topic of machine learning and artificial intelligence.  

 

VISUAL ONE:

Please find a screenshot of an image or picture that represents whatever comes to mind when you think of the concept of artificial intelligence and machine learning.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

  • What visual did you select?  Why did you choose this to represent artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • What three adjectives pop into your head when you hear the terms artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • What parts of your life are you aware of that have been made better or worse by artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • Is there a difference between artificial intelligence and machine learning in your mind? If so, how would you explain the difference?

  • Are there any smartphone manufacturers talking about artificial intelligence or machine learning? If so, who are they and what have you heard? 

  • If your smartphone could get to know your needs and help you do things in the most useful and intuitive way, what would you hope it could do?

  • When it comes to your phone understanding you better and adapting to your specific needs, what excites you? What would you expect it could help with? ...and what potentially scares you (if anything)?

 

VISUAL TWO:

THE ALL-IMPORTANT BATTERY:  

Please select a screengrab of something that represents how you feel when you know your battery is starting to run low, and might not stay powered for the entire time you need it.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

  • What visual did you select?  Why did you choose this?

  • What terms do you use to describe your phone’s battery?  

  • How do you think about your battery life and your battery usage?

  • What sort of expectations do you have for how long your battery lasts?

  • Have you ever used something like a battery pack, a replaceable battery, or carried your charger with you because you knew you wouldn’t get through the day? If so, how often did you do this? What made you think you wouldn’t make it through the day?

  • What sort of things come to mind when you think about battery usage?  For example, individual app usage, screen brightness, etc?  What do you feel drains your battery, and why?

  • Do you make any trade-offs or sacrifices in how you use your phone in order to save battery?

  • Is battery performance a consideration when it comes to shopping for your new smartphone?  Why or why not?  

 

VISUAL THREE:

Upload an image that represents how you might research the battery performance of a future potential smartphone.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

name: Atlanta Participants
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY:  Smartphones in Your Daily LIfe

Study Instructions

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study!  Together we’ll be discussing how smartphones help us in daily life, and where perhaps they could do a better job of it, as machine learning can potentially improve your experience.

  

DAY ONE:  “How You, Your Smartphone and Your Apps Get Stuff Done” will take about an hour and a half over the course of the day for you to give us a show and tell of your daily rhythm.  Your moderator will ask you some follow up questions throughout the day.

 

DAY TWO:  “Machine Learning & Your Smartphone” will take about an hour.  We will have more of an active dialogue, getting your top of mind thoughts about what artificial intelligence even means, and brainstorming a little on how your smartphone could become more intuitive to your needs to be more useful.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you to complete. For each question, please upload a relevant photo along with your response. We're just looking for your honest opinions so just give us the straight talk – it’s not a survey, it’s a conversation!  When your moderator has responded to a conversation thread, you’ll see a blue dot on the thumbnail of that post so you’ll know which ones to respond to!

 

THE TASKS

 

PREAMBLE: (To be completed prior to the study):

 

  1. Please upload a quick selfie so we can put a face to the name!

  2. Upload a screenshot of your current smartphone, and tell me what make and model it is.  In the comment section, tell me why you’re in the market for a new phone!  Is it just the lust for a particular new gadget or is something wrong with your current phone,  etc.?

  3. Take a screenshot of your homescreen, and tell us what apps are some of your most frequently used and why!

 

DAY ONE:  “How You, Your Smartphone and Your Apps Get Stuff Done”

 

Welcome to Day One! Today, we want to see how you use your smartphone to be productive, helping you throughout the day.  There are so many tools out there these days (digital and analog) and everyone has their own things they rely on to try to stay organized, informed and connected…   we want to see what this looks like for you.  

 

Today, you will be journaling all the ways you work with data in your daily life that helps everything run smoothly (or, at least, run…)

 

Send us pictures and screen grabs of everything you’re doing today, whether it’s managing a to-do list, texting or connecting with friends with friends, checking your FitBit, Skyping, setting up a calendar invite, searching on Google or on a social media platform, ordering an Uber, getting directions, shopping on Alexa or Google Home... we want to see it all!

 

With every screenshot you post, please tell us:

 

  1. What you’re doing

  2. What app you’re using (individually, or any pairs of apps you’re using together)

  3. Any frustrations with the task at hand (or anything that’s working unexpectedly well!)

 

If you use any resources other than your smartphone to help you get information or get things done today, we want to hear about that too.  Maybe you use an app like Slack or Trello on your laptop to coordinate projects?  Or Dropbox to organize your files?  Maybe you carry an analog organizer?  These are the kinds of things we’re interested in.

 

DAY TWO:  “A.I., Machine Learning & Your Smartphone”

 

So today we’re going to delve into the hot topic of machine learning and artificial intelligence.  

 

VISUAL ONE:

Please find a screenshot of an image or picture that represents whatever comes to mind when you think of the concept of artificial intelligence and machine learning.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

  • What visual did you select?  Why did you choose this to represent artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • What three adjectives pop into your head when you hear the terms artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • What parts of your life are you aware of that have been made better or worse by artificial intelligence and machine learning?

  • Is there a difference between artificial intelligence and machine learning in your mind? If so, how would you explain the difference?

  • Are there any smartphone manufacturers talking about artificial intelligence or machine learning? If so, who are they and what have you heard? 

  • If your smartphone could get to know your needs and help you do things in the most useful and intuitive way, what would you hope it could do?

  • When it comes to your phone understanding you better and adapting to your specific needs, what excites you? What would you expect it could help with? ...and what potentially scares you (if anything)?

 

VISUAL TWO:

THE ALL-IMPORTANT BATTERY:  

Please select a screengrab of something that represents how you feel when you know your battery is starting to run low, and might not stay powered for the entire time you need it.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

  • What visual did you select?  Why did you choose this?

  • What terms do you use to describe your phone’s battery?  

  • How do you think about your battery life and your battery usage?

  • What sort of expectations do you have for how long your battery lasts?

  • Have you ever used something like a battery pack, a replaceable battery, or carried your charger with you because you knew you wouldn’t get through the day? If so, how often did you do this? What made you think you wouldn’t make it through the day?

  • What sort of things come to mind when you think about battery usage?  For example, individual app usage, screen brightness, etc?  What do you feel drains your battery, and why?

  • Do you make any trade-offs or sacrifices in how you use your phone in order to save battery?

  • Is battery performance a consideration when it comes to shopping for your new smartphone?  Why or why not?  

 

VISUAL THREE:

Upload an image that represents how you might research the battery performance of a future potential smartphone.

 

In the comment section, please answer the following:

You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. Please be open, honest, and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! 

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing usthe options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in themoment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty ofLookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and uploadthem later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARECONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore adifferent aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo,screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the correspondingquestions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment issaved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond toyour posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderatorhas responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surroundinga topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that isoutlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New ModeratorComments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, themoderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be completewhen all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of thisstudy! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documentingeverything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ONTHE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast.Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in thephotos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially badfood), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and badlogistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will bedoing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK® Campus Life and Food Study! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm

your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment

and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK® screen.

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus – showing us the options you have

available to you and the choices you make!

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and

answer them! Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see

where you are on campus (or off!) and what you are eating! With EACH of those posts,

please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS! You’re getting paid for your thoughtful opinions! J

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your

experiences. That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera

roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE

CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Tuesday, January 22nd.

Please complete Part II on Wednesday, January 23rd. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING,

at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee. We want to see what you eat and drink ALL DAY

LONG, and we want to see the facilities that are available to you.

Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday, January 23rd.

PART I

YOU

1. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the

relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b. What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience? Health? Quality of the

food? Ability to personalize it?

2. Describe (through a few pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like. Please

comment on the following: How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs.

hanging out with friends?

YOUR SCHOOL

3. Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at your school. What three

adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture at your school? What adjectives would

you use to describe the student body? What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4. Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus. This can include

anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe

what you are sharing and what you get out of it. How can it be improved? We want details here,

down to the condiments you prefer for your tea or coffee.

5. Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience

at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6. Take pictures of any branded franchises that exist on your campus today (i.e., coffee shops, fast

food etc) and tell me if you ever frequent them, and why or why not. Are there others you’d be

delighted to see? If so, upload screenshots of them and tell me what you would like about

adding them!

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

7. Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you

most often visit. For each, please answer: when do you tend to go here? How often? Why do

you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often

would you say you go off campus to eat or drink?

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL

We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your

campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go

about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture

of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the

context. Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

8. What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or

with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).

9. What are you eating?

10. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?

11. What details are important – how is the QUALITY? HEALTHINESS? CONVENIENCE FACTOR?

PERSONALIZATION FACTOR? What was great – or what could be better?

PIE IN THE SKY

12. What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when

it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks,

restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these

ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would

improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on

your wish list?

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the

food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally

expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only.

Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and

your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up

questions. Thanks so much for participating!

Gen Z Fashion
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on fashion and your lifestyle in the 21st century! Virtual fashion is a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of this concept these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by end of day Saturday August 21st. Starting on an assigned day around August 23-26, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: US
Parents & Students 6-10
Sophomore
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!

 

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

 

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'

 

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! We want to see REAL LIFE - the good, the bad and the ugly. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!
