name: Prime Prospects
study_instructions: This study is designed to better understand the opportunities and challenges involved in a woman's life who is responsible for making a home "sing". We'll be curious about your tastes and preferences, and how you make choices about where to shop to stock up on necessities not just for you but others in the home!

name: Gen X
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study on how you make movie choices, and where the movies fit into your overall world of entertainment! 
 
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of where and how movies fit into your life. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Be sure to press SEND after entering your comments!
 
You will not receive notifications on your phone when your moderator starts sending you follow-ups, but you will see that a topic circle turns orange if they have engaged on that topic. You will see their comments marked with an orange symbol: "moderator comment". Your moderator will continue to ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
 
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty! Have fun!

name: Freshman
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! 

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing usthe options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in themoment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty ofLookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and uploadthem later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARECONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore adifferent aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo,screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the correspondingquestions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment issaved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond toyour posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderatorhas responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surroundinga topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that isoutlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New ModeratorComments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, themoderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be completewhen all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of thisstudy! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documentingeverything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ONTHE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast.Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially badfood), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and badlogistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will bedoing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Current Guests
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOKTM STUDY: Athleisure & Life INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-LookTM study on the role that athleisure plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you buy nice-quality athleisure but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and passions. If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-LookTM, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does it mean for you to live a balanced life, and how do you make quality choices in today’s busy world? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. DAY ONE: A Day in Your Life
Today, I want to understand what it’s like to be you. We’d like you to document your day with visuals and send us comments on what you are doing and how you’re feeling at key points of your day. Before we get started with that, let’s start with a few questions specific to athleisure – then we’ll get on with documenting your day! VISUAL: Take a picture of a few of your favorite and most often-worn pieces of athleisure, whether it’s a jacket, shorts, pants, tank, warm-up, etc.
COMMENT: FOR EACH, tell me the following: (i) What draws you to wearing this? (ii) Where and why did you buy it? VISUAL: Take a screenshot of the stores/sites where you buy most of your athleisure. COMMENT: FOR EACH, (i) What do you count on from this store/website? What kind of athleisure do you buy here and why?   Thank you! Now let’s get started with “A Day in My Life!” Below are a few prompts to get you started.
VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever you see when you wake up in the morning. COMMENT: What’s going through my head right now is ____________________. VISUAL: Take a few shots of your morning ritual(s). From getting ready to morning coffee, what is the rhythm of your morning? Show me.
COMMENT: Here, I’m [doing]_____________________. Feeling _____________. As you progress through your day, we’re not just interested in what you’re doing but how you’re feeling – when are you feeling good... and when are you stressed... bored, etc. Activities to document can include: work, running around, shopping, errands, spiritual practices, exercise, sports, relaxing, watching TV, listening to music, having fun with friends or family, going out, entertainment, reading/other media, taking care of a pet or loved one... really, anything that normally falls into place during a given weekday/evening. By the way, we know you’re on your phone during the day and we want to understand that too! What do you spend time on your phone doing most often – group chats? Insta/FB/Snapchat/YouTube? Games? Shopping? Fantasy football? Please send me screenshots of your phone activity. REALLY IMPORTANT: With each post, tell me something in the spirit of “This is me, [doing] _________. I’m feeling ________ because ____________.” I will respond with follow up questions in the evening, so look for the notifications that take you to my questions, either that night or first thing in the morning before we get started with Day 2. Any post with a blue dot signals there’s something from me to respond to. This will be different for everyone, but I’m expecting to see a minimum of 20 posts throughout your day and evening - but we love photos, so the more the merrier!
DAY TWO: Lululemon
So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups!
  1. VISUAL: Take a few pictures now (or screenshots) of several things that inspire you! Anything that gives you energy and inspiration to achieve your dreams, goals, desires, etc.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and it inspires me because _____________.
  2. VISUAL: Next, think about anything you've been contemplating doing in your life that you haven't yet done. Take a picture or grab a screenshot of something that represents that desire/goal and tell me what is holding you back from doing it. COMMENT: This is _______________ and it represents my desire to __________. What might be holding me back from doing this is ________________________.
  3. VISUAL: Next, what are a few of your personal passions? You may have touched on these yesterday, but really spell it out for me now. What do you love and get excited about? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
    COMMENT: This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.
  4. VISUAL: Show me several screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of athleisure you buy. Where do you discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below:
    COMMENT: This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.
  5. VISUAL: Take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? COMMENT: FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how?
  6. VISUAL: Screenshot something that represents the Lululemon brand. Could be a storefront or the logo. COMMENT: What are three juicy adjectives that come to mind when you see this brand or hear it mentioned? Why?
  1. VISUAL: Choose a screenshot that stands for what the Lululemon brand represents to you. COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? How does Lululemon live alongside other athleisure brands in your heart and mind? For ex, if Nike, Lululemon, Under Armor, Reebok and any other athleisure brands in your consideration set were all at a party, how would they all interact? (What would they drive to the party, show up wearing, choose to drink, want to dance to, hang out with... what energy would they bring? etc). Please have fun with this question. J
  2. VISUAL: Take a screenshot of something that represents the archetype that Lululemon represents to you - eg Sage, Hero, Caregiver, Magician, Parent, Jester, Child, Rebel, Creator, etc... (For example, Amazon Prime might be considered a “hero” archetype because it magically delivers things you need the next day.) COMMENT: Why did you choose this image? Finally, if Lululemon disappeared from the face of the earth tomorrow – what would the world be suddenly missing?
PERSONAL VIDEO
Your final task before completion will be to ask a friend or family member to record you talking about a specific subject that your moderator will choose, based on your two-day dialogue. It will probably be one of your areas of interest/passions. Stay tuned! This does not need to feel produced or rehearsed – we just want you to speak honestly from the heart, “off the cuff”, so to speak. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: Downtown
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: San Francisco
study_instructions: Congratulations on being selected for this important study on what the American Workplace looks like as the country deals with the challenges of reopening post-Covid.The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other aspects of your work environment can boost your motivation and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable as you return to the office post-Covid.Each topic on your LookLook home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)!All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Dave
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Athleisure Discovery

 

INTRODUCTION:

Congratulations on being selected for this study on athleisure’s role in your life and how you explore brands online!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolve” the post. Resolved posts will have a blue check mark on them. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-WORK VIDEO

Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignment during the weekend prior to the study.

 

Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out three (3) of your favorite athleisure and/or activewear items on your bed.

 

Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following: 

 

Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM.  If you want to submit three separate videos, that’s cool.  Or you would rather do the three pieces in one take, that is also fine – but please limit the length of the video to about 2 minutes total.

 

1.     What brand is this? Where did you buy it (if online, please specify)? When did you buy it? And why did you buy it?

2.     Roughly how much of your athleisure/activewear wardrobe is made up of this brand?

3.     What do you do while wearing this piece? (Exercise, lounge, etc). We are super interested in what items you choose for certain workout or non-workout activities!

4.     What product characteristics make this item good for doing that?  (Speak to fit, feel, function, style – whatever is important to you and for that activity!)

5.     Finally, how do you feel when wearing it?

 

DAY ONE:  A DAY IN YOUR LIFE!

 

1.     VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever it is that you see when you wake up!

COMMENT: What are we seeing here?  How are you feeling at this moment about the day ahead? 

 

2.     VISUAL: Take a picture or two of anything that is part of your morning ritual, from coffee to breakfast, to your commute, to meditation or exercise.

COMMENT: How do each of these elements make you feel?  What do you get out of it?

 

3.     VISUAL: Upload a few screenshots – or take pictures – of a few things that represent things that bring you JOY or INSPIRE YOU.

COMMENT:

·       What is this? Why are you passionate about this?

·       What is one goal you have that feels difficult to achieve but you REALLY WANT? What is standing in the way (if anything)?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of your work/studying or other primary activity during the day.

COMMENT:

·       How do you feel at various points of time during the primary part of your day?

·       What are the “pain points” (if any?)

·       What parts do you generally enjoy the most?

 

5.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of the most SOCIAL part of your day.

COMMENT: Who are you interacting with? How do you feel at these times?

 

6.     VISUAL: Think for a minute about the news and content/entertainment that draws you in (we’ll get to social media in a second.) Upload some screenshots that fill me in on the kind of content you enjoy.

COMMENT: What do you enjoy about these choices? What do you think they say about you?

 

7.     VISUAL: Now consider social media: Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn, Reddit, etc. Upload a screenshot or two that tells me which you engage with the most.

COMMENT:

·       For each, describe your way of participating. Do you observe more, or post more?

·       What do you enjoy about each social platform that you’re involved with? How important is it to you?

·       What brands or influencers do you follow on social media, and what do you get out of it?

·       What is your favorite brand to follow? Why? How has this impacted your perception of the brand? Your likelihood to purchase that brand?

 

8.     VISUAL: If you exercise at all regularly, please upload a picture of you doing what you do – i.e. workout, running, a fitness class, etc.

COMMENT:

·       Why do you exercise?

·       How important is exercising to you?

·       What is your favorite way to sweat? How frequently do you do this – and are there any other parts to your fitness repertoire?

·       How do you feel during exercising? Afterwards? Does this vary by activity?

 

9.     VISUAL:  We’re living in an age of technology obsession. Take a picture of any device or app that you are currently enjoying. 

COMMENT: What do you love about this? Do you ever use any tech as part of your fitness routine (apps, wearables, etc)? Why or why not?

 

10.  VISUAL: When evening rolls around, take a picture that tells me what you do for relaxation, or any other kind of evening activity or ritual.

COMMENT: What is it and what do you like about this?

 

11.  VISUAL: As you reflect on the day, what do you wish you could spend MORE time doing (if anything)? Upload a photo or screenshot to represent that.

COMMENT: Finally, if you had all the time in the world, what would you like to spend more time doing? Why?

 

PLEASE NOTE: Feel free to “ad lib” in this Day in the Life section and share additional photos, screenshots and comments about anything that tells me WHAT MAKES YOU YOU!  Food and drink choice posts are also super relevant and interesting here!

 

DAY TWO: LULULEMON & OTHER BRANDS – HOW DO YOU EXPLORE THEM?

 

12.  VISUAL:  Please take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? 

COMMENT:  FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how? 

 

13.  VISUAL: When you hear the lululemon name or see the logo, what comes immediately to mind? Upload a screenshot that represents this (it can be anything – be conceptual and creative!).

COMMENT: To what extend would you agree “lululemon is a brand for me” on a scale of 1-5 (with 5 being the strongest)? Why?

name: Gammas
study_instructions:
Welcome to the Luxury Jewelry and Watches Study!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

You have been chosen for this very selective study because you have great taste, and you buy luxury jewelry. This is not a focus group, although we do want your opinions. But we also want your input on how to revitalize a storied European luxury jewelry and watches brand. Therefore, we refer to this type of project as co-creation. We are looking for your ideas as well as your honest take on some jewelry designs. The voice of this brand should be developed to reach women like you.

We appreciate how busy you all are. In order for the study to be successful, the following questions must be completed and submitted on LOOKLOOK™ prior to the first scheduled day of your participation. Please do ‘Task 1: Selfie Time’ and answer all 4 questions and their subparts.

FIRST TASK: IT’S SELFIE TIME!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

Now, please upload photos of yourself wearing the pieces of jewelry you described to Susan when you spoke. For each of the pictures you have sent, please specify:

o   Was this a gift or did you buy it for yourself?  

o   Where was it purchased?

o   How did you discover this piece? What made you covet it?

THE QUESTIONS

On LOOKLOOK™, you will be prompted where to put these answers.

1.    SHOPPING FOR THE JEWELRY AND WATCH BRANDS YOU LOVE

 

a.    When you purchase jewelry, is it typically for a milestone, a seasonal  purchase, or an impulse buy?

b.   What are 1 or 2 of your favorite luxury jewelry/watch brands, and why?

c.    Do you browse for jewelry in stores or online?

o   If you browse in store, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite stores.

o   If you browse online, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite sites.

d.   When it’s time to purchase jewelry, do you do it in store or online? Or both?

e.    Is it different for watches?

 

2.    TELL ME ABOUT YOUR STYLE

 

a.    What 3  adjectives would you choose to describe your personal style (in general?)

b.   Please also upload 2 or 3 photos that demonstrate how you like to wear jewelry.

o   What rings do you wear?

o   What is your wrist look? Do you like to stack, mix designs, alloys, etc. or do you prefer to match?

o   What earring do you like to wear? Studs, cuffs, drop, etc.?

o   What necklaces do you like to wear? Do you like to layer them or wear one at a time?

o   Do you wear the same jewelry day and night or do you switch for evening?

c.    Do your jewelry pieces serve different needs (ie investment, statement, everyday)? How often do you  make fine jewelry purchases?

d.   List 1 or 2 of your favorite brands outside of jewelry (can be anything!)

 

3.YOUR MEDIA DIET

 

a.    Which of the following media do you use regularly (for anything – in general – not just shopping!)

o   Social media - If yes, what platforms?  

o   Websites - What sites?

o   Print magazines - Which ones? Subscribe or buy occasionally?  

o   Anything else? (Satellite Radio? Podcasts?)

o   TV Shows (Netflix? Cable?)

 

4.    WHAT YOU LOVE

a.    What are you most passionate about in life – other than your family? Take a  screenshot or picture that illustrates 1 or 2 of those interests.

b.   Where do you like to travel? 

c.    What happens to be on your wish list for your next jewelry purchase? Why do you love it? How did it get on your radar?

 

Thank you for completing the questions above! On your scheduled day of participation, your moderator will let you know what brand we are focusing on for the remainder of the study, and will start unveiling the pieces to you for your feedback! You get to take a break from sending us pictures.

At the time, please respond to your moderator’s queries on each specific piece. When you are done, your moderator will send through a bit of the background story on the brand we’re focusing on. Once you’ve read that, you are done with Day One!

name: 2 Bilingual Medium-Heavy Drinker
study_instructions:
We are very excited to have you participate in our research project! As was previously mentioned to you, prior to the online group discussion we would like to get to know you a little bit, and the way we would like to do this is by having you create some brief videos. 

A few things to keep in mind when recording your videos:
• Sometimes it helps to have a friend or family member hold the camera so you can focus on what you are talking about rather than worrying about holding the camera.
• Make sure you or whoever is filming holds the camera as still as possible (no shaking or jarring movements).
• Avoid any background noise or music - this often becomes much louder in the recording.
• Pause for two seconds at the beginning and end of your video to make sure your response isn't cut off at all.
• Before submitting your video(s), watch it to make sure everything looks/sounds okay:  
• Are you facing the right direction? It's easy to accidentally end up with sideways footage if you turn your smartphone while filming, and we want to avoid that happening!
• Is the lighting bright enough so we can see you and what you are recoding?
• Did you speak loud enough so we can clearly hear all that you are saying?

study_instructions: The Global Luxury Collective 에 참여하시게 되신 것을 다시 한번 더 축하 드립니다! 여러분들에 대해 알아갈 수 있는 기회에 시간과 노력을 들여주신 것에 다시 한번 더 감사드립니다. 저희는 플랫폼에서 다루게 될 모든 것들에 대한 여러분의 의견을 정말 기대하고 있습니다! 이번 첫번째 달에는, 여러분이 “럭셔리” 라는 단어를 떠올렸을 때, 가장 먼저 드는 생각과 코로나 이후 “럭셔리란 어떤 것인가?” 대한 생각에 변화가 있으셨다면, 어떤 변화가 있었는지에 대해 알아보고자 합니다. 항상 그랬듯이, 틀린 답은 없습니다- 개개인은 다 다르니까요! 그리고 가장 중요한 점은, 저희는 여러분의 눈을 통해 세상을 보는 것을 중요시 하기 때문에 미디어 업로드를 하실 때 여러분들의 답변을 가장 잘 살릴 수 있는 사진이나 스크린 샷을 업로드 해주시면 감사하겠습니다. 이 스터디는 현실 세계의 디테일을 세부적으로 포착하고자 하는 것을 목표로 합니다. 매달 초에 여러분이 답변 하실 새로운 질문들이 공유될 것이고, 그 주4일 ~ 5일 정도의 기간 이내에 여러분들께서 편하실 때에 답변 해주시면 됩니다.  첫번째로 나가는 이번 질문 세트는 5월4일까지 완료해주시길 바랍니다! 감사합니다.

name: High Value 55+
study_instructions:
LookLook® STUDY:   Fashion | Shopping | Life!

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this LookLook® study on how you shop for fashion today and the role it plays in your life! We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior.  We want to get into the details!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping?

 

Below are the instructions for the study.  Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses.  This is not a survey, it’s a conversation!  Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK:

Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s!  These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe.  It should take about half an hour.

 

GO-TO “LOOKS”

VISUAL:  POST THREE OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS.  We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality.  If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them?  (For ex., one person might have these four: “date night”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out-and-about.” But someone else might have: “client meeting”, “girls’ night”,  “Netflix and Chill”). This is all about your particular life style! Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light.  Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding!  But apparel is the focus of this exercise.

 

COMMENT:  IN EACH POST, tell me the following:  (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who is the designer of each piece and where did you buy? (iii) Where do you typically shop for this type of look? Why?

 

STUDY DAY!  

So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions!  Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment.  Look out for my follow-ups!

 

DISCOVERY AND INSPIRATION

VISUAL:  Post at least three screenshots of places you go online that INSPIRE the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, email from a brand, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.).  Where do you tend to discover new products/styles?  With each one, please complete the comment below:

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “This is ___________.  I go here (insert frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc).  I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”

 

WHY YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Find any image or picture (even an emoji) that represents the feeling that shopping (for apparel and accessories) brings alive in you.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “I chose this image because it represents my feeling of _______________ when I shop for clothes/accessories.” Why do you shop – is it always for replenishment of something you need – or do you shop for fun? At its best, what does a great shopping experience give you?  What really motivates you to make purchases? (ads, promotions, events, Instagram, etc)

 

WHERE YOU SHOP

VISUAL:  Think about the top 3 places where you spend the majority of your apparel dollars.  Post a screenshot of each destination (please list at least 2!)

 

COMMENT (FOR EACH):  Please complete in your own words:  “I tend to buy a lot of my fashion here:  _______________________ because  __________________”.  What percentage of your apparel money goes to this place, and why?

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN THE DIGITAL WORLD!

VIDEO:  Next, you’re going shopping on your phone. Just go browsing for fun. You could look for a specific item or you could just go on a favorite site or to a favorite shopping app to look around and see what you like.

 

We want you to record your screen with audio while you do this (instructions below if you are not familiar with how to do this.)

 

Spend about 1-2 minutes browsing for the item. While you’re browsing, just say out loud what you are thinking.  Tell us where you start your search and voice out loud your comments as you browse. As you click through different options, tell me why you are making your choices of where to go and what to look at. After you record for a few minutes, upload your video to LookLook®. Note: you do not have to be a Ninja at this! Just look around and talk to me while you’re browsing on your phone. If you get frustrated for any reason, mention that!

 

How to screen record on an iPhone (please be sure to turn on audio!)

  1. Go to Settings > Control Center > Customize Controls, then tap next to Screen Recording.
  2. Swipe up from the bottom edge of any screen.
  3. Press the record button firmly until the screen recording box comes up (it takes 3 seconds), turn the microphone on, and then tap Start Recording.
  4. Upload your video to LookLook®

 

How to screen record on an Android phone

5.     Download and use the free app Mobizen

6.     Enable sound before recording

7.     Upload your video to LookLook®

 

HOW YOU SHOP (IN-STORE)

VISUAL:  As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place.  Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. 

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words:  “Services that I enjoy at my favorite apparel/accessories stores include _______________________”.  These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to styling, events, exclusive product lines, delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a local sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.    

 

HOW IT ALL COMES TOGETHER

VISUAL:  Imagine for a moment that someone handed you the luxury of an entire afternoon to go clothing shopping – just for you.  How would you enjoy this gift of time? Would you curl up on the couch and go shopping online? Would you visit boutiques? A mall? Post a screenshot (or a few) of where you would go shopping.

 

COMMENT:  (FOR EACH ONE): Where is this? What do enjoy most about this experience? Provide as much detail as possible!   

 

INTERMIX

 

FAVORITE ITEM:

VISUAL:  Please screenshot an item you have purchased from Intermix in the past two years.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete in your own words:  “This is _______________________ and I bought it ________________ (store/website)”.  In addition, share these details:  What took you to Intermix on that particular occasion? How did you discover the piece?  What role does Intermix play in keeping your clothing repertoire up to date and exciting?

 

WHO IS THE INTERMIX WOMAN?

VISUAL:  Please screenshot a picture that represents, in your mind, the Intermix brand come to life as a woman.  This can be anyone!  Yourself, a celebrity, whatever pops into your head.  Don’t over-think this.

 

COMMENT:  Please complete: “I chose this image because_____________.”  Now imagine a cocktail party where a handful of your favorite apparel retail brands are brought to life as people (you can include retail websites!)  What would each be drinking?  What are they all wearing? Who would be talking to whom?  What are the energies like of these “people”?  Have fun with this and be creative please!

 

 

 

 

INTERMIX – NEXT GENERATION!

VISUAL:  Take a screenshot or picture of any type of experience or benefit that you would like to see Intermix create.

 

COMMENT:  What did you choose, and why? 

 

THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! 

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before you move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Participants
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ Study: Food at Work Instructions for Participants 

Welcome to the LOOK-LOOK™ Study on Food and the Modern Workplace!

 

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing.  Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOK-LOOK™ screen.

 

The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how people feel at work.  In other words, we want to find out what types of physical things can boost your motivation, inspire your creativity, and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable.  You can even think beyond food to dry cleaning, a place to collect packages, coffee and juice bars, etc. We’re looking to find out what really matters to people, perhaps some ideas that no one has done before!

 

Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below – and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me.

 

In this study, it’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE QUESTIONS BELOW, PLEASE J

 

Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them.  I’ll be responding to most of your comments, and answering these follow-up questions should about an additional hour (probably less) and you can complete them in the evening when you are home from work if that is easier.

 

PLEASE NOTE:  We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input.  The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study.

 

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only.

 

Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – ie for 1a, 1b, etc.  Generally speaking, the more pictures the better! 

 

THE QUESTIONS:

 

1)     DAY IN THE LIFE

a.     Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute…? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?

b.     Next, show me a picture that describes your workspace. In the comment space, tell me three adjectives that describe the rhythm of a typical workday. 

c.     If you think about your current workplace, what are some of your favorite amenities – or things that are offered to employees there?

d.     Is there anything special about your workplace compared to other workplaces in your city?  Give us as much detail as possible!

e.     What three words would you use to describe the unique culture at your company?

 

2)     Next, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work. Where do you go to get them?  (ie full-sized cafes, vending, coffee shops, convenience stores?) Please take a picture of any place snacks are offered.  For each one, what do you like about it, and tell me what – if anything – you would change about it!

 

3)     Next, we want to see your cafe/cafeteria(s)! Take a trip to the spot you usually frequent and show us the parts that are your favorite and your least favorite.  For each of the questions below, take a picture that brings to life the question you are answering:

a.     How could the quality be improved? Are there items you wish were offered that currently are not available?

b.     How could they improve the atmosphere of the cafe/cafeteria?

c.     Does your workplace offer healthy options? If so, what do they look like?  Could they be improved in any way?

d.     Is the food service making use of technology to keep things convenient and efficient?  What else could they do to improve on that front?

e.     Are you able to personalize your food to the extent that you wish?  Are there specific ways they could be more innovative?  We want to hear your suggestions!

 

4)     This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work.

a.     Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work.  Please visit the place near work where you go most often when not eating at work, and take a picture to accompany your answer to each of the following:

                                               i.     What is the name of this place?

                                              ii.     What do you like about this place?  What do they offer that you enjoy?

                                             iii.     How often do you visit?  Do you come alone or with colleagues?

name: Students 15-18
40-55 Women
study_instructions:
PARTICIPANT INSTRUCTIONS

 

Welcome to the Luxury Skin Care Product Study.

 

You've been selected for this particular study because you are well-versed in luxury and you are passionate about luxury skin care products.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you complete.  We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun and we can't wait to see what you show us!

 

We estimate that answering the questions, taking the pictures and recording the video will take a total of two and a half hours to complete (we’ve put time estimates in for each section but don’t feel limited by these!) Two hours for the tasks, and an additional half and hour to respond to follow-up questions throughout.

 

You can work through the study at your leisure – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along.

 

If you can finish by Wednesday November 9th it would be fantastic, but it you need a little more time, just let us know.

 

THE TASKS

 

FIRST, show me the luxury skin care products you are most loyal to, and tell me why. You may have two, you may have ten – everyone prioritizes differently.  We do not need to see your makeup choices – just skin care. Photograph each item that is currently part of your routine and tell us what motivated you to try it.  Is it a favorite or something new that you're trying?  What role does brand and product loyalty play when it comes to your skin care routine?  Do friends, word of mouth, or recommendations from aestheticians or dermatologists play a role at all in what you use?

(time estimate: 10 minutes)

 

SECOND, let’s discuss what influences your choices. Please answer these seven questions:

  1. How do you find out about the latest products, trends and innovations?  Show me through pictures and be as specific as possible.  If it’s blogs or vlogs, take screen shots.  If it’s through magazines (online or print), show me that.  Perhaps it’s through websites or by shopping in stores?  Do you typically have to sample a product before trying it?  Whatever counts for you, show me visually and explain in your comments WHY those things have the most influence for you.
  2. How often (if at all) do you visit a dermatologist or an aesthetician?  What services are you regularly receiving?  How do these influence your choices of product (if at all)?
  3. Where do you prefer to shop for luxury skin care - department stores, online, Sephora, boutiques?  Take screen grab of the type of environment that is most compelling for you.  Do you prefer an open environment/self-service model like Sephora or having interaction with sales associates/experts in a department store?  Why? Can the sales associate’s opinions and knowledge get you to try new things or convert from other brands?  Tell me about it.
  4. Do points or loyalty programs play a role in where you shop and if so, what do you desire in return?  How important are promotions or gift with purchase?  Product samples?  When you really think about it, what really drives your loyalty to a shopping environment, and to specific luxury skin care products?
  5. When you shop for luxury skincare, do you typically narrow down a brand's offering by shopping for a specific type of product (i.e. cream, serum, eye cream) or is it more by benefit – ie anti-aging, brightening, hydration, etc.)?
  6. When it comes to price, is there a threshold on what you will spend for a product to which you are loyal?  Is there a certain category that you are willing to invest more in than others?
  7. How important is product exclusivity – ie items that are exclusively available at one retailer?  Does that add to a sense of discovery or loyalty to that store?  How important is a sense of discovery when it comes to luxury skin care products?

(time estimate: 20 minutes)

 

THIRD, you're going shopping.  Choose an actual store where you really love to browse for luxury skin care products.  We realize that you may shop online for some products but we'd like to start in an actual store.

 

Please wander as you normally would and stop wherever you are interested.  Take pictures of whatever catches your eye, and describe why it got your attention. We are really curious about what draws you in – ie the display, the brand name, beautiful packaging, a friendly salesperson (if there is one), etc.  If you find a product that you're seriously coveting, please photograph and then define – why do you desire it?

(time estimate:  1 hour)

 

FOURTH, we’re going to talk about shopping online. Please take screen grabs of where you shop for luxury skin care products online, if you do.  Please send screen shots of all online stores that are in your repertoire, and describe what you typically buy there and why – even if it’s only occasional.

(time estimate:  15 minutes)

 

FINALLY, please have someone record you speaking to us on the following subject.  The video should be about a minute in length.  Think about it first, then use the video to tell us:  if you had your own luxury skin care store or luxury skin care website, what would be your best in class practices?  Describe what the experience would be like for the customer If you are in a store, what services are you receiving?  If you are online, how are you delivering a sense of luxury?  What is most important in this luxury skin care shopping experience?

(time estimate: 15 minutes)

study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!

 

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

 

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'

 

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! We want to see REAL LIFE - the good, the bad and the ugly. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Participants
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOKTM Study: Food at Work Instructions for Participants Welcome to the LOOK-LOOKTM Study on Food and the Modern Workplace!
The purpose of this study is to understand the role of food and drink in your everyday workday routine! The first step is to download the LOOK-LOOKTM app from iTunes or Google Play. Search “LookLook Spark” and you will find it. It’s free, and you just want to accept the terms and notifications, and you’re good to go. Next, log on with your email and the password: “hello” (ALL LOWERCASE.) Please post a selfie yet to confirm your participation. With LOOK-LOOKTM every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your screen. Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below – and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me. What we’re really trying to get at is how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how people feel at work. In other words, we want to find out what types of physical things can boost your motivation, inspire your creativity, and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable. It’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE QUESTIONS BELOW, PLEASE J Completing the tasks should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them. If your workplace has strong firewalls/iffy WiFi, it will make sense to simply take the pictures prior to the day of the study, save to camera roll, and then upload them with your comments when you are in a place with strong WiFi, perhaps after work in the evening. I’ll be responding to most of your comments and answering these follow-up questions should about an additional half hour. PLEASE NOTE: We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – ie for 1a, 1b, etc. Generally speaking, the more pictures the better!
THE QUESTIONS:
  1. 1)  DAY IN YOUR LIFE
    1. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute...? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
    2. If you think about your current workplace, what are some of your favorite amenities – or things that are offered to employees there?
    3. Is there anything special about your workplace compared to other workplaces in your city? Give us as much detail as possible!
    4. What three words would you use to describe the unique culture at your company?
  2. 2)  Next, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work. How many places to eat exist? (ie full-sized cafeterias, snacks and vending, cafes, convenience stores? With every image that you share, what do you like about it, and tell me what – if anything – you would change about it!
  3. 3)  Next, we want to see your cafe/cafeteria(s)! Take a trip down there and capture pictures of what is offered – especially the parts that are your favorite and your least favorite. For each of the questions below, take a picture that brings to life the question you are answering:
    1. What could be improved? What do you wish was offered that currently is not available?
    2. How could they improve the atmosphere of the cafe/cafeteria?
    3. Does your workplace offer healthy options? If so, what do they look like? What else might you enjoy from a “wellness” perspective?
    4. Is the food service making use of technology to keep things customized and efficient? What else could they do to improve on that front (for example, a mobile app for pre-ordering that earns you loyalty points)?
    5. How innovative is the food and drink offering – overall? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative? We want to hear your suggestions!
  4. 4)  This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work.
    1. Think about the options that exist in the neighborhood around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please visit the place near work where you go most often when not eating at work, and take a picture to accompany your answer to each of the following:
      1. What is the name of this place?
      2. What do you like about this place? What do they offer that you enjoy?
      3. How often do you visit? Do you come alone or with colleagues?
      4. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details.
    2. Now, think about where you live – please take some screen grabs of places you like to go out to eat near your home. With the picture for each one, please answer the following questions:
      1. What do you like about this place?
      2. How often do you visit?
      3. What adjectives describe this place? By “ambience” I mean environment and décor... the details.
  5. 5)  Now, some pie-in-the-sky dreaming. What could your work offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink (or other amenities) fueling your day? This could be new cafes, snacks, restaurants, bars, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could an employer possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?
Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS I’ll ask you about your comments and your pictures.

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® Study: Campus Life and Food!

 

Part I:  Complete by Monday 9 pm, February 18th

Part II:  Complete on Tuesday 5 pm, February 19th

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK® Campus Life and Food Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK® screen.

This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus.

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them!  Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where and what you are eating!  With EACH of those posts, please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS!  You’re getting paid for your thoughtful opinions! J

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

Please complete Part I by 9 pm on Monday February 18th

Please complete Part II on Tuesday February 19th, PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee.

 Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Tuesday February 19th.

PART I

YOU

1.     FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a.     How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b.     What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience?  Health?  Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?

 

2.     Describe (through a few pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  Please comment on the following:  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends?

YOUR SCHOOL

3.     Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at your school.  What three adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture at your school? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body?  What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4.     Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus.  This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it. How can it be improved?  We want details here, down to the condiments you prefer for your tea or coffee. 

5.     Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6.     Take pictures of any branded franchises that exist on your campus today (i.e., coffee shops, fast food etc) and tell me if you ever frequent them, and why or why not.  Are there others you’d be delighted to see? If so, upload screenshots of them and tell me what you would like about adding them! 

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

7.     Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit.  For each, please answer:  when do you tend to go here?  How often?  Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? 

FOOD JOURNAL (A) (DINNER, LATE NIGHT SNACKS)

In an effort to make tomorrow’s food journal a little easier to navigate we ask that you make your dinner post tonight. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Tonight, when you eat dinner, please snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context.  Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

8.What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).

9.What are you eating?

10. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?

11.  What details are important – how is the QUALITY?  HEALTHINESS?  CONVENIENCE FACTOR?  PERSONALIZATION FACTOR?  What was great – or what could be better?

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL (B) (BREAKFAST, LUNCH, SNACKS – THROUGH LATE AFTERNOON)

Today’s food journal will follow the same format as food journal (A) and should include your first meal or beverage of the day, coffee (if you drink it), any snacks or refreshments you have throughout the morning, your lunch, and any afternoon snacks. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that.  It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context.  Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

12.  What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).

13.  What are you eating?

14.  Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?

15.  What details are important – how is the QUALITY?  HEALTHINESS?  CONVENIENCE FACTOR?  PERSONALIZATION FACTOR?  What was great – or what could be better?

Once you’ve made your last afternoon snacks post you can continue on to PIE IN THE SKY.

PIE IN THE SKY

16.  What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. 

Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions.

name: Gen Z
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study! We are excited to learn from you over the next few days as you reflect on how you shop for things that are necessary (or just fun). In particular, we’re looking to understand how Covid has shifted some of your preferences and behavior, and what you think you might want from shopping experiences in the future! We’ve organized these into a few modules to be completed over a week. Each “day” is a different topic that explores various aspects of shopping. For each question throughout the study, please upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Visual details are super important in this one)!Please complete all questions by the end of Sunday night and look for follow ups on Monday and Tuesday. Have fun!

name: Grad Students
study_instructions:
Welcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study! In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!

 

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

 

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit 'send' so your comment is saved before your move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'

 

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! We want to see REAL LIFE - the good, the bad and the ugly. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Sophomores
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Chinese Participants
study_instructions: 再次恭喜您被选为“全球奢华调研团”的一员！也感谢您愿意让我们更为深入地了解您；我们很高兴能倾听您的意见和看法。在这次首月的调研中，我们希望了解您对奢侈品的看法，以及疫情如何影响您对奢侈品的感觉和看法。在这里没有所谓的标准答案–因为每个人都是与众不同的！-我们欢迎您尽情分享图片和截图，让您的回答更生动直观，也便于我们通过您的双眼发现更多。本调研的所有内容都是关于捕捉现实生活中的微妙细节。之后每个月初，都会有一系列新问题需要您的回答，您会有4-5天的时间来回答这些问题。对于第一次问答，请在5月4日（周二）之前完成！谢谢- 祝您答题愉快！

name: San Antonio (Control)
Freshman
Non-Users
study_instructions:
STUDY INSTRUCTIONS

Welcome to the Skin Care Study.

 You've been selected for this particular study because you are loyal to a skin care brand.

 Below are the tasks that we need you complete.  We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun and we can't wait to see what you show us!

We estimate that answering the questions, taking the pictures and recording the video will take a total of two and a half hours to complete -  two hours for the tasks, and an additional half an hour to respond to follow-up questions throughout.

You can work through the study at your leisure – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along.

 

THE TASKS

 

DAY ONE

 

FIRST, show me the skin care products you are most loyal to, and tell me why. You may have two, you may have ten – everyone prioritizes differently.  We do not need to see your makeup choices – just skin care. Photograph each item that is currently part of your routine and for each item, answer the following:

1.     Is it a favorite or something new that you're trying?  

2.     How long have you been using it?

3.     Is it a product you’re loyal to – and if so, why?

4.     What do you want from the product, and how is it performing for you?

 

SECOND, let’s focus on cleansers and moisturizers specifically for a minute.

1.     Are you more interested in a cleanser that prevents problems, or one that fixes problems?

2.     Are you more interested in a moisturizer that prevents problems, or one that fixes problems?

3.     Do gentle cleansers clean well?

 

THIRD, let’s talk conceptually about how you feel about your skin on a daily basis. 

6.     What does “skin health” mean to you?

7.     If you were to talk to your face in the morning – what would you say to your skin?

8.     If you were to talk to your face at night, what would you say to your skin?

 

FINALLY, let’s discuss what influences your choices.

9.     Do you like to discover new skin care products, trends and innovations?  Or do you typically like to stick with familiar favorites?

10.  If you do like to check out new products, show me through pictures and be as specific as possible.  If it’s blogs or vlogs, take screen shots.  If it’s through magazines (online or print), show me that.  Perhaps it’s through websites or by shopping in stores?  Take screen shots to show me.

 

DAY TWO

 

Today, you're going shopping!  Choose a drug, mass merchandiser or grocery store where you typically buy skin care products.  We realize that you may shop online for some products but we'd like to start in an actual store.

 

Please wander as you normally would and stop wherever you are interested.  Take pictures of whatever catches your eye, and describe why it got your attention. For each product, answer these questions:

 

1.     Are you finding any brands you might consider trying? If so, why - what stands out about those brands?

2.     We are really curious about what draws you in – ie the display, the brand name, packaging, any messaging on that packaging, etc.  If you do find a product that you're tempted to try, please photograph and then define – why does it appeal to you?

 

Next, find the section with Cetaphil products. Take a photo of the Cetaphil products and answer the following questions:

 

3.     Just based on appearance, how would you compare Cetaphil with the other brands on the shelf?

4.     What three descriptive adjectives come to mind when you see the Cetaphil products? 

5.     Cetaphil has been around for 70 years.  What do you think has prevented you from trying it?

6.     Are there any Cetaphil-branded products catching your eye on-shelf?  If so, please photograph and tell me what is interesting about them!

 

FINALLY, please have someone record you while you create 2 separate videos for us. Each should be roughly a minute in length.  Think about your answers to the questions first, then answer the following questions:

 

VIDEO ONE

·      What makes a good skin day?

·      Is your skin your friend, or your enemy?

·      If facial cleansers/moisturizers didn’t exist, how would your life change?

·      How do you show your skin you care, and keep it out of trouble?

·      Please read this and finish it in your own words:  “I would try Cetaphil if……”

 

VIDEO TWO

·      Now, sell me your favorite skincare brand as if I were your friend – what would you say to get me to persuade me to try it?  In making this argument, please start with this phrase: “The reason I love [my favorite skincare] brand is…….” then make your case!

 

 

Thank you for your participation!  You are complete when you have answered all of our follow-up questions.

name: Japanese Participants
study_instructions: 先月は、ハンドバッグについて、皆様からのご意見を頂戴しました。皆様の素晴らしいデザインと細部へのこだわりが伝わってきました。また、画面録画は、商品を見ているときに何が心に響くのかを判断する重要な材料であり、ご協力いただき改めて感謝いたします。 今月は、まったく別のテーマで皆様にご協力いただきたいと思います。ラグジュアリーブランドが、商品のインテグリティ（誠実さ）や豊かな創造性等を重視していく中で、今回のトピックでは、変化が激しい今日、ラグジュアリーブランドが社会的責任(CSR)をどのようにグローバル規模で伝えていくことができるのかに関して、皆様の率直なご意見を頂ければ幸いです。 「こうすべき」「こうあるべき」という視点ではなく、皆様にとって重要と感じることについて率直な意見を頂ければ幸いです。 今月は、動画や画像よりも、トピックに関し熟慮いただき、テキストのご回答に力をいれていただけましたら幸いです。 回答期限は<u>7月7日（水）</u>となります。尚、追加質問は<u>7月8日（木）</u>にアップされますので、適宜当サイトに再度アクセスいただき引き続きご回答いただけますようお願いいたします。

study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on fashion and your lifestyle in the 21st century! Virtual fashion is a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of this concept these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by end of day Saturday August 21st. Starting on an assigned day around August 23-26, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: William
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this study! The purpose is to get your honest feedback on your experience at and relationship with Sheetz. 

We are looking to understand what purpose it serves in your life. We will also ask you to take us along on your shopping journey in the store.
