name: Jenn
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Athleisure Discovery

 

INTRODUCTION:

Congratulations on being selected for this study on athleisure’s role in your life and how you explore brands online!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolve” the post. Resolved posts will have a blue check mark on them. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-WORK VIDEO

Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignment during the weekend prior to the study.

 

Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out three (3) of your favorite athleisure and/or activewear items on your bed.

 

Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following: 

 

Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM.  If you want to submit three separate videos, that’s cool.  Or you would rather do the three pieces in one take, that is also fine – but please limit the length of the video to about 2 minutes total.

 

1.     What brand is this? Where did you buy it (if online, please specify)? When did you buy it? And why did you buy it?

2.     Roughly how much of your athleisure/activewear wardrobe is made up of this brand?

3.     What do you do while wearing this piece? (Exercise, lounge, etc). We are super interested in what items you choose for certain workout or non-workout activities!

4.     What product characteristics make this item good for doing that?  (Speak to fit, feel, function, style – whatever is important to you and for that activity!)

5.     Finally, how do you feel when wearing it?

 

DAY ONE:  A DAY IN YOUR LIFE!

 

1.     VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever it is that you see when you wake up!

COMMENT: What are we seeing here?  How are you feeling at this moment about the day ahead? 

 

2.     VISUAL: Take a picture or two of anything that is part of your morning ritual, from coffee to breakfast, to your commute, to meditation or exercise.

COMMENT: How do each of these elements make you feel?  What do you get out of it?

 

3.     VISUAL: Upload a few screenshots – or take pictures – of a few things that represent things that bring you JOY or INSPIRE YOU.

COMMENT:

·       What is this? Why are you passionate about this?

·       What is one goal you have that feels difficult to achieve but you REALLY WANT? What is standing in the way (if anything)?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of your work/studying or other primary activity during the day.

COMMENT:

·       How do you feel at various points of time during the primary part of your day?

·       What are the “pain points” (if any?)

·       What parts do you generally enjoy the most?

 

5.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of the most SOCIAL part of your day.

COMMENT: Who are you interacting with? How do you feel at these times?

 

6.     VISUAL: Think for a minute about the news and content/entertainment that draws you in (we’ll get to social media in a second.) Upload some screenshots that fill me in on the kind of content you enjoy.

COMMENT: What do you enjoy about these choices? What do you think they say about you?

 

7.     VISUAL: Now consider social media: Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn, Reddit, etc. Upload a screenshot or two that tells me which you engage with the most.

COMMENT:

·       For each, describe your way of participating. Do you observe more, or post more?

·       What do you enjoy about each social platform that you’re involved with? How important is it to you?

·       What brands or influencers do you follow on social media, and what do you get out of it?

·       What is your favorite brand to follow? Why? How has this impacted your perception of the brand? Your likelihood to purchase that brand?

 

8.     VISUAL: If you exercise at all regularly, please upload a picture of you doing what you do – i.e. workout, running, a fitness class, etc.

COMMENT:

·       Why do you exercise?

·       How important is exercising to you?

·       What is your favorite way to sweat? How frequently do you do this – and are there any other parts to your fitness repertoire?

·       How do you feel during exercising? Afterwards? Does this vary by activity?

 

9.     VISUAL:  We’re living in an age of technology obsession. Take a picture of any device or app that you are currently enjoying. 

COMMENT: What do you love about this? Do you ever use any tech as part of your fitness routine (apps, wearables, etc)? Why or why not?

 

10.  VISUAL: When evening rolls around, take a picture that tells me what you do for relaxation, or any other kind of evening activity or ritual.

COMMENT: What is it and what do you like about this?

 

11.  VISUAL: As you reflect on the day, what do you wish you could spend MORE time doing (if anything)? Upload a photo or screenshot to represent that.

COMMENT: Finally, if you had all the time in the world, what would you like to spend more time doing? Why?

 

PLEASE NOTE: Feel free to “ad lib” in this Day in the Life section and share additional photos, screenshots and comments about anything that tells me WHAT MAKES YOU YOU!  Food and drink choice posts are also super relevant and interesting here!

 

DAY TWO: LULULEMON & OTHER BRANDS – HOW DO YOU EXPLORE THEM?

 

12.  VISUAL:  Please take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? 

COMMENT:  FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how? 

 

13.  VISUAL: When you hear the lululemon name or see the logo, what comes immediately to mind? Upload a screenshot that represents this (it can be anything – be conceptual and creative!).

COMMENT: To what extend would you agree “lululemon is a brand for me” on a scale of 1-5 (with 5 being the strongest)? Why?

name: Regular Guests
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Men’s Apparel – Focus on Casual Shorts and Swim
INTRODUCTION:
Congratulations on being selected for this study on lululemon men’s apparel!
If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.
Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.
Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignments prior to the study.
PRE-WORK VIDEO 1: Swimwear
Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out a pair or two of your favorite swim shorts/trunks. Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following:
Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM:
What brand is this? Where did you buy them (if online, please specify)? How long have you owned them, and do you remember what motivated you to choose them? What makes them your favourite / how do they compare to the rest of the swim shorts in your closet?
PRE-WORK VIDEO 2: Casual Shorts
Now, take a moment to prepare and lay out a few pairs of your favorite casual shorts (i.e. shorts with room for a belt – vs. athletic shorts) and then create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following:
What brand is this? Where did you buy them (if online, please specify)? How long have you owned them, and do you remember what motivated you to choose them? What makes these your favourite? How do they compare to the rest of the casual shorts in your closet?
PART ONE A: Casual Shorts & Lifestyle
1. VISUAL: Think about the various occasions when you wear casual shorts (i.e. jeans or chinos.) Upload a few photos or screenshots to represent these occasions and the various activities you do in your casual shorts.
COMMENT: FOR EACH, what style works best for this? Is it easy or hard to find shorts that work for these occasions? Where (if anywhere) do you get inspiration for the fashion aspect of styling shorts? Are there occasions where you would never wear casual shorts but would like to, and why?
2. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents where you made your last casual short purchase.
COMMENT: Where did you get the last pair of casual shorts that you purchased? How often do you replenish your casual shorts? Have you ever stocked up on one particular style? Why or why not? How do feel about wearing shorts (ie socially) – in other words, are there situations where you hesitate to wear shorts? If so why?
3. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents what comes to mind when you think about lululemon non-athletic apparel.
COMMENT: How familiar are you with lululemon apparel for men that is non-fitness related? What expectations do you have (if any) for what they offer in casual shorts?
PART ONE B: Swim Shorts & Lifestyle
1. VISUAL: Imagine that you didn’t have any swim trunks/shorts on hand, and you wanted to go swimming? Upload a screenshot or take a picture of another type of short you own that you might use instead (ie a boardie short).
COMMENT: Have you ever found yourself swimming in non-swim trunks/shorts? If so, what do you find works? If not, why not?
2. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents where you made your last swim short purchase.
COMMENT: Where did you get the last pair of swim shorts that you purchased? How often do you replenish your swim shorts? Have you ever stocked up on one particular style? Why or why not?
3. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents what comes to mind when you think of men’s swimming apparel from lululemon.
COMMENT: Were you aware that lululemon had swim shorts? What would your expectations be of what they offer?
4. VISUAL: Take a minute to check out www.lululemon.com on your phone and search for three styles of shorts: the Surge, the Pacebreaker, and the T.H.E. Upload a screenshot of any style that appeals to you.
COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? What would you think of lululemon creating swim versions of these shorts, like a Surge swim short for example? What, if anything, has held you back from purchasing lululemon casual shorts in the past? What, if anything has held you back from purchasing lululemon swim shorts in the past?
PART TWO: Shopping at lululemon
Time to shop for shorts at your local lululemon store!
5. VISUAL: Enter the store and take a photo of the first place you would go to look for casual shorts.
COMMENT: When you enter the store, where would you first look for casual shorts? How easy is it to find the selection? What is your first impression of the men’s section?
6. VISUAL: Please browse the casual shorts offering and upload photos of anything that you particularly like.
COMMENT: What do you think of the current selection? What gets your attention? What, if anything, turns you off? What brand would you compare this offering to, and why? How does lululemon compare?
7. VISUAL: Now, take a photo of the first place you would go to look for swimwear in the lululemon store.
COMMENT: Where would you go to look at swimwear in the lululemon store? How easy is it to find?
8. VISUAL: Please browse the swimwear offering and upload photos of anything that you particularly like.
COMMENT: What do you think of the current selection? What gets your attention? What, if anything, turns you off? What brand would you compare this offering to, and why? How does lululemon compare?
9. VISUAL: Please try on a pair of swim shorts in store and ask a salesperson or friend to take a picture of you wearing them.
COMMENT: What features do you like about these? What, if anything, is missing that you wish it had?
10. VISUAL: Please try on a pair of casual shorts in store and ask a salesperson or friend to take a picture of you wearing them.
COMMENT: What features do you like about these? What, if anything, is missing that you wish it had?
WRAP-UP!
Time to summarize your thoughts and advice to the lululemon product team!
11. VIDEO: Once you get back home, please create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following:
a. Why did you choose to try on the specific pairs of casual and swim shorts you tried on in store?
b. How did these options compare to what you already own?
c. What would it take for you to buy a swim short from lululemon? And a casual short from lululemon?
d. Any other feedback or advice for the design team in creating new swim or casual shorts?
THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® Study: Campus Life and Food! Part I: Complete by Wednesday 9 pm, February 13th Part II: Complete on Thursday, February 14th Welcome to the LOOKLOOK® Campus Life and Food Study! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK® screen.
In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus – showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them! Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses. PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where you are on campus (or off!) and what you are eating! With EACH of those posts, please answer related questions in full. PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS! You’re getting paid for your thoughtful opinions!J
We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! HERE ARE THE TASKS: Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Wednesday February 14th.
Please complete Part I by 9:00 pm on Wednesday February 13th! Please complete Part II on Wednesday February 14th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee. We want to see what you eat and drink ALL DAY LONG, and we want to see the facilities that are available to you.
PART I YOU
  1. FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:
    1. How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?
    2. What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience? Health? Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?
  2. Describe (through a few pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like. Please comment on the following: How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends?
YOUR SCHOOL 3. Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at your school. What three adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture at your school? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body? What makes this place unique? FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL
  1. Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus. This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it. How can it be improved? We want details here, down to the condiments you prefer for your tea or coffee.
  2. Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?
  3. Take pictures of any branded franchises that exist on your campus today (i.e., coffee shops, fast food etc) and tell me if you ever frequent them, and why or why not. Are there others you’d be delighted to see? If so, upload screenshots of them and tell me what you would like about adding them!
FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL 7. Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit. For each, please answer: when do you tend to go here? How often? Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? FOOD JOURNAL (A) (DINNER, LATE NIGHT SNACKS) In an effort to make tomorrow’s food journal a little easier to navigate we ask that you make your dinner post tonight. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Tonight, when you eat dinner, please snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context. Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.
  1. What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).
  2. What are you eating?
  3. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?
  4. What details are important – how is the QUALITY? HEALTHINESS? CONVENIENCE FACTOR?
PERSONALIZATION FACTOR? What was great – or what could be better? PART II FOOD JOURNAL (B) (BREAKFAST, LUNCH, SNACKS – THROUGH LATE AFTERNOON) Today’s food journal will follow the same format as food journal (A) and should include your first meal or beverage of the day, coffee (if you drink it), any snacks or refreshments you have throughout the morning, your lunch, and any afternoon snacks. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context. Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.
  1. What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).
  2. What are you eating?
  3. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?
  4. What details are important – how is the QUALITY? HEALTHINESS? CONVENIENCE FACTOR? PERSONALIZATION FACTOR? What was great – or what could be better?
Once you’ve made your last afternoon snacks post you can continue on to PIE IN THE SKY. PIE IN THE SKY 16. What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list? PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of. Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only.  Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

study_instructions:
¡Nos da mucho gusto que esté participando en nuestro proyecto de investigación! Tal como se lo habíamos comentado, antes de su discusión de grupo en línea queremos conocerlo un poco, y la forma cómo nos gustaría  hacer esto es por medio de unos videos que usted grabará.  

A continuación, se encuentran algunas cosas para tener en mente al grabar sus videos:
• A veces ayuda que un amigo o familiar sostenga la cámara para que pueda concentrarse en lo que está hablando en lugar de preocuparse por sostener la cámara.
• Asegúrese de que usted o quien sea que esté filmando mantenga la cámara lo más quieta posible (sin movimientos temblorosos o agitados).
• Evite cualquier ruido de fondo o música - esto a menudo se escucha mucho más alto en la grabación.
• Haga una pausa durante dos segundos al principio y al final del vídeo para asegurarnos de que la respuesta no esté cortada.
• Antes de enviar su(s) video(s), reprodúzcalo para asegurarse de que todo se ve/suena bien: 
• ¿Está usted mirando en la dirección correcta? Es fácil accidentalmente terminar con imágenes laterales si gira su smartphone mientras filma, ¡y queremos evitar que eso suceda!
• ¿La iluminación es lo suficientemente brillante para que podamos verlo
• ¿Habló lo suficientemente alto para que podamos escuchar claramente todo lo que está diciendo

nWelcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study!  The most important thing to know about this study is that we want you to focus on life BEYOND COVID . In other words, we're looking to create a revamped dining experience for NEXT YEAR. That's why we're going to ask you about your memories of what was available last year so we can build from that . This assumes that while some safety protocols will still be necessary, a much more varied and complete dining experience will again be available!

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 3 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Potential - Infrequents
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY: Fashion, Shopping, and You! INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study on how you shop for fashion today. We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior. We want to get into the details! If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look™, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK: Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s! These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe. It should take about half an hour. GO-TO “LOOKS” VISUAL: POST FOUR OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS. We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality. If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them? (For ex., one person might have four: “date night”, “weekend brunch”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out- and-about.”) Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light. Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding! But apparel is the focus of this exercise.
COMMENT: IN EACH POST, tell me the following: (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who makes each of the elements of this look? (ie who is the designer?) SUPERSTAR VISUAL: Identify the top Superstar individual piece in your wardrobe that you consider high value - ie you wear it often and feel great wearing it. Please photograph the piece in good light, hanging or laid out on your bed (or have someone snap a picture of you wearing it!) COMMENT: “This is a Superstar piece because ___________________________. It’s made by ________________ and I bought it at ________________________. I can count on it for ________________________.” STUDY DAY! So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups! PASSIONS VISUAL: Who/where/what areas of personal interest light your fire? What do you really love to spend time doing and get excited about – outside of family? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
COMMENT: Please finish this sentence in your own words: “This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.” FASHION DISCOVERY VISUAL: Post a few screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.). Where do you tend to discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below: COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”
PURCHASE EXAMPLE VISUAL: Next, think about the last contemporary or luxury apparel purchase you made. Screenshot where you made that purchase - whether it was an actual store or a website/app. COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “I purchased this _______________________ (item/outfit) at __________________ (store/site).” Now, think about the details of that purchase. Were you buying for a specific occasion? Was it an impulse buy? Where you shopping for fun or were you on a mission? Had you seen the piece or the look before? (If so, where?) In the end, what was the voice in your head that motivated you to make the actual purchase? WHERE YOU LOVE TO SHOP VISUAL: Think about where you actually spend the majority of your apparel dollars. Post a screenshot that destination, whether it’s a brand, a boutique/dept store brand, or a brand or store website. You can create multiple posts here as applicable! COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “I tend to buy most of my apparel here: _______________________ because __________________”. Reasons for loyalty to a certain shopping experience might include convenience, loyalty points, a relationship with a certain sales associate, the easily navigation of an e-commerce website, or just your enjoyment of a certain atmosphere! Whatever it is, give this some thought, and share as much detail as possible! SERVICES AND LOYALTY VISUAL: As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place. Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. COMMENT: (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words: “Services that I enjoy at my favorite stores include _______________________”. These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.
VERONICA BEARD
YOUR VERONICA BEARD PURCHASE: VISUAL: Please screenshot the 1-2 item(s) you have from Veronica Beard. COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “This is _______________________ and I bought it ________________ (which store/boutique/website)”. In addition, share these details: When did you buy it? How did you discover the piece? What role does it play in your wardrobe? WHO IS THE VERONICA BEARD WOMAN? VISUAL: Please screenshot a picture that represents, in your mind, the woman who shops a lot of Veronica Beard. This can be anyone! A celebrity, whatever pops into your head (don’t over think it!) COMMENT: Please complete: “I chose this image because_____________.” URGENCY VISUAL: Take a screenshot or picture of any type of clothing item that you feel MORE urgency to purchase than Veronica Beard. COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? What do you think would give you more of a sense of excitement about getting to know the Veronica Beard line a bit bitter? (Be completely honest! Is there any way Veronica Beard could do a better job of following up with you after your initial purchase? If so, how? SUBSCRIPTON SERVICES! VISUAL: Take a screenshot of any type of clothing subscription service that is currently on your radar, that you use, or have tried. If no clothing subscription services come to mind, take a screenshot of any other type of subscription service (i.e. beauty) that are on your radar, that you use, or have tried. COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? Is there any reason you would subscribe to an apparel subscription service? If you have never tried one, what concerns do you have? What would be the ideal apparel subscription service that offers something no
one else does, that would actually motivate you to try it? Would you prefer a single brand or a multibrand offering from an apparel subscription service? THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: Will Purchase Next 6-12 Months
study_instructions:
恭喜您被选中, 来体验 LookLook. 您是对进口豪华车了解颇深而且正在考虑/刚刚购买一辆的人，这款 App 是专门为您设计的。
首页上的每个主题内容都是为了探索您购车体验的各个方面, 目的是为了更好地理解您如何选择品牌与车型, 访问经销商店后的感受，这些能帮助我们未来提升您的购车体验。
您在反复思考后可以上传建议/意见、照片截频和/或视频来回答每一个问题。在招募者指定的日期, 一位主持人会根据您提供的信息提出跟进问题。当某个主题已结束, 主持人会将主题标记为“已完成”(旁边有个蓝色勾勾)。当所有的主题都标记为”已完成”, 您就完成调研了。
请保持开放的心态, 诚恳且完整地表达您的想法。这不是大规模调研, 而是一场内容分享！您分享的一切, 都仅仅限于本次研究活动所用(一切信息都保密). 答案无关对错, 我们只希望您 100%地诚实。

Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: Luxury Gamers
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on fashion and your lifestyle in the 21st century! Virtual fashion is a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of this concept these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by end of day Saturday August 21st. Starting on an assigned day around August 23-26, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: Betas 2
study_instructions:
Welcome to the Luxury Jewelry and Watches Study!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

You have been chosen for this very selective study because you have great taste, and you buy luxury jewelry. This is not a focus group, although we do want your opinions. But we also want your input on how to revitalize a storied European luxury jewelry and watches brand. Therefore, we refer to this type of project as co-creation. We are looking for your ideas as well as your honest take on some jewelry designs. The voice of this brand should be developed to reach women like you.

We appreciate how busy you all are. In order for the study to be successful, the following questions must be completed and submitted on LOOKLOOK™ prior to the first scheduled day of your participation. Please do ‘Task 1: Selfie Time’ and answer all 4 questions and their subparts.

FIRST TASK: IT’S SELFIE TIME!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

Now, please upload photos of yourself wearing the pieces of jewelry you described to Susan when you spoke. For each of the pictures you have sent, please specify:

o   Was this a gift or did you buy it for yourself?  

o   Where was it purchased?

o   How did you discover this piece? What made you covet it?

THE QUESTIONS

On LOOKLOOK™, you will be prompted where to put these answers.

1.    SHOPPING FOR THE JEWELRY AND WATCH BRANDS YOU LOVE

 

a.    When you purchase jewelry, is it typically for a milestone, a seasonal  purchase, or an impulse buy?

b.   What are 1 or 2 of your favorite luxury jewelry/watch brands, and why?

c.    Do you browse for jewelry in stores or online?

o   If you browse in store, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite stores.

o   If you browse online, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite sites.

d.   When it’s time to purchase jewelry, do you do it in store or online? Or both?

e.    Is it different for watches?

 

2.    TELL ME ABOUT YOUR STYLE

 

a.    What 3  adjectives would you choose to describe your personal style (in general?)

b.   Please also upload 2 or 3 photos that demonstrate how you like to wear jewelry.

o   What rings do you wear?

o   What is your wrist look? Do you like to stack, mix designs, alloys, etc. or do you prefer to match?

o   What earring do you like to wear? Studs, cuffs, drop, etc.?

o   What necklaces do you like to wear? Do you like to layer them or wear one at a time?

o   Do you wear the same jewelry day and night or do you switch for evening?

c.    Do your jewelry pieces serve different needs (ie investment, statement, everyday)? How often do you  make fine jewelry purchases?

d.   List 1 or 2 of your favorite brands outside of jewelry (can be anything!)

 

3.YOUR MEDIA DIET

 

a.    Which of the following media do you use regularly (for anything – in general – not just shopping!)

o   Social media - If yes, what platforms?  

o   Websites - What sites?

o   Print magazines - Which ones? Subscribe or buy occasionally?  

o   Anything else? (Satellite Radio? Podcasts?)

o   TV Shows (Netflix? Cable?)

 

4.    WHAT YOU LOVE

a.    What are you most passionate about in life – other than your family? Take a  screenshot or picture that illustrates 1 or 2 of those interests.

b.   Where do you like to travel? 

c.    What happens to be on your wish list for your next jewelry purchase? Why do you love it? How did it get on your radar?

 

Thank you for completing the questions above! On your scheduled day of participation, your moderator will let you know what brand we are focusing on for the remainder of the study, and will start unveiling the pieces to you for your feedback! You get to take a break from sending us pictures.

At the time, please respond to your moderator’s queries on each specific piece. When you are done, your moderator will send through a bit of the background story on the brand we’re focusing on. Once you’ve read that, you are done with Day One!  

The focus of Day Two will be helping us come up with great creative ideas!

We also want to understand from your perspective how choices about these types of options show up as part of your work responsibilities, as it’s different for every organization.

name: Current Purchasers
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: Fitness Gear, Props and Accessories

Congratulations on being selected for this study on fitness gear, props and accessories! You’ve been selected for this elite panel because you are serious about your fitness, your wellness and specifically because you are into at least one of these three fitness activities:

(a)   Running

(b)   Training

(c)    Yoga/Barre/Pilates

 

While you may take part in a number of fitness activities, we specifically want to explore the gear and accessories you invest in for your primary fitness activities – the ones you take most seriously and do most often – as well as any other health and wellness focused activities.

   

Fitness accessories can be anything from what you carry to and from a work out, to what you use during, or after a workout! (i.e. socks, bags, mats, at-home equipment, rollers, massage balls, cold weather accessories – anything!)

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

OVERVIEW:

There are three parts to this study. 

(i)              First, we want to get to know you a bit. You can answer these questions as soon as you post your selfie.

(ii)            Next, we want you to keep a diary of how you use your gear/props/accessories for two separate workout occasions over the next four days, ideally one day over the weekend and one day over the week. (We want to see how your weekend fitness activity may be different from a weekday.)

(iii)           Finally, as a bit of a wrap-up on Tuesday June 11th we’ll be engaging in some back and forth discussion about how your fitness activity fits into your overall wellness strategy!

 

 

GETTING TO KNOW YOU: A DEEP DIVE ON BAGS AND SOCKS

 

1.     VISUAL: Think about an image that represents how you feel when you get the MOST out of your workout routine and post a screenshot that depicts that feeling. COMMENT: Tell me why you chose this and provide a few adjectives that describe the feeling.

 

2.     VIDEO – YOUR SOCK WARDROBE: Gather all of the socks that you wear most frequently both to work out and in day to day life. Choose only items you purchased for yourself (no gifts or generic items; we’re interested in brands here.) Group your socks into categories and lay them out. Then have a friend or family member film you while you show me the socks in each category and answer the following:

a.     Why did you group the socks into these categories? Which socks do you use for fitness and which are worn day to day, and which for both? What features make a sock good for one or the other, or both?

b.    What do you get out these socks? What benefits do each of the categories provide?

c.     What brands are your socks? What do you count on those brands for when it comes to socks?

name: Enthusiasts
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY: Fashion, Shopping, and You! INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study on how you shop for fashion today. We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior. We want to get into the details! If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look™, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK: Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s! These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe. It should take about half an hour. GO-TO “LOOKS” VISUAL: POST FOUR OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS. We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality. If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them? (For ex., one person might have four: “date night”, “weekend brunch”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out- and-about.”) Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light. Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding! But apparel is the focus of this exercise.
COMMENT: IN EACH POST, tell me the following: (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who makes each of the elements of this look? (ie who is the designer?) SUPERSTAR VISUAL: Identify the top Superstar individual piece in your wardrobe that you consider high value - ie you wear it often and feel great wearing it. Please photograph the piece in good light, hanging or laid out on your bed (or have someone snap a picture of you wearing it!) COMMENT: “This is a Superstar piece because ___________________________. It’s made by ________________ and I bought it at ________________________. I can count on it for ________________________.” STUDY DAY! So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups! PASSIONS VISUAL: Who/where/what areas of personal interest light your fire? What do you really love to spend time doing and get excited about – outside of family? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
COMMENT: Please finish this sentence in your own words: “This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.” FASHION DISCOVERY VISUAL: Post a few screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.). Where do you tend to discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below: COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”
PURCHASE EXAMPLE VISUAL: Next, think about the last contemporary or luxury apparel purchase you made. Screenshot where you made that purchase - whether it was an actual store or a website/app. COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “I purchased this _______________________ (item/outfit) at __________________ (store/site).” Now, think about the details of that purchase. Were you buying for a specific occasion? Was it an impulse buy? Where you shopping for fun or were you on a mission? Had you seen the piece or the look before? (If so, where?) In the end, what was the voice in your head that motivated you to make the actual purchase? WHERE YOU LOVE TO SHOP VISUAL: Think about where you actually spend the majority of your apparel dollars. Post a screenshot that destination, whether it’s a brand, a boutique/dept store brand, or a brand or store website. You can create multiple posts here as applicable! COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “I tend to buy most of my apparel here: _______________________ because __________________”. Reasons for loyalty to a certain shopping experience might include convenience, loyalty points, a relationship with a certain sales associate, the easily navigation of an e-commerce website, or just your enjoyment of a certain atmosphere! Whatever it is, give this some thought, and share as much detail as possible! SERVICES AND LOYALTY VISUAL: As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place. Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. COMMENT: (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words: “Services that I enjoy at my favorite stores include _______________________”. These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.
VERONICA BEARD FAVORITE ITEM: VISUAL: Please screenshot the item you have from Veronica Beard that is your absolute favorite – ie you wear it often and love it. COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “This is _______________________ and I bought it ________________ (which store/boutique/website)”. In addition, share these details: When did you buy it? How did you discover the piece? What role does it play in your wardrobe? WHO IS THE VERONICA BEARD WOMAN? VISUAL: Please screenshot a picture that represents, in your mind, the Veronica Beard brand come to life as a woman. This can be anyone! Yourself, a celebrity, whatever pops into your head. Don’t over-think this. COMMENT: Please complete: “I chose this image because_____________.” Now imagine a cocktail party where all of the following brands have come to life as people: Veronica Beard and three of your favorite apparel brands! What would each be drinking? Who would be talking to whom? What are the energies like of these “people”? Have fun with this and be creative please J WHAT IS VERONICA BEARD FAMOUS FOR? VISUAL: Take a screenshot or picture of whatever you think the brand is most famous for. This can be absolutely anything! COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? What drew you to Veronica Beard initially? How did you discover it? Do you have any idea about the brand story – or who is designing? Is that something that interests you? What would you like to learn – and if it is of interest, where/how would you like to learn about it?
VERONICA BEARD IN THE FUTURE! VISUAL: Take a screenshot or picture of any type of additional apparel item or any other type of product you would love to see Veronica Beard design! COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? SUBSCRIPTON SERVICES! VISUAL: Take a screenshot of any type of clothing subscription service that is currently on your radar, that you use, or have tried. If no clothing subscription services come to mind, take a screenshot of any other type of subscription service (i.e. beauty) that are on your radar, that you use, or have tried. COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? When it comes to clothing subscription services, would you be more likely to try a single brand or a multibrand offering? If Veronica Beard were to offer a subscription service, what would you want them to offer? THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: Light Users with Kids
study_instructions: Welcome to this creative ideation session where you will be weighing in on the most appealing way to bring a new brand character to life! We’re talking to people of all ages and walks of life who include grain or protein bars as part of a balanced lifestyle. It doesn’t matter whether you currently eat them, but for this LookLook session we are focusing on the Belvita brand! Please be expressive with the questions that ask for written responses! And finally, there are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty – have fun! One last note, a reminder from the LookLook® terms of service that this project is confidential, please don’t post about it on social media:No material from the Website or the Mobile App may be copied, reproduced, displayed, republished, reverse engineered, downloaded, posted, digitized, translated, modified, transmitted, distributed or commercially exploited in any way without SPARK’s express consent.

name: Potential - Non-Purchasers
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY: Fashion, Shopping, and You! INTRODUCTION: Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study on how you shop for fashion today. We wanted you in the study not only because you are passionate about fashion, but also because you are articulate and comfortable reflecting on your interests and shopping behavior. We want to get into the details! If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look™, please do so now. We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does fashion mean to you at this point in your life, and how do you make choices in today’s busy world when there are so many ways to discover new looks, new brands and new ways of shopping? Below are the instructions for the study. Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. PRE-STUDY HOMEWORK: Prior to your day of participation and dialogue with your moderator, we’d like to get a sense of your personal sense of style and brands you consider your “go-to’s! These questions need to be completed when you are at home with access to your wardrobe. It should take about half an hour. GO-TO “LOOKS” VISUAL: POST FOUR OF YOUR GO-TO LOOKS. We’d love to understand what kind of outfits you put together, as a reflection of your current lifestyle and your personality. If you think about your day to day rhythm, how many occasions do you regularly dress for, and what is the type of go-to outfit you create for them? (For ex., one person might have four: “date night”, “weekend brunch”, “creative meeting”, “chic and comfy out- and-about.”) Please lay out each outfit on your bed and photograph it in good light. Shoes and handbags would be a great touch to complete the look if you feel like adding! But apparel is the focus of this exercise.
COMMENT: IN EACH POST, tell me the following: (i) What do you call this type of look, and how often do you wear it? (ii) Who makes each of the elements of this look? (ie who is the designer?) SUPERSTAR VISUAL: Identify the top Superstar individual piece in your wardrobe that you consider high value - ie you wear it often and feel great wearing it. Please photograph the piece in good light, hanging or laid out on your bed (or have someone snap a picture of you wearing it!) COMMENT: “This is a Superstar piece because ___________________________. It’s made by ________________ and I bought it at ________________________. I can count on it for ________________________.” STUDY DAY! So, today we are going to get a little more detail about certain topics. Looking for total honesty here – as well as creativity in how you answer these questions! Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment. Look out for my follow-ups! PASSIONS VISUAL: Who/where/what areas of personal interest light your fire? What do you really love to spend time doing and get excited about – outside of family? Share a few pictures or screenshots.
COMMENT: Please finish this sentence in your own words: “This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.” FASHION DISCOVERY VISUAL: Post a few screenshots of places you go online that inspire the types of clothing you buy. (This can include any social media, editorial, store sites, apps, or brand sites/apps.). Where do you tend to discover new products/styles? With each one, please complete the comment below: COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “This is ___________. I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc). I’m drawn to this because ______________________.”
PURCHASE EXAMPLE VISUAL: Next, think about the last contemporary or luxury apparel purchase you made. Screenshot where you made that purchase - whether it was an actual store or a website/app. COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “I purchased this _______________________ (item/outfit) at __________________ (store/site).” Now, think about the details of that purchase. Were you buying for a specific occasion? Was it an impulse buy? Where you shopping for fun or were you on a mission? Had you seen the piece or the look before? (If so, where?) In the end, what was the voice in your head that motivated you to make the actual purchase? WHERE YOU LOVE TO SHOP VISUAL: Think about where you actually spend the majority of your apparel dollars. Post a screenshot that destination, whether it’s a brand, a boutique/dept store brand, or a brand or store website. You can create multiple posts here as applicable! COMMENT: Please complete in your own words: “I tend to buy most of my apparel here: _______________________ because __________________”. Reasons for loyalty to a certain shopping experience might include convenience, loyalty points, a relationship with a certain sales associate, the easily navigation of an e-commerce website, or just your enjoyment of a certain atmosphere! Whatever it is, give this some thought, and share as much detail as possible! SERVICES AND LOYALTY VISUAL: As you consider where you really enjoy shopping the most, think about services you receive that make you feel loyal towards that place. Screenshot something (or a few!) that represent(s) that experience. COMMENT: (FOR EACH ONE): Please complete in your own words: “Services that I enjoy at my favorite stores include _______________________”. These could include anything from tailoring to transactional services such as digital receipts and mobile payment to delivery or gifting options, to having a “text relationship” with a sales associate who provides personal messages about new arrivals or upcoming promotions.
VERONICA BEARD WHAT IS VERONICA BEARD? VISUAL: Take a minute to check out the Veronica Beard website, its Instagram and the kind of product that is offered: www.veronicabeard.com. Please screenshot an item or an image that attracts you. COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? What – if anything – appeals to you about this brand? Does it seem similar to other apparel brands – if so, which ones? Were you familiar with Veronica Beard prior to this study? IF SO, what were your impressions, and what do you think has prevented you from purchasing? IF NOT, how strong is your desire to check it out further (scale of 1-10, with 10 being strongest)? URGENCY VISUAL: Take a screenshot or picture of any type of clothing item that you feel MORE urgency to purchase than Veronica Beard. COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? SUBSCRIPTON SERVICES! VISUAL: Take a screenshot of any type of clothing subscription service that is currently on your radar, that you use, or have tried. If no clothing subscription services come to mind, take a screenshot of any other type of subscription service (i.e. beauty) that are on your radar, that you use, or have tried. COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? Is there any reason you would subscribe to an apparel subscription service? If you have never tried one, what concerns do you have? What would be the ideal apparel subscription service that offers something no one else does, that would actually motivate you to try it? Would you prefer a single brand or a multibrand offering from an apparel subscription service? THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: Senior
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at University Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make! We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS! Each topic on your LookLook® home screen will explore a different phase of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and give us a thoughtful response (no one-word answers please! Details are super important in this one)! TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great! The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on enjoyable life experiences! We are excited to learn from you over the next few days as you reflect on what in-person experiences mean to you.  We’ve organized these into a handful of topics to be completed at your leisure over a period of three days, as you can consider them mindfully and can give us thoughtful responses. In this study, pictures, screenshots, and videos are very important for us to understand and visualize the experiences you’re sharing. Please be generous with these throughout – thank you! For timing, please finish answering all questions (Topics 1-5) by Sunday, October 3rd. On Monday, October 4th, a moderator will be asking you some follow-up questions and those should be answered by Tuesday, October 5th. We’ll be in touch with you throughout, via text/WhatsApp, and we’re happy to answer your questions along the way. Thank you!

name: Essential Workers
Upperclass
study_instructions:
nWelcome to the LookLook® Campus Life and Food Study!  The most important thing to know about this study is that we want you to focus on life BEYOND COVID . In other words, we're looking to create a revamped dining experience for NEXT YEAR. That's why we're going to ask you about your memories of what was available last year so we can build from that . This assumes that while some safety protocols will still be necessary, a much more varied and complete dining experience will again be available!

In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!  

We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!  

Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions. You will know when your moderator has responded to one of your posts when there is an orange outline surrounding a topic circle. To view the moderator comments, click on a topic circle that is outlined in orange and look for the orange text bubble that says 'New Moderator Comments.'  

When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.  

TOPIC 3 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.  

WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!  

We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.  

The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Baylor Med Center
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: FOOD AT WORK
Instructions for Participants
Welcome to the LookLook® Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing.
The purpose of this study is for us to show us how eating, drinking and other types of experiences affect how people feel at work. What makes you feel comfortable (or uncomfortable), more productive, more motivated, more creative…? You can even think beyond food to other amenities like fitness centers, amazing décor, collaborative workspaces, etc.
We’re looking to find out what really matters to people – perhaps un-earthing some ideas that no one has thought of before!
Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions and accompany each with a picture that you either take – or save as a screen grab – and post. It’s all about the details, so NO ONE WORD COMMENTS please!
Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to answer them. Your moderator will respond with follow-up to many of your posts and answering those will likely take an additional half hour.
Please note we want total candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will do with the study. If you work in a public space such as a hospital, please avoid showing people in the photos that you take – just focus on the food and amenities! All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and is being used for research purposes only.
Finally, please label your answers with the letters and numbers as they are outlined in the instructions (#1a, #3b, etc)
THE QUESTIONS
1. HOW YOU START YOUR DAY
a. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?
b. Screenshot and post an emoji or other image that represents the vibe of where you work. What three words describe how you feel at work on a typical day?
2. Next, we want to see your food and drink options! Do you have a café or cafeteria? Is there a convenience store? Please take a trip to the spots that are available to you for meals and take pictures to show what is offered. If it is a café or cafeteria, please visit each station. Don’t forget drinks and coffee/tea! For each option please answer the following:
a. How could the quality be improved? (Freshness, taste, variety, etc?)
b. Is it healthy enough for your tastes? If not, how would you improve it?
c. How convenient is it? Could technology play a role in some way that would make its delivery more convenient?
d. Are you able to personalize it to the extent that you wish? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative?
3. Now, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work.
Where are there snacks available (ie vending, coffee shops, convenience stores, etc)?
Please take a picture of each option and answer:
a. What is this? How would you describe the quality?
b. How convenient is it?
c. How healthy is it? Anything you would change on that front?
d. Can you personalize it?
4. This section is about where you eat AWAY from work.
a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please take screenshots of the places near work where you go most often when not eating at the office, and answer the following:
i. What is the name of this place?
ii. What do you like about this place?
iii. How often do you come here?
iv. What adjectives describe the atmosphere of this place? Do you wish there was something like this offered at your work?
5. Finally, think about your comfort level at work. What could be added to your work environment that would really lower your stress level and make it more fun, enjoyable and pleasant to be there? What would really blow your mind and surprise and delight you? Grab a few screenshots of ideas that represent your ideas. With each one, tell me what it is and how you would like to see it brought to life.
Please note: If one of your posts does not show a checkmark, there is likely a follow-up to answer. You will be compensated when you have answered all questions! Have fun, and thanks for participating!

name: Students
Bicultural
study_instructions:
¡Bienvenidos a este estudio! Usted ha sido seleccionado para formar parte de un grupo especial de personas a lo largo y ancho del país para explorar y entender mejor cómo su mundo inmediato puede haber cambiado como resultado del fenómeno Covid-19. Aunque vamos a explorar un amplio rango de temas, es importante que sepa que no hay una respuesta correcta o incorrecta a cualquier pregunta, ¡sus verdaderos sentimientos y respuestas sinceras son de gran valor para nosotros!
Hay algunas preguntas donde  les pedimos que nos contesten con un video, y verá que solo la opción de video estará activa. Para las demás preguntas, podrá contestar con texto o video según lo prefiera y agregar imágenes y emojis para ilustrar su respuesta.
¡Muchas gracias!

name: Millennial Prospects
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY: KRAVE Innovation!   

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study on protein snacks, including KRAVE Jerky!

 

In this study, we want to understand your snacking choices – particularly packaged snacks that you consider “better for you”.  We want to see what you buy, what you consider to be good choices and why, and how you discover new options for snacking in general.  We’ll be really curious about the role of protein snacks in your life – i.e., when are you eating them? Why do you choose a protein snack over other snacks?

 

Finally, the most exciting part is that we will be brainstorming with you about where a brand like KRAVE can innovate and create new protein snack options (beyond meat)!

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload a photo or video per the instructions and respond to the comment that goes along with it. Your moderator will ask you follow up questions throughout the days, be sure to look out for them.

 

Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.  

 

Day 1 Tasks:

 

KICKING OFF – SNACKS IN REAL LIFE

 

1.     VISUAL: Let’s visit your kitchen. Think for a moment about where you store snacks, both in the pantry and the fridge.  You’re going to take a series of pictures here of the types protein snacks that you eat most frequently.  For each picture, tell me the following:

COMMENT:

Ø  What is this? Describe the time of day/mood/occasion that you normally eat it.  What benefit does this have going for it?  How does it make you feel, and what makes you want it?

 

2.     VISUAL: During the course of a normal day, please take some selfies of yourself (or better yet, have a friend, family member or colleague take a good shot of you) snacking on whatever you would normally grab!  We’d love to see at least 2-3 examples here, taken at different times of day, serving different needs.  Make sure at least one or two of these occasions are active (pre or post-workout, out for a walk, on the go at work, etc.) during the day!

COMMENT:

Ø  Finish this sentence in your own words:  It’s _____ o’clock, and I am (doing) ____________________. I’m eating __________ because I feel like ____________.

 

SNACK SHOPPING!

Next, let’s go shopping for some protein snacks.  We’d like you to use the $25 included in your incentive payment to go shopping, where you normally do, for snacks you consider “better for you”.  Plan a trip to the store where you typically buy these, take a bit more time than perhaps you normally would, and browse the aisles to look at new items or buy familiar favorites – whatever appeals to you!  Important:  please include purchase of at least one package of KRAVE on this shopping trip

 

You will be engaging with LookLook during this shopping trip.  As you look at a range of protein snack options, we want to understand how you make your purchase decisions.

 

In-Store

 

3.     VISUAL: Take a picture of yourself outside the place you like to go to buy “better for me” snacks.

COMMENT:

Ø  Where are you?  Do you typically buy these types of snacks at one certain place, or wherever it’s convenient?

Ø  Do these snack purchases ever drive the shopping trip – one of the primary reasons you go to the store – OR are they a component on your shopping list…OR something you tend to purchase on the spot?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture of the aisle sign in the store where you first go to explore protein snacks.

COMMENT:

Ø  Is it easy to find delicious great snack options that you consider pretty healthy?  Why or why not? Do you feel like you have to do some hunting to find the good stuff, or are there tons of great possibilities?  Is there anything specific that you can’t easily find?

 

5.     VISUAL: Now, take a picture of each “contender” item that you consider buying for your protein snacks.

COMMENT (for each one):

Ø  What is this?  Is it something you know and have tried before – if so, what do you like about it?  If it’s new, what makes it look good?  NOTE:  we’re looking for at least 3-5 pictures of possible options here, but more are welcome!

Ø  Do you look at the nutritional information when you’re considering snacks to buy?  If so, please take a picture of whatever you look at, and tell me what interests you!

Ø  What could be better about this snack?

 

6.     VISUAL: Now, if you haven’t arrived there already please visit the part of the store where you would expect to find KRAVE jerky.  Take a picture of the aisle sign to show me where you are in the store.

COMMENT:

Ø  Is KRAVE hard to find in your store?  Why or why not?  Please take some pictures of other snacks that are near KRAVE on the shelf, and for each one, comment whether or not it is a snack that appeals to you.  ALSO, PLEASE INCLUDE AT LEAST ONE KRAVE PRODUCT OF YOUR CHOOSING IN YOUR PURCHASES TODAY.

 

At Home

 

7.     VISUAL: Take a group picture of the range of snacks you ended up selecting.

COMMENT (for each snack):

Ø  What is this?  Why did it win out?  Are you envisioning a specific time and place when you’ll enjoy it?

Ø  For the KRAVE specifically, why did you choose this flavor/product type (i.e., pouch, bar, stick)?  What was appealing about it?

 

KRAVE – Experience

8.     VISUAL: Take a picture of the KRAVE product that you purchased.

COMMENT:

Ø  Of all the options on the shelf, what was it about this package of KRAVE that was most appealing, and why?

Ø  What made you try KRAVE for the first time?

Ø  (First-timers only) Why have you never tried KRAVE before?

Ø  (After sampling it) What are your thoughts of this particular KRAVE product?

 

9.     VISUAL: Have a friend or family member take a picture of you enjoying some KRAVE in an everyday context.

COMMENT:

Ø  Where are you and what time of day is it?  Describe “The KRAVE Moment” in as much detail as possible!   

Ø  Which of your normal protein snacks could KRAVE possibly replace (if any) and why?

 

10. VISUAL: Upload a screenshot that represents the most important health benefit you associate with KRAVE (this can be anything – be creative!)

COMMENT:

Ø  What does this image represent?  Why is this benefit important?  Are there any other health benefits you might associate with KRAVE?
