name: Fashion Forward Guests
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Men’s Apparel – Focus on Casual Shorts and Swim
INTRODUCTION:
Congratulations on being selected for this study on lululemon men’s apparel!
If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.
Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.
Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignments prior to the study.
PRE-WORK VIDEO 1: Swimwear
Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out a pair or two of your favorite swim shorts/trunks. Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following:
Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM:
What brand is this? Where did you buy them (if online, please specify)? How long have you owned them, and do you remember what motivated you to choose them? What makes them your favourite / how do they compare to the rest of the swim shorts in your closet?
PRE-WORK VIDEO 2: Casual Shorts
Now, take a moment to prepare and lay out a few pairs of your favorite casual shorts (i.e. shorts with room for a belt – vs. athletic shorts) and then create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following:
What brand is this? Where did you buy them (if online, please specify)? How long have you owned them, and do you remember what motivated you to choose them? What makes these your favourite? How do they compare to the rest of the casual shorts in your closet?
PART ONE A: Casual Shorts & Lifestyle
1. VISUAL: Think about the various occasions when you wear casual shorts (i.e. jeans or chinos.) Upload a few photos or screenshots to represent these occasions and the various activities you do in your casual shorts.
COMMENT: FOR EACH, what style works best for this? Is it easy or hard to find shorts that work for these occasions? Where (if anywhere) do you get inspiration for the fashion aspect of styling shorts? Are there occasions where you would never wear casual shorts but would like to, and why?
2. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents where you made your last casual short purchase.
COMMENT: Where did you get the last pair of casual shorts that you purchased? How often do you replenish your casual shorts? Have you ever stocked up on one particular style? Why or why not? How do feel about wearing shorts (ie socially) – in other words, are there situations where you hesitate to wear shorts? If so why?
3. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents what comes to mind when you think about lululemon non-athletic apparel.
COMMENT: How familiar are you with lululemon apparel for men that is non-fitness related? What expectations do you have (if any) for what they offer in casual shorts?
PART ONE B: Swim Shorts & Lifestyle
1. VISUAL: Imagine that you didn’t have any swim trunks/shorts on hand, and you wanted to go swimming? Upload a screenshot or take a picture of another type of short you own that you might use instead (ie a boardie short).
COMMENT: Have you ever found yourself swimming in non-swim trunks/shorts? If so, what do you find works? If not, why not?
2. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents where you made your last swim short purchase.
COMMENT: Where did you get the last pair of swim shorts that you purchased? How often do you replenish your swim shorts? Have you ever stocked up on one particular style? Why or why not?
3. VISUAL: Upload a photo or screenshot that represents what comes to mind when you think of men’s swimming apparel from lululemon.
COMMENT: Were you aware that lululemon had swim shorts? What would your expectations be of what they offer?
4. VISUAL: Take a minute to check out www.lululemon.com on your phone and search for three styles of shorts: the Surge, the Pacebreaker, and the T.H.E. Upload a screenshot of any style that appeals to you.
COMMENT: What did you choose, and why? What would you think of lululemon creating swim versions of these shorts, like a Surge swim short for example? What, if anything, has held you back from purchasing lululemon casual shorts in the past? What, if anything has held you back from purchasing lululemon swim shorts in the past?
PART TWO: Shopping at lululemon
Time to shop for shorts at your local lululemon store!
5. VISUAL: Enter the store and take a photo of the first place you would go to look for casual shorts.
COMMENT: When you enter the store, where would you first look for casual shorts? How easy is it to find the selection? What is your first impression of the men’s section?
6. VISUAL: Please browse the casual shorts offering and upload photos of anything that you particularly like.
COMMENT: What do you think of the current selection? What gets your attention? What, if anything, turns you off? What brand would you compare this offering to, and why? How does lululemon compare?
7. VISUAL: Now, take a photo of the first place you would go to look for swimwear in the lululemon store.
COMMENT: Where would you go to look at swimwear in the lululemon store? How easy is it to find?
8. VISUAL: Please browse the swimwear offering and upload photos of anything that you particularly like.
COMMENT: What do you think of the current selection? What gets your attention? What, if anything, turns you off? What brand would you compare this offering to, and why? How does lululemon compare?
9. VISUAL: Please try on a pair of swim shorts in store and ask a salesperson or friend to take a picture of you wearing them.
COMMENT: What features do you like about these? What, if anything, is missing that you wish it had?
10. VISUAL: Please try on a pair of casual shorts in store and ask a salesperson or friend to take a picture of you wearing them.
COMMENT: What features do you like about these? What, if anything, is missing that you wish it had?
WRAP-UP!
Time to summarize your thoughts and advice to the lululemon product team!
11. VIDEO: Once you get back home, please create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following:
a. Why did you choose to try on the specific pairs of casual and swim shorts you tried on in store?
b. How did these options compare to what you already own?
c. What would it take for you to buy a swim short from lululemon? And a casual short from lululemon?
d. Any other feedback or advice for the design team in creating new swim or casual shorts?
THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

name: U.S. MVG - Male
Tom
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK® STUDY: Athleisure Discovery

 

INTRODUCTION:

Congratulations on being selected for this study on athleisure’s role in your life and how you explore brands online!

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolve” the post. Resolved posts will have a blue check mark on them. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

PRE-WORK VIDEO

Please upload a selfie, and then complete the following video pre-work assignment during the weekend prior to the study.

 

Before filming, take a moment to prepare and lay out three (3) of your favorite athleisure and/or activewear items on your bed.

 

Now, create a video (or have someone film you using your phone camera) answering the following: 

 

Introduce yourself (just your first name is fine!) then answer these questions FOR EACH ITEM.  If you want to submit three separate videos, that’s cool.  Or you would rather do the three pieces in one take, that is also fine – but please limit the length of the video to about 2 minutes total.

 

1.     What brand is this? Where did you buy it (if online, please specify)? When did you buy it? And why did you buy it?

2.     Roughly how much of your athleisure/activewear wardrobe is made up of this brand?

3.     What do you do while wearing this piece? (Exercise, lounge, etc). We are super interested in what items you choose for certain workout or non-workout activities!

4.     What product characteristics make this item good for doing that?  (Speak to fit, feel, function, style – whatever is important to you and for that activity!)

5.     Finally, how do you feel when wearing it?

 

DAY ONE:  A DAY IN YOUR LIFE!

 

1.     VISUAL: Take a picture of whatever it is that you see when you wake up!

COMMENT: What are we seeing here?  How are you feeling at this moment about the day ahead? 

 

2.     VISUAL: Take a picture or two of anything that is part of your morning ritual, from coffee to breakfast, to your commute, to meditation or exercise.

COMMENT: How do each of these elements make you feel?  What do you get out of it?

 

3.     VISUAL: Upload a few screenshots – or take pictures – of a few things that represent things that bring you JOY or INSPIRE YOU.

COMMENT:

·       What is this? Why are you passionate about this?

·       What is one goal you have that feels difficult to achieve but you REALLY WANT? What is standing in the way (if anything)?

 

4.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of your work/studying or other primary activity during the day.

COMMENT:

·       How do you feel at various points of time during the primary part of your day?

·       What are the “pain points” (if any?)

·       What parts do you generally enjoy the most?

 

5.     VISUAL: Take a picture or upload a representative screenshot of the most SOCIAL part of your day.

COMMENT: Who are you interacting with? How do you feel at these times?

 

6.     VISUAL: Think for a minute about the news and content/entertainment that draws you in (we’ll get to social media in a second.) Upload some screenshots that fill me in on the kind of content you enjoy.

COMMENT: What do you enjoy about these choices? What do you think they say about you?

 

7.     VISUAL: Now consider social media: Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn, Reddit, etc. Upload a screenshot or two that tells me which you engage with the most.

COMMENT:

·       For each, describe your way of participating. Do you observe more, or post more?

·       What do you enjoy about each social platform that you’re involved with? How important is it to you?

·       What brands or influencers do you follow on social media, and what do you get out of it?

·       What is your favorite brand to follow? Why? How has this impacted your perception of the brand? Your likelihood to purchase that brand?

 

8.     VISUAL: If you exercise at all regularly, please upload a picture of you doing what you do – i.e. workout, running, a fitness class, etc.

COMMENT:

·       Why do you exercise?

·       How important is exercising to you?

·       What is your favorite way to sweat? How frequently do you do this – and are there any other parts to your fitness repertoire?

·       How do you feel during exercising? Afterwards? Does this vary by activity?

 

9.     VISUAL:  We’re living in an age of technology obsession. Take a picture of any device or app that you are currently enjoying. 

COMMENT: What do you love about this? Do you ever use any tech as part of your fitness routine (apps, wearables, etc)? Why or why not?

 

10.  VISUAL: When evening rolls around, take a picture that tells me what you do for relaxation, or any other kind of evening activity or ritual.

COMMENT: What is it and what do you like about this?

 

11.  VISUAL: As you reflect on the day, what do you wish you could spend MORE time doing (if anything)? Upload a photo or screenshot to represent that.

COMMENT: Finally, if you had all the time in the world, what would you like to spend more time doing? Why?

 

PLEASE NOTE: Feel free to “ad lib” in this Day in the Life section and share additional photos, screenshots and comments about anything that tells me WHAT MAKES YOU YOU!  Food and drink choice posts are also super relevant and interesting here!

 

DAY TWO: LULULEMON & OTHER BRANDS – HOW DO YOU EXPLORE THEM?

 

12.  VISUAL:  Please take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, travel, sports, etc) that really speak to you. In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”? 

COMMENT:  FOR EACH, please explain why it resonates with you! Do any of these brands in particular align with your core values? If so, how? 

 

13.  VISUAL: When you hear the lululemon name or see the logo, what comes immediately to mind? Upload a screenshot that represents this (it can be anything – be conceptual and creative!).

COMMENT: To what extend would you agree “lululemon is a brand for me” on a scale of 1-5 (with 5 being the strongest)? Why?

name: Occasional Users
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ STUDY:   Chocolate, Life, Desires & You

 

INTRODUCTION:

 

Congratulations on being selected for this Look-Look™ study on life and chocolate!  We wanted you in the study not only because you enjoy Brookside, but also because you are comfortable reflecting on your interests and passions.

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on Look-Look™, please do so now.

 

We are looking to paint the big picture with this study – what does it mean for you to be a happy, multi-faceted woman in today’s world… and how do small pleasures like satisfying the desire for dark chocolate and fruit find a role in the hectic pace of modern life?

 

Below are the instructions for the study.  Please be open, thoughtful and expressive with your responses.  This is not a survey, it’s a conversation!  Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

DAY ONE:  A Day in Your Life

Today, I want to understand what it’s like to be you.  We’d like you to document your day with visuals and send us comments on what you are doing and how you’re  feeling at key points of your day. 

 

Before we get started with that, let’s start with a few questions specific to Brookside – then we’ll on with documenting your day!

 

VISUAL:  Take a picture of where Brookside lives within your home – ie a shelf or elsewhere…

COMMENT:  Tell me the following about Brookside:  (i) Where is this within your home? (ii) Where did you buy this?  Do you always Brookside at the same store?  Why or why not? (iii) What part of the store do you usually find Brookside?  How do you feel about where it is located within the store?  Is there any reminder or message about Brookside that you would like to see within the place you shop?  How top of mind is it when you are doing your food/snack shopping?

 

Thank you!  Now let’s get started with “A Day in My Life!”  Below are a few prompts to get you started.

 

VISUAL:  Take a picture of whatever you see when you wake up in the morning.

COMMENT:  What’s going through my head right now is ____________________.

 

VISUAL:  Take a few shots of your morning ritual(s).  From getting ready to morning coffee, what is the rhythm of your morning?  Show me.

COMMENT:  Here, I’m _____________________________.  Feeling _____________.

 

As you progress through your day, we’re particularly interested in your key activities and what you’re eating and drinking.  If you have Brookside at home, please take a picture of the package and tell me where you bought it and describe where you find it at the store.  What is going through your mind when you reach for it?  Where does it fit into your life?  Do you typically eat it by yourself or share it?  Do you eat it with other things?  If so, what?  What does it add to your life?

 

We are also interested in your media consumption as well as your interface with technology - use of phone for what and when.  With each shot, describe what you are doing, and what you’re feeling.

 

This can include:  work, running around, shopping, errands, spiritual practices, exercise, relaxing, watching TV, listening to music, having fun with friends or family, going out, entertainment, reading/other media, taking care of a pet or loved one… really, anything that normally falls into place during a given weekday.

 

I’m SUPER INTERESTED also in what you are doing when you check your phone.  What are you checking?  Email?  Texts?  Social media?  Games?  Shopping?  Please send me screenshots of each component of your online activity, whether it’s on your phone or on a computer.

 

I will respond with follow up questions a few times throughout the day, so look for the notifications that take you to my questions.  Any thumbnail with a blue dot signals there’s something from me to respond to.

 

This will be different for everyone, but I’m expecting to see about 30 posts from you (give or take 10!) throughout your day and evening.

 

DAY TWO:  Desires, Dreams, and Personal Goals

Now we’re going to zero in on your personal priorities, and what lies ahead for you in life.  Below are the key questions I’d like you to answer, along with the visuals to accompany each comment.  Look out for my follow-ups!

 

1.     VISUAL:  Take a few pictures now (or screenshots) of several things that inspire you!  Anything that gives you energy and inspiration to achieve your dreams, goals, desires, etc.

COMMENT:  This is ______________ and it inspires me because _____________.

 

2.     VISUAL: Next, think about anything you've been contemplating doing in your life that you haven't yet done. Take a picture or grab a screenshot of something that represents that desire/goal and tell me what is holding you back from doing it.

COMMENT:  This is _______________ and it represents my desire to __________.  What might be holding me back from doing this is ________________________.

 

3.     VISUAL:  Next, what are a few of your personal passions?  You may have touched on these yesterday, but really spell it out for me now.  What do you really love and get excited about?  Share a few pictures or screenshots. 

COMMENT:  This is ______________ and I’m passionate about it because _____.

 

4.     VISUAL:  Show me several screenshots of places you go online or on your phone/tablet that are related to ANY of the above subjects – ie your desires, overcoming obstacles, your dreams, and your personal passions.  With each one, please complete the comment below:

COMMENT:  This is ___________.  I go here about (describe frequency – per day, per week, per month, etc).  I go here to get _______________________________.

 

5.     VISUAL:  Take a few screenshots of brands (any category – could be food, fashion, sports, etc) that really speak to you.  In other words, what are a few brands that you truly consider “a brand for me”?  Please explain (for each) why it resonates with you! 

 

PERSONAL VIDEO

Your final task before completion will be to ask a friend or family member to record you talking about a specific subject that your moderator will choose, based on your two-day dialogue.  It will probably be one of your areas of interest/passions.  Stay tuned!  This does not need to feel produced or rehearsed – we just want you to speak honestly from the heart, “off the cuff”, so to speak.

 

THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION!

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: Food at Work Instructions for Participants Welcome to the LookLook® Study on Food and the Modern Workplace! If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your LookLook® screen. The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how people feel at work. In other words, we want to find out what types of physical things can boost your motivation, inspire your creativity, and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable. You can even think beyond food to dry cleaning, a place to collect packages, coffee and juice bars, etc. We’re looking to find out what really matters to people, perhaps some ideas that no one has done before! Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me. In this study, it’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE QUESTIONS BELOW. Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them. Your moderator will be responding to most of your comments and asking follow-up questions. Answering these follow-up questions should take about an additional hour (probably less) and you can complete them in the evening when you are home from work if that is easier. PLEASE NOTE: We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input. The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – i.e., 1a, 1b, etc. THE QUESTIONS: 1) DAY IN THE LIFE
a) Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute? How typical is this – or does it vary by day? 2) Next, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work. Where do you go to get them? (i.e., full-sized cafes, vending, coffee shops, convenience stores?) Please take a picture of any place snacks are offered. For each one, what do you like about it, and tell me what – if anything – you would change about it! 3)  Next, we want to hear about your cafe/cafeteria(s)! Take a trip to the spot you usually frequent and show us the parts that are your favorite and your least favorite. For each of the questions below, post a picture that brings to life the question you are answering:
    1. a)  How could the quality be improved? Are there items you wish were offered that currently are not available?
    2. b)  How could they improve the atmosphere of the cafe/cafeteria?
    3. c)  Does your workplace offer healthy options? If so, what do they look like? Could they be improved in any way?
    4. d)  Is the food service making use of technology to keep things convenient and efficient? What else could they do to improve on that front?
    5. e)  Are you able to personalize your food to the extent that you wish? Are there specific ways they could be more innovative? We want to hear your suggestions!
    6. 4)  This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work.
a) Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work. Please take screenshots of the places near work where you go most often when not eating at the office, and answer the following:
  1. i)  What is the name of this place?
  2. ii)  What do you like about this place?
  3. iii)  How often do you visit?
  4. iv)  What adjectives describe this place?
  1. 5)  Next, we want to hear about your work place:
    1. a)  If you think about your current workplace, what are some of your favorite things offered to employees there?
    2. b)  What three words would you use to describe the culture of your company?
    3.  
  2. 6)  The final part is about some pie-in-the-sky dreaming. What could your work offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, snacks, restaurants, bars, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could an employer possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?
Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS I’ll ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of my follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating! Have fun!

study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™ Study: College Food & Lifestyle

 

Part I:  Complete prior to Wednesday, November 28th.

Part II:  Complete on Thursday, November 29th.

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ UNC Charlotte Food & Lifestyle Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus.

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them!  Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where and what you are eating!  With EACH of those posts, please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS!  You’re getting paid for your opinions as well as showing us what is available to you!

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook™ is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Wednesday, November 28th.

Please complete Part II on Thursday November 29th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee.

 Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Thursday November 29th.

PART I

YOU

1.       FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a.        How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b.       What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience?  Health?  Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?

 

2.       Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots from your camera roll here but make sure to use real photos!

YOUR SCHOOL

3.       Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at UNC.  What adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body?  What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4.       Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus.  This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it.  How can it be improved?  We want details here, down to the condiments for your tea or coffee. 

5.       Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6.       Are you on a meal plan? Why or why not?  If you’re an upperclassman, what do you recall about your experience on the meal plan?

7.       How do you feel about the branded franchises that exist on the UNC campus today (ie coffee shops, fast food etc) – are there others you’d be delighted to see?  Take a picture of one of these if possible.

8.       What do you miss about the way you eat when you’re not at school?  Any aspects of living at home that you miss when it comes to food, drink, etc?

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

9.       Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit.  For each, please answer:  when do you tend to go here?  How often?  Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? 

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL

10.    We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that.  It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

a.        What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends?

b.       What are you eating?

c.        Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now?

d.       What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts?  What was great – or what could be better?

 

11.    PIE IN THE SKY

a.       What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?

 

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

name: Unassigned
study_instructions: Once again, we loved your feedback on the very fun topic of handbags last month! Your sophistication and attention to detail continue to impress us and those of you that did screen recordings – thank you! They were full of insights about what speaks to you during the process of browsing. This month, we need your expertise on a very different topic. There are truly many aspects of maintaining a luxury brand that are important today, from the integrity of the product to all-important creativity, and in this set of topics and questions we want your honest opinions on how a luxury house can best communicate its social responsibility, as a global force in a changing world. This is not a place to showcase political correctness; we want (as always) your bone honest opinions on what MATTERS to you. Pictures and video are less important this month than your thoughtful consideration and verbal responses. Please complete by Wednesday, July 7th! Follow-ups will be posted starting on Thursday, July 8th.

name: American Participants
study_instructions: You wowed us with the responses to the first month’s queries. Thank you for such thoughtful responses. This month, we’re going to take a big step back and reflect on this moment in time. As the U.S. moves towards its vaccination goals, more people are traveling and shopping than they have in a long time. We’re interested in your mindset during this moment of transition as the ground is still shaking from many disruptive forces.For this set of questions, please complete by Friday, May 7th! And please be sure to punctuate your responses with screenshots – it really makes it so much more personal and interesting to read – thanks!

name: Gen Y Fashion
study_instructions: Congrats on being selected for this fun study on fashion and your lifestyle in the 21st century! Virtual fashion is a somewhat futuristic topic, and we’ll be sharing several concepts and ideas with you. There are absolutely no right or wrong answers to anything! We are simply curious about what aspects of these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Because it is such an experiential idea, we’ll be asking you to go online and on your phone as part of this study to try out some new technologies, which are in the early stages… so a lot of this will be about using your imagination and thinking conceptually. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. If screen recordings are new for you, let us know and we’ll send you demos. All of this visual feedback is super important; it brings everything to life. Please complete your responses by Friday August 6th. Starting on an assigned day around August 7-11, your moderator will post some follow-up questions, and you’ll have an entire day and evening to respond to the follow-ups, which will complete the study.

name: Freshmen
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® Study: Campus Life and Food!

 

Part I:  Complete by Monday 9 pm, February 18th

Part II:  Complete on Tuesday 5 pm, February 19th

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK® Campus Life and Food Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK® screen.

This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus.

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them!  Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where and what you are eating!  With EACH of those posts, please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS!  You’re getting paid for your thoughtful opinions! J

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

Please complete Part I by 9 pm on Monday February 18th

Please complete Part II on Tuesday February 19th, PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee.

 Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Tuesday February 19th.

PART I

YOU

1.     FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a.     How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b.     What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience?  Health?  Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?

 

2.     Describe (through a few pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  Please comment on the following:  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends?

YOUR SCHOOL

3.     Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at your school.  What three adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture at your school? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body?  What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4.     Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus.  This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it. How can it be improved?  We want details here, down to the condiments you prefer for your tea or coffee. 

5.     Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6.     Take pictures of any branded franchises that exist on your campus today (i.e., coffee shops, fast food etc) and tell me if you ever frequent them, and why or why not.  Are there others you’d be delighted to see? If so, upload screenshots of them and tell me what you would like about adding them! 

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

7.     Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit.  For each, please answer:  when do you tend to go here?  How often?  Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? 

FOOD JOURNAL (A) (DINNER, LATE NIGHT SNACKS)

In an effort to make tomorrow’s food journal a little easier to navigate we ask that you make your dinner post tonight. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that. It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Tonight, when you eat dinner, please snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context.  Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

8.What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).

9.What are you eating?

10. Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?

11.  What details are important – how is the QUALITY?  HEALTHINESS?  CONVENIENCE FACTOR?  PERSONALIZATION FACTOR?  What was great – or what could be better?

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL (B) (BREAKFAST, LUNCH, SNACKS – THROUGH LATE AFTERNOON)

Today’s food journal will follow the same format as food journal (A) and should include your first meal or beverage of the day, coffee (if you drink it), any snacks or refreshments you have throughout the morning, your lunch, and any afternoon snacks. We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that.  It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of the place where you are eating or drinking because we want to see the context.  Then tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

12.  What time is it?  Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends? (please make clear WHERE YOU ARE).

13.  What are you eating?

14.  Why did you choose this particular place at this moment?

15.  What details are important – how is the QUALITY?  HEALTHINESS?  CONVENIENCE FACTOR?  PERSONALIZATION FACTOR?  What was great – or what could be better?

Once you’ve made your last afternoon snacks post you can continue on to PIE IN THE SKY.

PIE IN THE SKY

16.  What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. 

Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions.

name: Regulars
study_instructions:
Welcome back!!  We're excited to share some new ideas about Nabisco and what the brand stands for. Nabisco has some major product evolutions in the works and brand activations that I think you will enjoy hearing about in this final phase of the study.
We'll be sharing two distinct new ideas with you for your honest feedback. It's REALLY IMPORTANT that you understand this is NOT ADVERTISING. 
What you'll see are two sets of ideas (each has two parts) that describe a NEW DIRECTION for the brand. We want to know which direction you find most intriguing, bold and compelling. Which one really nails it for you and may even get you a little excited about what Nabisco is becoming?
Thanks in advance for your thoughtful attention to this MOST important part of the project!

name: Freshmen
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK™ Study: College Food & Lifestyle

 

Part I:  Complete prior to Wednesday, November 28th.

Part II:  Complete on Thursday, November 29th.

 

Welcome to the LOOKLOOK™ UNC Charlotte Food & Lifestyle Study!  If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

This study is all about understanding how you make choices about where, what, why and how you eat – both on campus and off campus.

PART ONE (DAY ONE) – we need you to pay close attention to the questions below and answer them!  Please reference the question number (1a, 2b, etc) in your responses.

PART TWO (DAY TWO) – we’re going to follow you around during a typical day to see where and what you are eating!  With EACH of those posts, please answer questions 10a-d in full.

PLEASE, NO ONE WORD ANSWERS!  You’re getting paid for your opinions as well as showing us what is available to you!

We realize you are busy – and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences.  That’s ok – the beauty of LookLook™ is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments.  POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!

HERE ARE THE TASKS:

Please complete Part I by 3:00 pm on Wednesday, November 28th.

Please complete Part II on Thursday November 29th. PART II SHOULD START IN THE MORNING, at breakfast or when you’re grabbing coffee.

 Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day on Thursday November 29th.

PART I

YOU

1.       FIRST OFF, we want to know a little about you. Upload a picture that demonstrates the relationship you have with food, and comment on the following:

a.        How does it affect your mood and how you feel on a daily basis?

b.       What is important to you when it comes to food? Convenience?  Health?  Quality of the food? Ability to personalize it?

 

2.       Describe (through pictures or screen shots) what your daily routine is like.  How much time do you spend in class vs. studying vs. work vs. hanging out with friends? Feel free to use screen shots from your camera roll here but make sure to use real photos!

YOUR SCHOOL

3.       Upload a picture that conceptually represents the unique culture at UNC.  What adjectives would you use to describe the campus culture? What adjectives would you use to describe the student body?  What makes this place unique?

FOOD AT YOUR SCHOOL

4.       Please take pictures of any dining facilities you use most often on campus.  This can include anything from a café to a vending machine or convenience store! With each, please describe what you are sharing and what you get out of it.  How can it be improved?  We want details here, down to the condiments for your tea or coffee. 

5.       Upload a photo that represents how you feel overall about the current campus dining experience at your school. Why have you chosen this and what does it represent?

6.       Are you on a meal plan? Why or why not?  If you’re an upperclassman, what do you recall about your experience on the meal plan?

7.       How do you feel about the branded franchises that exist on the UNC campus today (ie coffee shops, fast food etc) – are there others you’d be delighted to see?  Take a picture of one of these if possible.

8.       What do you miss about the way you eat when you’re not at school?  Any aspects of living at home that you miss when it comes to food, drink, etc?

FOOD AWAY FROM SCHOOL

9.       Now let’s talk about where you go to eat off campus. Upload some screen shots of places you most often visit.  For each, please answer:  when do you tend to go here?  How often?  Why do you choose it? What does this place have that you can’t find on campus? In general, how often would you say you go off campus to eat or drink? 

PART II

FOOD JOURNAL

10.    We want to understand where you choose to eat and drink during a typical day, and how your campus dining options fit into that.  It’s really important to just behave as you normally would and go about your day; you’re just taking us along with you. Throughout the day, snap a picture of whatever you are eating or drinking, and tell us the following WITH EACH PICTURE.

a.        What time is it? Where are you? Are you on-campus, or off-campus? Name of venue? Alone or with friends?

b.       What are you eating?

c.        Why did you feel like eating this at this particular place now?

d.       What details are important – like technology, service, atmosphere – anything that adds or detracts?  What was great – or what could be better?

 

11.    PIE IN THE SKY

a.       What could your college offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day? This could be new cafes, ethnic cuisines, snacks, restaurants, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life. Think beyond food and drink. What else could your college offer you that would improve your quality of life on a daily basis? For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?

 

PLEASE NOTE: We want to see REAL LIFE – the good, the bad and the ugly. We want to see the food you are proud of, and anything you may not be proud of.  Cold pizza for breakfast is totally expected. The more honest and thorough you are the better job you will be doing with this study.

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS that the moderator will ask you about your comments and your pictures. You will be compensated when you have answered all of the moderator’s follow-up questions. Thanks so much for participating!

恭喜您被甄选为本次有关运动服饰尺码合身问题调研的参与者！
本次调研中，我们将会邀请您和我们分享您过往购买运动服饰品牌的经历以及在实体店和线上购物中关于尺码和试穿等问题的反馈。
当您进入调研的页面中，您的主页上会出现不同的圆圈，每个圈都会代表一个大的话题，每个话题下会分别有一些小问题需要您的回答，根据题目提示，会需要您发表您的观点，上传相关图片，截屏，或者录制并上传相关短片视频。
在您回答之后，主持人会进行随机的追问，您可以进入到相关问题下再次回答。在追问环节结束后，您的话题圆圈会从之前的“橙色”变成“蓝色”这表示该话题下的问题已全部完成，直到所有的话题圆圈均变成蓝色，此次调研才算全部结束。
我们希望您能真诚如实地回答我们的问题，这将对我们的调研起到非常至关重要的作用。我们希望通过这次机会和您进行一次隔空“对话”而不是书面调查！请您放心，调研中您给予的所有回答，资料和信息，我们都将严格保密。我们非常尊重您的隐私并希望您也能对本次调研中所看到的信息进行保密。
最后，衷心感谢您和我们分享您的看法并献出您宝贵的时间参与此次调研！
在调研中我们会经常提到运动服饰以及非运动服饰，为了让您有更清楚的认识，我们对于这两个概念的解释分别是：
运动服饰：您锻炼时所穿的服装，比如：打底紧身裤，慢跑运动裤，短裤，运动上衣，运动胸衣等
非运动服饰：日常休闲服饰，比如牛仔裤，长裤，T恤，长袖上衣，连帽衫，线衫等

name: Users
study_instructions:
STUDY INSTRUCTIONS

 

Welcome to the Skin Care Study.

 

You've been selected for this particular study because you are loyal to a skin care brand.

 

Below are the tasks that we need you complete.  We're just looking for your honest opinions so have fun and we can't wait to see what you show us!

 

We estimate that answering the questions, taking the pictures and recording the video will take a total of two and a half hours to complete -  two hours for the tasks, and an additional half an hour to respond to follow-up questions throughout.

 

You can work through the study at your leisure – just make sure to check for follow-up questions from the moderator on your previous posts as you go along.

 

THE TASKS

 

DAY ONE

 

FIRST, show me the skin care products you are most loyal to, and tell me why. You may have two, you may have ten – everyone prioritizes differently.  We do not need to see your makeup choices – just skin care. Photograph each item that is currently part of your routine and for each item, answer the following:

1.     Is it a favorite or something new that you're trying?  

2.     How long have you been using it?

3.     Is it a product you’re loyal to – and if so, why?

4.     What do you want from the product, and how is it performing for you?

 

SECOND, let’s focus on cleansers and moisturizers specifically for a minute.

1.     Are you more interested in a cleanser that prevents problems, or one that fixes problems?

2.     Are you more interested in a moisturizer that prevents problems, or one that fixes problems?

3.     Do gentle cleansers clean well?

 

THIRD, let’s talk conceptually about how you feel about your skin on a daily basis. 

6.     What does “skin health” mean to you?

7.     If you were to talk to your face in the morning – what would you say to your skin?

8.     If you were to talk to your face at night, what would you say to your skin?

 

FINALLY, let’s discuss what influences your choices.

9.     Do you like to discover new skin care products, trends and innovations?  Or do you typically like to stick with familiar favorites?

10.  If you do like to check out new products, show me through pictures and be as specific as possible.  If it’s blogs or vlogs, take screen shots.  If it’s through magazines (online or print), show me that.  Perhaps it’s through websites or by shopping in stores?  Take screen shots to show me.

 

DAY TWO

 

Today, you're going shopping!  Choose a drug, mass merchandiser or grocery store where you typically buy skin care products.  We realize that you may shop online for some products but we'd like to start in an actual store.

 

Please wander as you normally would and stop wherever you are interested.  Take pictures of whatever catches your eye, and describe why it got your attention. For each product, answer these questions:

 

1.     Are you finding any brands you might consider trying? If so, why - what stands out about those brands?

2.     We are really curious about what draws you in – ie the display, the brand name, packaging, any messaging on that packaging, etc.  If you do find a product that you're tempted to try, please photograph and then define – why does it appeal to you?

 

Next, find the section with Cetaphil products. Take a photo of the Cetaphil products and answer the following questions:

 

3.     Just based on appearance, how would you compare Cetaphil with the other brands on the shelf?

4.     What three descriptive adjectives come to mind when you see the Cetaphil products? 

5.     Which are your favorite Cetaphil products and what do you like about it/them?

6.     Are there any Cetaphil products catching your eye that you haven’t tried before?

 

FINALLY, please have someone record you while you create 2 separate videos for us. Each should be roughly a minute in length.  Think about your answers to the questions first, then answer the following questions:

 

VIDEO ONE

·      What makes a good skin day?

·      Is your skin your friend, or your enemy?

·      If facial cleansers/moisturizers didn’t exist, how would your life change?

·      How do you show your skin you care, and keep it out of trouble?

 

VIDEO TWO

·      Now, sell me Cetaphil as if I were your friend – what would you say to get me to persuade me to try it?  In making this argument, please start with this phrase: “The reason I love Cetaphil is…….” then make your case!

 

Thank you for your participation!  You are complete when you have answered all of our follow-up questions.

We are very excited to have you participate in our research project! As was previously mentioned to you, prior to the online group discussion we would like to get to know you a little bit, and the way we would like to do this is by having you create some brief videos. 

A few things to keep in mind when recording your videos:
• Sometimes it helps to have a friend or family member hold the camera so you can focus on what you are talking about rather than worrying about holding the camera.
• Make sure you or whoever is filming holds the camera as still as possible (no shaking or jarring movements).
• Avoid any background noise or music - this often becomes much louder in the recording.
• Pause for two seconds at the beginning and end of your video to make sure your response isn't cut off at all.
• Before submitting your video(s), watch it to make sure everything looks/sounds okay:  
• Are you facing the right direction? It's easy to accidentally end up with sideways footage if you turn your smartphone while filming, and we want to avoid that happening!
• Is the lighting bright enough so we can see you and what you are recoding?
• Did you speak loud enough so we can clearly hear all that you are saying?

study_instructions:
Welcome to the Luxury Jewelry and Watches Study!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

You have been chosen for this very selective study because you have great taste, and you buy luxury jewelry. This is not a focus group, although we do want your opinions. But we also want your input on how to revitalize a storied European luxury jewelry and watches brand. Therefore, we refer to this type of project as co-creation. We are looking for your ideas as well as your honest take on some jewelry designs. The voice of this brand should be developed to reach women like you.

We appreciate how busy you all are. In order for the study to be successful, the following questions must be completed and submitted on LOOKLOOK™ prior to the first scheduled day of your participation. Please do ‘Task 1: Selfie Time’ and answer all 4 questions and their subparts.

FIRST TASK: IT’S SELFIE TIME!

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before proceeding. Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment, and sends when you tap the checkmark in the lower right- hand corner of your LOOKLOOK™ screen.

Now, please upload photos of yourself wearing the pieces of jewelry you described to Susan when you spoke. For each of the pictures you have sent, please specify:

o   Was this a gift or did you buy it for yourself?  

o   Where was it purchased?

o   How did you discover this piece? What made you covet it?

THE QUESTIONS

On LOOKLOOK™, you will be prompted where to put these answers.

1.    SHOPPING FOR THE JEWELRY AND WATCH BRANDS YOU LOVE

 

a.    When you purchase jewelry, is it typically for a milestone, a seasonal  purchase, or an impulse buy?

b.   What are 1 or 2 of your favorite luxury jewelry/watch brands, and why?

c.    Do you browse for jewelry in stores or online?

o   If you browse in store, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite stores.

o   If you browse online, please list 1 or 2 of your favorite sites.

d.   When it’s time to purchase jewelry, do you do it in store or online? Or both?

e.    Is it different for watches?

 

2.    TELL ME ABOUT YOUR STYLE

 

a.    What 3  adjectives would you choose to describe your personal style (in general?)

b.   Please also upload 2 or 3 photos that demonstrate how you like to wear jewelry.

o   What rings do you wear?

o   What is your wrist look? Do you like to stack, mix designs, alloys, etc. or do you prefer to match?

o   What earring do you like to wear? Studs, cuffs, drop, etc.?

o   What necklaces do you like to wear? Do you like to layer them or wear one at a time?

o   Do you wear the same jewelry day and night or do you switch for evening?

c.    Do your jewelry pieces serve different needs (ie investment, statement, everyday)? How often do you  make fine jewelry purchases?

d.   List 1 or 2 of your favorite brands outside of jewelry (can be anything!)

 

3.YOUR MEDIA DIET

 

a.    Which of the following media do you use regularly (for anything – in general – not just shopping!)

o   Social media - If yes, what platforms?  

o   Websites - What sites?

o   Print magazines - Which ones? Subscribe or buy occasionally?  

o   Anything else? (Satellite Radio? Podcasts?)

o   TV Shows (Netflix? Cable?)

 

4.    WHAT YOU LOVE

a.    What are you most passionate about in life – other than your family? Take a  screenshot or picture that illustrates 1 or 2 of those interests.

b.   Where do you like to travel? 

c.    What happens to be on your wish list for your next jewelry purchase? Why do you love it? How did it get on your radar?

 

Thank you for completing the questions above! On your scheduled day of participation, your moderator will let you know what brand we are focusing on for the remainder of the study, and will start unveiling the pieces to you for your feedback! You get to take a break from sending us pictures.

At the time, please respond to your moderator’s queries on each specific piece. When you are done, your moderator will send through a bit of the background story on the brand we’re focusing on. Once you’ve read that, you are done with Day One!  

The focus of Day Two will be helping us come up with great creative ideas!

name: Potential Guest - Online (Shopping for Female)
Non-Freshman
Korean Participants
study_instructions: 지난 달에 참여해주신 설문조사의 여러분들의 답변은 정말 훌륭했습니다! 저희는 전 세계적으로 넓은 범위의 응답들을 받기 때문에 여러분들의 의견을 정말 소중히 생각합니다. 정성 어린, 구체적인 답변에 다시 한번 감사의 말씀을 드립니다. 6월의 스터디에서는 온라인 쇼핑에 100% 집중할 것 입니다! 여러분들이 아이템을 구매하기 전에 어떤 식으로 인터넷 서칭을 하고 어떤 과정을 통해 심사 숙고 하는지에 대해 이해해보고자 합니다.주의 사항: 여러분들이 업로드 해주시는 사진은 굉장히 굉장히! 중요합니다. 사진들은 여러분들의 답변을 훨씬 더 실감나게 해줍니다. 여러분들의 답변에 사진들을 포함해주시면 정말 감사하겠습니다.이 질문 세트들은 6/5까지 완료해 주시길 바랍니다.

name: Non-Purchaser (under 35)
Male Season Ticket Holders/Group Ticket Buyers
study_instructions:
Congratulations on being selected for this very fun study on The Fever!
In this study, you’ll be telling us about your connection to The Fever and how you engage with your love of sports, particularly basketball!
Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study.  
For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and provide a thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.
Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: Travelers
study_instructions: Congratulations on being selected for this study on the role of airport lounges in travel!Each topic on your home screen will explore a different aspect of this experience. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups on most questions.Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only. There are no right or wrong answers; we want total honesty!

name: Sophomores
study_instructions: Welcome to the LookLook® Food at School Study!In this study, you’ll be our eyes on your campus - showing us the options you have available to you and the choices you make!We realize you are busy - and sometimes can’t comment “in the moment” as you are documenting your experiences. That’s ok - the beauty of LookLook® is that you can snap pictures, save to your camera roll, and upload them later when you have time to write the comments. POST WHEN YOU ARE CONNECTED TO STRONG WIFI FOR BEST RESULTS!Each of the topic circles on your home screen will explore a different aspect of the study. For each question, upload the comment, photo, screenshot, and/or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. After you type a comment, make sure to hit SEND so your comment is saved before you move on to another question. Your moderator will respond to your posts by asking you follow up questions.When your moderator is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator will “resolve” the post with a blue checkmark. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.TOPIC 2 (The Food Journal) is the most important part of this study! Please choose a school day when you can devote time to documenting everything you eat and drink.WE DON'T NEED PICTURES OF FOOD THAT WE COULD FIND OURSELVES ON THE INTERNET. For ex., we don’t need just a picture of an orange for breakfast. Show us context and tell us where you are! Seeing some actual people in the photos is also great!We want pictures of actual good and bad food (especially bad food), good and bad food presentation (especially bad) and good and bad logistical setups.The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study. All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Thanks so much for making your voice heard!

name: Germany
study_instructions:
Herzlichen Glückwunsch das Du für diese interessante und wichtige Studie zu Kleidung und Markenbotschaften ausgewählt wurdest!
In dieser Studie erzählst Du uns von deinen Erfahrungen beim Kauf von Sport- / Aktivbekleidungsmarken und gibst uns Feedback zu bestimmten Markenbotschaften und  Konzepten. 
Jeder der Themenkreise auf Deinem Startbildschirm erforscht einen anderen Aspekt der Studie. Lade für jede Frage das passende Kommentar, das Foto, den Screenshot und / oder das Video hoch und bitte beantworte die entsprechende Frage sorgfältig.
Wenn Deine Moderatorin mit einem Konversationsthema zufrieden ist, schliesst die Moderatorin den Beitrag mit einem blauen Häkchen ab. Du bist fertig, wenn alle Deine Beiträge geschlossen sind.
Je ehrlicher und ausdrucksfähiger Du bist, desto besser wirst Du diese Studie bearbeiten können. Alle Informationen werden ausschließlich zu Forschungszwecken und STRENG VERTRAULICH behandelt. Vielen Dank, dass Du Deine Stimme gibst!

name: Manufacturing Business Decision Makers
study_instructions: Welcome to Part 2 of our discussion on CAD | CAM | CAE programs. Your input was so insightful and helpful the first time around that we now want to invite you into the creative process a bit. Based on your feedback, some new creative layouts have been developed and we would love to get your reactions to them. When you engage with the topics and questions, please reply with an honest, thorough, and thoughtful answer. On the day specified by your recruiter, a moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved. Your responses are anonymized and are STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. There are no “wrong” answers; we just want your honest opinions! Thanks!

name: Ambassadors
study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: Fitness Gear, Props and Accessories

Congratulations on being selected for this study on fitness gear, props and accessories! You’ve been selected for this elite panel because you are serious about your fitness, your wellness and specifically because you are into at least one of these three fitness activities:

(a)   Running

(b)   Training

(c)    Yoga/Barre/Pilates

 

While you may take part in a number of fitness activities, we specifically want to explore the gear and accessories you invest in for your primary fitness activities – the ones you take most seriously and do most often – as well as any other health and wellness focused activities.

   

Fitness accessories can be anything from what you carry to and from a work out, to what you use during, or after a workout! (i.e. socks, bags, mats, at-home equipment, rollers, massage balls, cold weather accessories – anything!)

 

If you have not yet uploaded a selfie on LookLook®, please do so now.

 

Below are the instructions for the study. For each question, upload the photo, screenshot, or video requested and carefully answer the corresponding questions. Your moderator will ask you follow ups throughout the day. When he or she is satisfied with a conversation thread, the moderator “resolves” the post with a blue check mark. Check unresolved posts (any post without a blue check mark) to see if there is a follow-up awaiting a response. You will be complete when all of your posts are resolved.

 

Please be open, honest and expressive with your responses. This is not a survey, it’s a conversation! Everything you share is for research purposes only.

 

OVERVIEW:

There are three parts to this study. 

(i)              First, we want to get to know you a bit. You can answer these questions as soon as you post your selfie.

(ii)            Next, we want you to keep a diary of how you use your gear/props/accessories for two separate workout occasions over the next four days, ideally one day over the weekend and one day over the week. (We want to see how your weekend fitness activity may be different from a weekday.)

(iii)           Finally, as a bit of a wrap-up on Tuesday June 11th we’ll be engaging in some back and forth discussion about how your fitness activity fits into your overall wellness strategy!

 

 

GETTING TO KNOW YOU: A DEEP DIVE ON BAGS AND SOCKS

 

1.     VISUAL: Think about an image that represents how you feel when you get the MOST out of your workout routine and post a screenshot that depicts that feeling. COMMENT: Tell me why you chose this and provide a few adjectives that describe the feeling.

 

2.     VIDEO – YOUR SOCK WARDROBE: Gather all of the socks that you wear most frequently both to work out and in day to day life. Choose only items you purchased for yourself (no gifts or generic items; we’re interested in brands here.) Group your socks into categories and lay them out. Then have a friend or family member film you while you show me the socks in each category and answer the following:

a.     Why did you group the socks into these categories? Which socks do you use for fitness and which are worn day to day, and which for both? What features make a sock good for one or the other, or both?

b.    What do you get out these socks? What benefits do each of the categories provide?

c.     What brands are your socks? What do you count on those brands for when it comes to socks?

name: Participants
study_instructions:
LOOK-LOOK™ Study:  Food at Work 

Instructions for Participants

 

Welcome to the LOOK-LOOK™ Study on Food and the Modern Workplace!

 

If you have not sent a selfie yet to confirm your participation, please do so before continuing.  Every picture has to be accompanied by a comment and sends when you tap the arrow in the lower right-hand corner of your LOOK-LOOK™ screen.

 

The purpose of this study is for us to get a firsthand sense of how eating, drinking and other types of value-added experiences affect how people feel at work.  In other words, we want to find out what types of physical things can boost your motivation, inspire your creativity, and/or just make life easier or more enjoyable. You can even think beyond food to dry cleaning, a place to collect packages, coffee and juice bars, etc. We’re looking to find out what really matters to people, perhaps some ideas that no one has done before!

 

Your task for this study is to THOUGHTFULLY answer each of the questions below

– and accompany each with a picture that you either take or save as a screen grab then use the app to send to me.

 

In this study, it’s all about the details so NO ONE-WORD COMMENTS TO THE QUESTIONS BELOW

 

Collectively, completing the tasks below should take about one hour to complete, and you can divide them up during your day when you have time to thoughtfully answer them. Your moderator will be responding to most of your comments and asking follow-up questions. Answering these follow-up questions should take about an additional hour (probably less) and you can complete them in the evening when you are home from work if that is easier.

 

PLEASE NOTE:  We want total, candid honesty. There is no right way or wrong way to answer these questions – we just want genuine input.  The more honest and thorough you are, the better job you will be doing with this study.

 

All information will be held STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL for research purposes only. Please create a new post and submit AT LEAST one picture (or screen grab) for each topic outlined below – i.e., 1a, 1b, etc.   

 

THE QUESTIONS:

 

1)    DAY IN THE LIFE

a. Show me what you eat for breakfast! Describe what is in the picture: is this at home, at work, during your commute? How typical is this – or does it vary by day?

 

2) Next, show me what is available for you to eat and drink SNACKWISE while at work. Where do you go to get them?  (i.e., full-sized cafes, vending, coffee shops, convenience stores?) Please take a picture of any place snacks are offered.  For each one, what do you like about it, and tell me what – if anything – you would change about it!

 

3) Next, we want to hear about your cafe/cafeteria(s)! Take a trip to the spot you usually frequent and show us the parts that are your favorite and your least favorite.  For each of the questions below, post a picture that brings to life the question you are answering:

a. How could the quality be improved? Are there items you wish were offered that currently are not available?

b.    How could they improve the atmosphere of the cafe/cafeteria?

c. Does your workplace offer healthy options? If so, what do they look like?  Could they be improved in any way?

d.    Is the food service making use of technology to keep things convenient and efficient?  What else could they do to improve on that front?

e.    Are you able to personalize your food to the extent that you wish?

Are there specific ways they could be more innovative?  We want to hear your suggestions!

 

4)    This section is about where you like to eat AWAY from work.

a. Think about the options that exist around your workplace, and the places you go when you want to get away from work.  Please take screenshots of the places near work where you go most often when not eating at the office, and answer the following:

i.    What is the name of this place?

ii.    What do you like about this place?  

iii.    How often do you visit?  

iv.    What adjectives describe this place?  

 

5)     Next, we want to hear about your work place:

a. If you think about your current workplace, what are some of your favorite things offered to employees there?

b. What three words would you use to describe the culture of your company?

 

6)     The final part is about some pie-in-the-sky dreaming.  What could your work offer that would really blow your mind – surprise and delight you when it comes to food and drink fueling your day?  This could be new cafes, snacks, restaurants, bars, juice bars, anything you can think of. Submit some screen grabs that bring these ideas to life.  Think beyond food and drink.  What else could an employer possibly offer you that could make it easier to live the life you want to live on a daily basis?  For each idea, please answer: Why would this be on your wish list?

 

Please answer ALL THE QUESTIONS I’ll ask you about your comments and your pictures.  You will be compensated when you have answered all of my follow-up questions.

 

Thanks so much for participating!  Have fun!

We are simply curious about what aspects of these ideas get you excited, what doesn’t, and why. Because it is such an experiential idea, we’ll be asking you to go online and on your phone as part of this study to try out some new technologies, which are in the early stages… so a lot of this will be about using your imagination and thinking conceptually. Finally, we will be asking for screenshots and screen recordings. study_instructions:
LOOKLOOK® STUDY: User Experience on LookLook®
INTRODUCTION:
Thanks for participating in this study on our own product! We really value your opinion and are eager to get your objective feedback on what it is like to be contacted for a study, participate, and ways in which we can make use of the app a better experience!
As always, there are no right or wrong answers, and we really do want your bone honesty! Truly – do not mince words or hesitate to tell us anything negative – we want to find ways to improve! 
PART ONE: Study Experience
1. VISUAL: Upload a screenshot or emoji that represented how you felt (if you can remember) the first time you were contacted by SPARK.
COMMENT: Were you called/emailed? Had you ever participated in a market research study before – and if so, did this sound similar or different in any way? Was it easy to find the app on iTunes or Google Play? What did you think of the download instructions – were they clear, and professional – or confusing in any way?
2. VISUAL: Post a picture of the log on page for LookLook®.
COMMENT: When you are done with a study, do you delete the app or keep it on your phone? Do you get notified when there is an update to the app? Is there anything about the logon process that is problematic?
3. VISUAL: Post a screenshot of study instructions from a study you’ve participated in.
COMMENT: Do you tend to use the PDF instructions or the instructions on the app to complete a study (or both), and why? In your experience, what works about the way we are currently providing instructions? Is there any way we could make this easier? For example, serving up one question at a time? Or would that slow you down…?
4. VISUAL: Post a screenshot of your LookLook® home screen that contains your list of posts.
COMMENT: Is it easy for you to reference which posts are resolved (with the checkmark)? In your experience, has your moderator maintained a good pace of dialogue with you? Too much, too little? Too frequent, or too infrequent?
5. VISUAL: Tap the camera icon and post a screenshot of the screen that gives you the upload picture/take a video option.
COMMENT: Have you ever had trouble posting a picture or video? If so, please describe your experience? How did you report the problem? Was it resolved promptly – or were you left hanging? What about notifications – are they useful? Why or why not?
6. VISUAL: Post an emoji that represents your satisfaction with the speed of LookLook® and your experience with WiFi connectivity.
COMMENT: Have you ever experienced any issues with the LookLook application's server/internet connection? Have you ever received an error message of any kind? If so, how was it resolved?
7. VISUAL: Post an emoji that represents your overall satisfaction with the experience of participating in a study.
COMMENT: How exciting and motivating is it to participate in a LookLook® study? Did you feel you were able to complete the study successfully? Why or why not?
PART TWO: Ideas for Development
In this next section, we’re going to post a number of ideas. For each, please give us a rating of 1-10 (10 being strongest) in terms of your enthusiasm for it, and then comment as indicated below.
[THESE WILL COME WEDNESDAY AFTER PART ONE IS COMPLETE].
